shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Rahul, no run
text: good length and just outside off, not too much movement on that one, gets forward and pats it into the off side off the middle

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Rahul, no run
text: good length and just outside off, not too much movement on that one, gets forward and pats it into the off side off the middle

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Rahul, no run
text: good length and a hint of shape inwards this time, Rahul leans into a cover drive but this nips back in and goes off the sticker

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Rahul, 1 run
text: good length at middle stump, closes the face and turns it into the leg side

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Sharma, OUT
wkt_text: RG Sharma lbw b Shaheen Shah Afridi 0 (6m 1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00
text: bang on the money! Peak Shaheen. What a bowler. This is yorker length, marginal bend inwards, nothing exagerrated. But the direction on this and the pace on it have given Rohit no chance. He's hurriedly getting the front leg out of the way as it curves in late and trying to whip it through midwicket. He's caught in front of middle stump on his back leg. Too good to sort that out first ball

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Kohli, no run
text: good length and rising in the corridor, left alone

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Kohli, 1 run
text: good length and just outside off, leans in and pushes with hard hands. Gets it off the inside half, bat turning, and a single at midwicket
good length and curved into the pad, clipped with the angle to short fine

shortText: Imad Wasim to Rahul, no run
text: full and just outside off, another arm ball, driven to extra cover
good length and floated in at leg stump, pushed through square leg off the back foot
good length and in at middle stump, leans in and pushes towards long-on

shortText: Imad Wasim to Rahul, no run
text: good length and tight at middle and leg, patted to midwicket off the back foot
good length at middle stump, punched to long-on off the back foot

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Rahul, OUT
text: and another! Rahul's played around this and lost his wickets. Shaheen Afridi is spitting fire here! India have no answers at the moment. This is good length, shaped in from the corridor off stump. Rahul leans in and closes the face on it to try and play with the angle into him. It looks like he's missed and this has gone off the thigh and into the stumps. Might have been an inside edge first too. Fully cramped and playing across the line

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Yadav, no run
text: good length and across off stump, pushed to extra cover off the front foot

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Yadav, no run
text: low full toss just outside off, looks to whip it into the leg side, toe-ends it

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Yadav, 1 run
text: full and just outside off, shuffles and mistimes a flick to mid-on's right

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Kohli, 1 run
text: good length at leg stump, leans in and flicks to deep square

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Yadav, SIX
text: just clears deep square! Heart in the mouth for a moment there for sure if you're the batter, but that is crisply struck. It's short and slanted across the corridor but he doesn't let it go across him. Closes the face on it, brings out his quick wrists and gets this short-arm pull over the man

shortText: Imad Wasim to Kohli, no run
text: good length at middle stump, pushed into the leg side

shortText: Imad Wasim to Kohli, no run
text: good length and at middle stump, gets well forward and pushes in front of the body
good length at middle stump, punched down to long-on with the angle

shortText: Imad Wasim to Yadav, 1 leg bye
text: big appeal for lbw but he was outside off when he was struck I think. Rizwan has a word with Babar and then there's no review. Full ball outside off, misses on the sweep, takes the leg bye at short third
good length at off stump, gets forward and jabs into the covers
lovely shot. Vintage SKY. Good length at leg stump, gets down swiftly and sweeps confidently past short fine

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Kohli, 2 runs
text: good length and across middle stump, walks down at that and flicks into the vacant midwicket region to pick up two to deep square's left

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Kohli, no run
text: good length and just outside off, down the track again and pushes into the covers

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Kohli, no run
text: good length and tight at off stump, stays deep in the crease and can only steer this to point with an open face

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Kohli, no run
text: offcutter at a length, just outside off. Driven on the rise to cover point

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Kohli, SIX
text: sweeeet. This has been clattered. Good length ball at middle and leg, rising up at Kohli who has walked into the leg side. And he uses that bounce and his wrists to whip this over mid-on. And it's come off the absolute middle of the bat before its flown over the boundary

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Kohli, 1 run
text: yorker curving away from middle stump, leans in and stabs that to mid-off

shortText: Hasan Ali to Kohli, no run
text: good length and slanted in at off stump, walks down at it and turns it to midwicket
length and just outside off, opens the face and runs it to third man

shortText: Hasan Ali to Yadav, no run
text: good length and just outside off, pushed to point off the back foot

lovely grab by Rizwan! Banged in at a length, lands on the seam and straightens just a bit as SKY gets down the pitch to try and punch it on the rise. That bit of straightening has done him outside off and this is a big deflection off the outside edge. Rizwan does really well to track this to his right and hold on, that was a touch wider than a first slip would have been
good length and just outside off, turned into the leg side with the angle

squeezed past cover and point to end the powerplay. This is length, skidding on nicely outside off, and Kohli with a trademark push at the ball, the face opening at the last moment to bisect those two fielders

shortText: Shadab Khan to Pant, no run
text: full at middle stump, driven back at the bowler on the bounce

shortText: Shadab Khan to Pant, no run
text: full and turning into the pad at a leg stump line, can't get the flick off the bat

shortText: Shadab Khan to Pant, no run
text: good length and turning in at leg stump, glanced with the turn to short fine
shot. Short of a length and skidding on, but he's picked the variation. Waits on it and chops it to sweeper's left

shortText: Shadab Khan to Pant, no run
text: good length at middle stump, steps out and clips to midwicket
full at leg stump, steps out and flicks to deep midwicket's left. Hasan Ali rapidly onto it to prevent any thoughts of a second

shortText: Mohammad Hafeez to Pant, no run
text: good length at middle stump, tight at his body, he pushes it down the pitch
good length outside off, gets low and sweeps along the ground to deep square's right
good length outside off, leans in and flicks to long-on

shortText: Mohammad Hafeez to Pant, no run
text: Rizwan is convinced he has Pant caught behind. Erasmus says no. Pakistan have reviewed immediately. This is a good length ball, rising and turning marginally away outside off. Pant has attempted a reverse sweep. It's definitely hit his arm not hit anything on the way to Rizwan. Flatline. Not out
short of a length and tight at off stump, backs away and punches to sweeper cover
good length at leg stump, uppishly jabbed to midwicket's right off the back foot
dipping full toss at middle stump, reaches out and has a swish. Off the inside edge to deep midwicket

shortText: Shadab Khan to Pant, no run
text: beaten. Googly at a length outside off, Pant looks to swing across the line but that turns away
oh lovely work by Haris at the fence. Short and wide outside off, absolutely muscled off the back foot towards the point boundary, but he puts in a slide and stops that
toe-end slog ends up safely in front of long-off. This is good length and wide outside off, he can't manage to gets the bat around it
good length, possibly a googly, in at off stump. Gets deep in the crease and flicks it off the thick inside edge through midwicket. Shadab chases it down and keeps them to one
that's a gift to Pant, and he's taken it gratefully. Attempted googly lands short and down leg side. Pant gets on one knee and swipes this over short fine
good length and across off stump, gets deep in the crease and clips through square leg

finds the gap! Short of a length and coming in with his around-the-wicket angle. Tight at off stump, but Pant manages to get rapid hands to scythe this from inside the line and get it wide of short third
good length at middle stump, steps out and pushes towards long-on
good length and turning into leg stump, flicked through square leg

shortText: Mohammad Hafeez to Pant, no run
text: good length and sliding on quickly into the pad from middle stump as Pant jumps down and looks to whip through midwicket
short of a length outside off, deep in the crease as he caresses this to deep midwicket
short, slanting away into a wide-ish line outside off, slapped to deep point
length ball close to off stump, straightens off the deck. Shuffles across and looks to work it to midwicket, gets a thick leading edge down to deep third
fires a quick, full ball down the leg side, past the attempted flick
full, slanting across to finish just outside off. Drives with an open face to deep third
length ball on off stump, clipped towards mid-on, without much timing, but that makes it easier for the batters to scamper the single with the fielder on the edge of the circle

shortText: Haris Rauf to Pant, no run
text: full, slanting across to off stump, too full for Pant to get under. Driven firmly but straight to extra-cover
full on off stump, not quite as full as the previous ball, brings his wrists into play to drive against the angle to long-on

shortText: Hasan Ali to Pant, no run
text: length ball on off stump, looks to step out and make room but too far from the pitch of the ball to really go hard at it. Slapped to extra-cover

that's a Pant special. Another in his long list of one-handed sixes. Terrific hit. He was premeditating here, looking to go over midwicket, and Hasan fired a length ball into his body, cramping him for room. Down he goes on his back knee, and off comes the bottom hand, and he extends his front arm fully and whips it over the square leg boundary

another one-handed six, this time over the off side. Wow. Full slower ball now, angling across to off stump, and Pant uses the extra leverage he gets to meet the ball well in front of his body and lift it with a straight bat over the long-off boundary. Mid-off was in, and he just cleared the boundary
back of a length outside off, opens his bat face to steer to the left of deep third
back of a length, angling into the body, tucked away to long leg

shortText: Hasan Ali to Kohli, no run
text: steps out to a length ball angling in towards off stump, not quite close enough to the pitch to attack it, and doesn't get any room either. Clipped to midwicket

that's a pretty poor ball, and he only ends up conceding two. Down the leg side, there to be swept, but it's slower than Pant expects, and he's through his shot early. Ends up gloving it over the keeper's head

wrong'un, and that's done the trick, Shadab ends a dangerous innings just before it can take Pakistan out of the game. Looped up slow, pitching on middle and leg or thereabouts, and Pant looks to sweep. The ball dips on him a little, turns away, and he ends up skewing it high in the air, in the direction of mid-on. Long-on is back on the boundary, though, so it falls to the bowler to backtrack to his left and take a very well-judged catch with both hands, over his head
down the leg side again, quicker this time, and Pant ends up missing the sweep

shortText: Shadab Khan to Kohli, no run
text: loopy googly outside off. Looks to drive to long-off, ends up playing it back to the bowler
another googly, shorter this time, goes on the back foot and tucks it away to deep square leg
legbreak turning into the pads, stays on the back foot and works it to deep square leg
tossed up on middle stump, stretches out with his pad next to the line of the ball and pushes inside-out to sweeper cover
steps out to a length ball angling in towards off stump, and clips to long-on

shortText: Haris Rauf to Jadeja, no run
text: fires a blockhole ball, slanting it away from the left-hander and pitching just outside off. Looks to jab through point, ends up playing it back to the bowler off the inside half of the bat
length ball angling into a wide-ish line, and that's nicely placed, opens his bat face to steer it to the left of deep third, where old man Malik does very well to stop it with a slide at the rope
back of a length, closer to off stump this time, hangs back and opens his bat face to dab to deep third

ooh, misses his line slightly, and Kohli puts it away. Looks for the leg-stump yorker, but he ends up slightly outside leg, and with Kohli stepping across, outside Kohli's pads. So instead of cramping him for room, he ends up offering a freebie that's clipped to the fine leg boundary, to the right of the man at short fine
bouncer over off stump, Kohli ducks, and the square leg umpire judges that it's bounced above head height. Well above, it seemed

shortText: Haris Rauf to Kohli, no run
text: quick length ball close to off stump, looks to dab into the covers and set off for a quick single, but it's too close to the bowler's follow-through

shortText: Shadab Khan to Jadeja, no run
text: length wrong'un turning away from off stump. Presses forward and opens his bat face to dab into the point region

shortText: Shadab Khan to Jadeja, no run
text: fuller now, floated across to finish outside off, check-driven to extra-cover
now the legbreak, tossed up quite full and turning in from outside off. Clipped with the turn to long-on
legbreak pitching full on middle and off, quite a lot of flight, opens his bat face to squeeze it towards sweeper cover
tossed up full outside off, driven firmly to long-off
short outside off, legbreak, chopped to sweeper cover

shortText: Hasan Ali to Kohli, no run
text: ooh, well bowled. Saw Kohli looking to step out, and hit the pitch hard on a shortish length outside off, got it to rise uncomfortably. Tries to use his wrists to play that to long-on, but it hits the high part of the bat and bounces feebly down in front of the bowler
poor ball. Shortish, angling down leg, and fine leg is inside the circle. Kohli turns his wrists over on top of the bounce and whips it to the left of the fielder

shortText: Hasan Ali to Kohli, no run
text: extra bounce outside off, beats Kohli's edge as he tries to run that down to deep third
full outside off, and Kohli threads his favourite gap. Strides forward and just jabs that drive to the right of the diving extra-cover fielder. Mid-off chases back, but he has no chance
slower length ball outside off, punched to deep cover point
shortish, gets it to climb steeply and cramp Jadeja for room over off stump. Hops to ride the bounce and dabs it square on the off side
full, angling across to off stump. Looks to stay leg-side of the ball and drive to the right of mid-off, but hits it too close to him to get anything more than a single

good-looking shot, but just one. Full outside off, and Kohli ends up making more room than he needs. Wants to drive over extra-cover, but ends up hitting it squarer than he wants, on the bounce to sweeper cover
nicely bowled. He knows Jadeja wants to make room, so he bowls a slower length ball at his legs. No room or pace to work with, so he just pushes into the covers and takes the single

shortText: Haris Rauf to Kohli, no run
text: slower length ball wide of off stump, and Kohli swings and misses, looking to carve it through the covers off the front foot

shortText: Haris Rauf to Kohli, no run
text: slower length ball again, this time he waits on the back foot and looks to force it past backward point, but ends up hitting it straight to the fielder
full, angling into middle and leg, and deep square leg is well behind square, Kohli can only clip it to him for one

back of a length, angling into middle and leg, and Kohli clips it towards deep midwicket, without a lot of weight on the shot, so he knows he's getting two if he hurries. He does, and he gets to yet another fifty against Pakistan at a T20 World Cup. It's taken him 45 balls, though.
bad ball. Wide, back of a length, slower ball, and Kohli puts it away, waits on it and flat-bats it over extra-cover
length ball on off stump, pushed to deep cover and gets to the other end
poor ball. Fine leg is inside the circle, and Hasan angles this shortish ball down the leg side. Jadeja just helps it on its way, over the man at short fine

fullish slower ball outside off, and the lack of pace does Jadeja in. He's looking to hit over mid-on initially, I think, but he's early on the shot, reaching well in front of his body, and then tries to adjust by bringing his wrists into the shot. All that does is send the ball down the throat of deep midwicket
length ball angling in towards off stump, steps out and clips towards deep midwicket, who has to run in quite a distance, so Kohli picks up another two

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Pandya, no run
text: shortish slower ball angling into that wide line again. Tries to flat-bat it through mid-on/midwicket, but he can't connect

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Pandya, 1 wide
text: wide yorker straight up, but it's judged as being too wide after Pandya reaches out, throws his bat at the ball, and fails to connect

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Pandya, FOUR
text: unlucky, for the bowler. Perfect off-stump yorker, and Hardik jams his bat down on it, looking only to protect his stumps, and he ends up squeezing it to the fine third man boundary

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Pandya, 1 run
text: perfect bouncer, quick and rising steeply, over Hardik's front shoulder. Too late on the attempted hook, and he gloves it, or arm-guards it, loopily to land between the bowler and keeper rushing in from opposite directions

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Kohli, OUT
text: got him, this has been an outstanding over from Shaheen! Slower bouncer, gets up around the right shoulder, and Kohli is too early on his attempted pull. All he manages is a top-edge that plops gently to the right of the keeper. That's the first time Pakistan have dismissed him in a T20 World Cup game

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Kumar, 1 run
text: full on the stumps, clipped into the midwicket region and the bowler rushes there to keep it down to one

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Pandya, 5 byes
text: oh my, it's all happening, and Pakistan are leaking runs that they shouldn't! A good free-hit ball, bouncer slanting across and finishing around the right shoulder. Pandya misses the pull, and tries to run a quick single to retain the strike. Rizwan's underarm throw misses at his end, then the bowler picks the ball up and flings a wild throw past the stumps at his end, and it rushes away too quickly for long-on to stop to his right

shortText: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Pandya, (no ball) FOUR
text: bad ball to finish a terrific over. Possibly looking for the wide yorker, ends up slipping out a wide full-toss, and Pandya opens his bat face to guide it into the gap between deep point and backward point. And it's judged to be a no-ball! On height, I think.

shortText: Haris Rauf to Pandya, no run
text: slower length ball outside off, and Pandya swings too early, looking to hit leg-side, and misses. That turned like a proper offbreak
slower ball, into the pitch, gets up around bail-high on off stump. Flat-batted to the right of long-on, and they can pick up two

another slower ball, on a length outside off, and that's proving unhittable today, at least when Rauf delivers them. Looks to hit it with a straight bat over the bowler's head, but he ends up skewing it over the off side, and deep cover runs in and takes it close to the 30-yard circle

fullish slower ball close to off stump, and Bhuvneshwar steps forward and clips it gently towards long-on, relying on the gentleness of the shot to allow him to get two. They hurry through, but there's a third-umpire's judgment to be made at the end of it, at the danger end. Direct hit might have been close, but Shami's made it well before the bowler collects and disturbs the furniture

this is quite smart from Bhuvneshwar. He knows he's not a big hitter, but Pakistan can't bring the field in either. No one in the circle at midwicket, and he clips a length ball into that region, and picks up another easy two by the time deep midwicket makes his way in from the deep

shortText: Kumar to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: big swing. Starts middle and curves away to the corridor from middle, thick outside edge as he pushes at this

searching for swing again but this full one goes straight on and into the pads. Leans in and flicks this wide of Varun at mid-on. He gives chase, plonks his knees into the turf as he dives at the boundary. Close call as he flicks it back in. His left hand is touching the boundary as he lets go a backhand flick with the right hand. Third umpire deems the ball hadn't left his hand quick enough
swatted over the deep square boundary. This is short of a length and up at his hips, and he bends his knees a touch to get under this and brings a lovely flow of the hands for a half-flick, half-pull

shortText: Kumar to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: good length and tight at off stump, defended into the covers

shortText: Kumar to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: good length and slanted into off and middle, shuffles and jabs into the leg side

shortText: Kumar to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: good length and in at off stump again, solidly behind that to defend. Bhuvneshwar's defensive plan for the last three balls has worked

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Babar Azam, 1 run
text: good length and just outside off, pushes into the off side with soft hands and they pinch a run from Jadeja. Kohli not amused

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: good length and tight at off stump, solidly pushed down the pitch

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, 2 runs
text: good length and onto the pads, shuffles and places his glance fine of deep square leg

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run
text: good length and at middle stump, forced towards mid-on off the back foot

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Babar Azam, FOUR
text: oh yes. Handsome, handsome stuff. Good length and just outside off, in the corridor. Babar stands firm and allows that on before punching it past cover with a still head. Gorgeous

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Babar Azam, no run
text: leading edge into the covers. Good length and into leg stump, closes the face too early
full and angled in at middle stump, leans in and flicks off the toe-end to deep square

shortText: Bumrah to Babar Azam, no run
text: in the air briefly. Short of a length and just outside off, stands tall for another back foot punch but can't quite control this one. It's well short of Jadeja. Did that stick in the pitch? Seemed like it

shortText: Bumrah to Babar Azam, no run
text: offcutter at a length on off stump, leans in and tries to steer that to third man. Jadeja cuts it off and Rizwan sends Babar back
low full toss at leg stump, waits on that and flicks off the bottom of the bat to deep square's left. SKY has a long chase before sliding to keep it in

shortText: Bumrah to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: offcutter at a length outside off, gets forward and pushes into the covers. Wants to sneak a run, sent back with a raucous call

shortText: Bumrah to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: lovely. Nails the yorker at off stump and Rizwan can't do more than push this back at the bowler
good length outside off, drives to extra cover's right. Kohli leaps but parries it behind mid-off
full and just outside off, shuffles and jams this to deep midwicket with a sweep

shortText: Varun to Babar Azam, no run
text: short of a length and tight at off stump, backs away for the cut and finds Jadeja doing Jadeja things there at point. Dive, recovery, throw, direct hit. All in a second

shortText: Varun to Babar Azam, no run
text: good length outside off, chopped straight to short third

shortText: Varun to Babar Azam, no run
text: beaten on the cut. Short of a length, gripping and rising outside off. He's itching to cut this but loses his shape

shortText: Varun to Babar Azam, no run
text: good length and turning into leg stump, looks to whip off the back foot and cops it on the pad

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run
text: good length and into leg stump, whipped out to deep square

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Babar Azam, no run
text: another dot ball. Short of a length cutter just outside off, opens the face to try and run that past short third. Inside edge towards the keeper

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Babar Azam, FOUR
text: lofted to the wide long-on boundary. Graceful as ever. Not a great ball though. Full and into leg stump. He leans in and offers the full face as he chips it wide of mid-on

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Babar Azam, 1 run
text: offcutter at a length on leg stump, flicked to deep square's left

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR
text: blazed behind deep square! Wow, that's sensational timing against a slower ball. Offcutter, short of a length and at waist height. Gets really low in the crouch and swipes across this to get it into the boundary, along the turf

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run
text: full and into the pads, flicked to deep square
legcutter, dug into the pitch at middle stump. Waits on it and pulls to deep square's right. Comes back for the second and completes it with a huge dive
good length and down leg side, beaten on the flick
legcutter again on leg stump, skids straight on. Flicked out to deep square
good length and tight at off stump, defended onto the pad off the inside edge for a single on the off side
legcutter at off stump, good length, pushed into the covers with soft hands
legcutter again, good length at leg stump, deep in the crease and flicks to deep square's left

shortText: Kumar to Babar Azam, no run
text: good length at off stump, defended into the leg side off the back foot
good length and turning away a touch outside off, gets deep in the crease and whips it to long-on

shortText: Jadeja to Babar Azam, no run
text: good length and skidding on with the arm, looks to drive on the rise through cover, it comes off the inside half and trickles down the pitch

shortText: Jadeja to Babar Azam, no run
text: good length at off stump, pushed back to the bowler

shortText: Jadeja to Babar Azam, no run
text: good length and pushed into the midwicket region, Jadeja sprints across to get to it. Slips awkwardly as he does it but back on his feet
full and into leg stump, gets forward and flicks to deep midwicket
short and wide outside off, reaches out and pushes to backward point on the bounce
full and just outside off, leans in and drives to sweeper's left
short of a length outside off, backs away and punches to sweeper cover

shortText: Varun to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: good length, turning away from middle stump, defended on the front foot
good length and grip, turning down leg though and past the flick
good length outside off, flicked hurriedly down to long-on
good length and skidding on at off stump, backs away and punches to sweeper cover
good length and into leg stump, gets deep in the crease and nudges it through midwicket
short and wide outside off, cut to sweeper cover
good length at off stump, driven on the rise to sweeper cover
good length outside off, leans in and drives with the turn to long-off

shortText: Jadeja to Babar Azam, no run
text: short of a length outside off, steps out and mistimes a punch to Kohli at extra cover, who whips a throw a back at the keeper

clubs it over deep midwicket! First boundary in four overs, and it's a maximum. This is dropped marginally short at middle stump and Babar swivels and hits with the intention of clearing the shorter side. And he does
good length and turning away outside off, deep in the crease to punch that to sweeper cover

not in control but safe. Short and wide, perhaps gets too far under this as he gets deep in the crease and reaches out. He gets in the gap he was looking for - between point and short third - but it was off a thick outside edge. But a nice start to the over
good length outside off, driven past the bowler to long-off
they steal a second from long-on! Short of a length outside off, he shuffles into line and expertly pushes this wide of SKY with soft hands and Babar calls decisively

direct hit at the non-striker's end. Rizwan was diving. And he was doing it awkwardly, but he's just about made it. Length ball at middle stump, shuffles and turns to short fine. When he dives, the bat is almost upright, like it is when they pat the pitch in between balls. And that is when he's falling. So the bat has to come down to the floor even though the line of it is past the crease. Thankfully for him, it comes down in time. Bhuvneshwar with the direct hit
good length outside off, shuffles and whips through midwicket off the back foot

shortText: Varun to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: good length at middle stump, shuffles and thinks of the sweep, checks it and offers the full face on the defence

back of a length, angling into middle and leg, spotting the batter looking to make room. Manages to chop it to the right of the diving backward point fielder, and they pick up two by the time deep point runs around
not the best ball Bumrah has ever bowled. A wide half-volley, and Babar frees his arms to lift it over the leaping fielder at extra-cover, and to the left of mid-off

shortText: Bumrah to Babar Azam, no run
text: back of a length on off stump, uses his wrists to clip that to midwicket

shortText: Bumrah to Babar Azam, no run
text: yorker, very close to off stump, sneaks under the bat as Babar looks to jam his bat down and squeeze it away through point
goes for the off-stump yorker again, underpitches a little, and Babar clears his front leg to manufacture a bit of room for a wristy chip over the bowler's head
wide length ball, looks to slash it away off the front foot and gets a thick edge down to deep third
looks to make room, and Jadeja follows him with a length ball. Clipped quietly to deep midwicket

shortText: Jadeja to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: length ball sliding on towards off stump, punched back to the bowler. Was playing for turn and looking to go through cover
pulls his length back slightly and goes wider outside off, and Rizwan gets down on one knee to pull-sweep to deep square leg

shortText: Jadeja to Babar Azam, 1 leg bye
text: flat, fired down the leg side. Misses the flick and gets a leg bye into the backward point region
flat, a touch short, going with the angle towards off stump, goes deep in his crease to pull into the gap between long-on and deep midwicket

shortText: Jadeja to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: looks to create a bit of room and Jadeja fires in a back-of-a-length slider on leg stump. He's cramped for room, and ends up inside-edging his flick into his pad
wrong'un spinning in towards off stump from just back of a length. No room to pull, drags it towards short fine leg off the bottom edge

bam. That's a difficult shot, because it was an awkward length to hit. Went down on one knee premeditatedly for the sweep, and had to almost drag a kneeling pull from outside off stump, just clears the boundary to the right of deep square leg
back of a length on off stump, makes room and chops into the point region

fifty! Gets there in some style, as Varun bowls a long-hop on off stump, and he quickly opens up at the hip to swat it high over the midwicket boundary. Super shot, super innings from Pakistan's captain
quickish, skids inwards towards middle and leg from just short of a length, and Rizwan goes deep in his crease to muscle towards long-on and bring up Pakistan's 100
length ball turning in from outside off, steps towards the ball to clip to long-on
flat, angling into leg stump, swept along the ground to deep backward square leg

drops a touch short on off stump, and that's a superb shot. Shifts his left foot well outside leg stump to create a lot of room, and then swings downwards through the pull and finds the gap to the left of deep midwicket. Swivels through his hips at impact to create serious power
length ball close to off stump, stays leg-side of the ball to punch to sweeper cover
tossed up outside off, driven to long-off

shortText: Jadeja to Babar Azam, no run
text: down the track and Jadeja shortens his length and goes wider. Slashes at it and gets a thick edge to short third
shortish, angling down leg, and again Babar's footwork is lightning. Goes deep in his crease with left leg well out of the way, and then whips it away off his hip to the left of short fine leg

shortText: Bumrah to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: angles a yorker in towards off stump from wide of the crease, and Rizwan jams his bat down to block it back to the bowler

superb. Babar was pulling spinners when they were dropping marginally short, and now Rizwan does it off the pace of Bumrah. Just back of a length on off stump, and he seemed to be waiting on it, swivels through the hips to hit it to the right of midwicket and bring up his fifty. Terrific stuff
typical Rizwan. Fullish slower ball outside off, and get gets forward and uses his wrists to clip that towards deep midwicket, who's just dropped back, and sprints with typical energy to pick up two
in the blockhole on middle and leg, clipped to deep square leg
in the blockhole on off stump, makes room for a smooth push towards mid-off, who's on the edge of the circle and can't save the single
shortish offcutter outside off, jumps across to chop into the backward point region

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR
text: short, gets up around the hip, and Rizwan plays a short-arm whip to easily beat deep square leg to his right

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: full, just outside off, clipped towards midwicket

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run
text: full, angling in towards off stump, clipped to long-on

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Babar Azam, 1 run
text: looks for the off-stump yorker, doesn't quite get it full enough. Gets his front leg out of the way and clips through square leg

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run
text: quickish, on the fuller side of a length, nipping in to hit the pad after Rizwan misses the flick. Going down leg, so there's no appeal, and they sneak a leg bye into the cover region

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Babar Azam, no run
text: in the blockhole on off stump, jammed back to the bowler
shortish outside off, reaches out and slaps it towards sweeper cover, who's quite square
stays back to a length ball on off stump, clears his front leg, and flat-bats towards long-on

shortText: Kumar to Mohammad Rizwan, no run
text: wide yorker, and Rizwan misses the reach-out-and-slash
full outside off, driven to long-off with a bottom-handed flourish
slower ball wide of off stump. Rizwan has a massive swing at it and misses, and this time it's adjudged wide
back of a length outside off, opens up at the hip and flat-bats to the right of long-off. Not too much distance for the fielder to cover, but they whizz through for two anyway
playing with that off-side tramline again. Full, not quite a yorker, left alone, and it's called wide. Seemed to nip away off the pitch and end up just outside the tramline

shortText: Kumar to Babar Azam, no run
text: wide length ball, hugging the tramline once again. Not called wide this time after Babar leaves it, and he doesn't look pleased

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, SIX
text: Nope. That's not going to win any games. Full-toss at the hip, and Rizwan steps across and whips it away over the backward square leg boundary. Not a no-ball, but close

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR
text: superb. Fullish outside off, and Rizwan steps across and swipes it away to the left of midwicket, and easily beats long-on to his right

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR
text: short, chest-high ball on off stump, and this is stunning. This wasn't an easy ball to put away, but he manages to get on top of the bounce, roll his wrists over, and beat deep square leg to his right with the pull

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run
text: full on off stump, clipped quietly down to long-on

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Babar Azam, 2 runs
text: fullish on off stump, clipped to the right of long-on, and that's it, Pakistan have handed their first-ever 10-wicket defeat in T20Is. And they've ended a long, winless run against India in World Cups, stretching all the way back to 1992. And Babar and Rizwan complete it in a way that sums up their partnership. Into the gap, and they quickly sprint two to complete the job

shortText: Karunaratne to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: very full on fifth stump, driven firmly to cover.

shortText: Karunaratne to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: back of a length on fourth stump, defended in front of point.
back of a length on the hips, flicked behind square for one to get the scoring underway.

shortText: Karunaratne to Liton Das, no run
text: back of a length on fifth stump, guided to backward point.
back of a length on off, pushed gently into mid-on.

shortText: Karunaratne to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: full on the pads, can't flick this away at 139 kph.

shortText: B Fernando to Liton Das, no run
text: full on the stumps, blocked defensively.

shortText: B Fernando to Liton Das, no run
text: full again at 127 kph, blunted back to Binura.

shortText: B Fernando to Liton Das, no run
text: back of a length on fourth stump, defended to backward point.

shortText: B Fernando to Liton Das, FOUR
text: full on the legs at 133 kph, tickled fine past the keeper to the fine leg rope.

shortText: B Fernando to Liton Das, 1 run
text: full again and flicked into the leg side to get off strike.

shortText: B Fernando to Mohammad Naim, 2 runs
text: full and wide, driven through the covers for a pair.
full on the stumps at 146 kph, tapped into midwicket for one.
back of a length on middle at 140 kph, tapped gently into midwicket for one.
back of a length, guided behind point to deep third man for one.

shortText: Chameera to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: bouncer over leg stump, Naim ducks under, deemed legal on the line and length.
full on the pads at 150 kph, serious heat from Chameera but Naim flicks this through midwicket with ease and it races away to the rope.

shortText: Chameera to Mohammad Naim, (no ball) 2 runs
text: full and slanted into the legs, flicks this in the air over midwicket for a pair. Bad news for Chameera. He's overstepped again according to the third umpire.

shortText: Chameera to Mohammad Naim, 1 no ball
text: full on middle and leg, defended into midwicket. But the third umpire has radio'd down to notify of a no ball on an overstep.
full on the pads ago, slower ball this time at 113 kph, but Naim adjusts with soft hands to push into mid-on for one.

full and wide at 141 kph, driven over cover and they are able to come back and scamper a rare three in Sharjah. Boundaries are lopsided square today. 57 meters on one side, 73 on the other due to the position of the strip.

shortText: Kumara to Liton Das, no run
text: full on off at 137 kph, defended into cover.
fullish length on fourth stump at 138 kph, shovels this in the air just short of extra cover and they scamper a single.

shortText: Kumara to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: attempted yorker is a low full toss at shin height on off stump at 138 kph, but Naim misses out punching it straight to mid-on.
length ball on fourth stump at 138 kph, sits up for Naim to club high over mid-on.

shortText: Kumara to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: full on the stumps at 145 kph, punched back to Kumara who fields one-handed and fires back over Naim's shoulder. Keeper saves it from being four overthrows.
overpitched on fifth stump at 148 kph, driven firmly to mid-off for a sharp single.
short on middle, pulled firmly through midwicket for a pair.
back of a length on middle, slower ball at 114 kph, guided softly in front of point for one.
slower ball again short and wide, guides this 113 kph wristily behind point and pierces the gap to perfection.
another slower ball outside off guided in front of point for a single.

shortText: Chameera to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: short on middle at 144 kph, Naim can't reach with an uppercut, deemed legal on height.
overpitched on fourth stump, driven firmly to wide mid-off, diving stop on the ring for one.

shortText: Kumara to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: full on off, driven into cover for a dot.

shortText: Kumara to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: wide yorker on fifth stump, can't jam this out.
slower yorker wide this time on fifth stump, edges this wide of the keeper who dives to slow it down for one.

Liton tries to get a bit too creative and pays the price. And now some spicy exchange after the catch at mid-off! Kumara and Liton have to be separated as Liton was walking off. Naim comes from behind and pushes Kumara to get away from Liton. The umpires have to hustle forward as the players continue making physical contact, pushing, shoving and trash-talking. The NBA/NFL comes to the T20 World Cup! As for the wicket itself, Liton backed away from leg trying to drive a full ball over the ring but picked out mid-off at head height. That's a footnote in the sequence now that. We may have a lengthy match referee report after play.

shortText: Kumara to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full on the stumps, flicked square for a single.

shortText: Asalanka to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR
text: full and wide, Shakib drives inside out over extra cover. Pure class.

shortText: Asalanka to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full and pushed gently into the ring for one.
good length ball, but too wide outside off, too easy to cut this behind point past the diving fielder to the rope.
full on fourth stump, uses the feet to drive firmly to mid-off.

shortText: Asalanka to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: full on off, driven back to Asalanka.

shortText: Asalanka to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR
text: good length ball on middle, Shakib backs away from leg to create room to carve this through cover and it beats the diving effort on the rope by the cover sweeper.

shortText: Karunaratne to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: good length ball on off, defended.
full on fifth stump, driven wide of extra cover to the sweeper.

shortText: Karunaratne to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: short and wide, cuts behind point but stopped on the ring.

shortText: Karunaratne to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT
text: backs away from leg trying to flick over the leg side but Karunaratne bowls the perfect delivery clipping the top of leg stump. He sprints away into the covers making 100% sure to not be anywhere near Shakib after the unsavory incident following the first wicket.
short and wide, slapped off the toe to third man for one.
full on the legs, flicked through midwicket for one.

shortText: de Silva to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: good length ball on off, flicked into midwicket.

shortText: de Silva to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: good length ball flicked away square again for one.

shortText: de Silva to Mohammad Naim, 2 runs
text: short on middle, stays low and pulled through midwicket for a very tight pair.

shortText: de Silva to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: short on the stumps, flicked into mid-on for one.

shortText: de Silva to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: short on fifth stump, cuts this behind point for one.

shortText: de Silva to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: short and punched through the covers for another single.
length ball on the legs at 128 kph, goes to flick over the leg side and a top/leading edge swirls over third man for a pair.
full on off, driven through extra cover for a pair again.
good length ball tapped away for one.
full and punched down the ground for one.
full on the stumps, punched back to Karunaratne, flings this back into leg stump and ricochets away for an overthrow.

shortText: Karunaratne to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: back of a length ball at 133 kph jags in from sixth stump, goes to cut and misses.

shortText: de Silva to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: fuller around, gets low and sweeps it towards deep midwicket

shortText: de Silva to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: tossed up around off, Mushfiqur goes on his knee and slog-sweeps it towards deep midwicket

shortText: de Silva to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: flighted again. In the line of the stumps. Comes and whips it towards long-on

shortText: de Silva to Mushfiqur Rahim, SIX
text: maximum! Another slog sweep from Mushfiqur. This time he goes aerial and clears the deep-midwicket fielder with ease

shortText: de Silva to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: another sweep from Mushfiqur. Goes squarer and along the ground this time. A single to deep square leg

shortText: de Silva to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: fuller on the stumps, drives it towards long-on. Naim was looking for the second but sent back
starts with a length ball on middle and leg. Punched towards midwicket

shortText: Shanaka to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: length ball around off, Mushfiqur looks to drop and run but Shanaka is quick to the ball to prevent any runs
use of feet this time, backs away as well but Shanaka bangs it into the pitch and follows the batter. Dabbed towards third man
length ball in the line of the stumps, punched towards long-off
a high full toss on the pads but he gets away with it. Can only flick it towards deep square leg. Only a single

shortText: Shanaka to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: fuller around off, digs it out towards extra cover. An excellent over from Shanaka, just four singles from it

shortText: B Fernando to Mushfiqur Rahim, SIX
text: Mushfiqur takes on the tall man. A slower one from Binura, on a length and cutting across, Mushfiqur stays back and slog sweeps it over deep square leg

shortText: B Fernando to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: length ball around off and angling across. Fails to get bat on this

shortText: B Fernando to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: short of length around off, hangs back and opens the face of the bat to steer it past the keeper. Third man does well to keep it to one

shortText: B Fernando to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: another slower one. This time banged in the pitch. Extracts bounce this time and Naim cannot get on the top of it and fails to connect the cut

shortText: B Fernando to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: short of length around off, swats it towards long-on

shortText: B Fernando to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: a full toss outside off, driven but straight towards sweeper cover

a direct hit and Naim was gone but they get a single off the overthrow instead. A length ball outside off, Mushfiqur taps it towards point and takes a step down the ground. Naim charges out of his crease before realising his partner is no longer interested. The point fielder misses the direct hit at the bowler's end though
an excellent yorker from Kumara. Outside off but in the blockhole. Squeezes it out towards third man
another brilliant yorker. Mushfiqur digs it out down the ground

that's fifty for Naim. Off 44 balls. Stays deep in his crease this time, Kumara once again goes for the yorker but this time just misses his mark and Naim carts him over his head. The fielder at long-on puts in the dive but cannot stop

shortText: Kumara to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: mistimes this length ball towards covers
short of length this time but Naim is up to it. Clears his front leg and pulls it towards midwicket for four more

shortText: de Silva to Mushfiqur Rahim, FOUR
text: and Mushfiqur welcomes him with another slog-swept four. Bisecting the gap between deep square leg and deep midwicket

shortText: de Silva to Mushfiqur Rahim, FOUR
text: skips across the stumps this time, seeing Hasaranga has bowled it on the leg stump, adjusts quickly and slog sweeps it to the left of short fine leg. He is playing a valuable knock here

shortText: de Silva to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: fuller outside off, drives it towards sweeper cover

shortText: de Silva to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: length ball on the stumps, pushed towards midwicket. Hasaranga chases it himself and manages to keep it to one

shortText: de Silva to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: a googly this time. Mushfiqur goes back and cuts it towards deep point

shortText: de Silva to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: looked like another googly. Naim finds the point fielder with the cut
length ball down the leg side. Mushfiqur was ready to scoop it over the keeper but misses. Gets a bye as the keeper fumbles

length ball around off, Naim looks to give himself some room and go for the cut but all he manages is a top edge. But it's all going Bangladesh's way at the moment as the edge skids between the keeper and short third man
bunts this towards long-off for a single
short of length outside off, backs away and cuts it towards deep point. A good stop by the third man fielder to keep it to two
backs away this time but the bowler follows him. Digs it out towards long-on
Looks like a slower one that went wrong. Short of length but down the leg side. Mushfiqur was looking to move across but leaves it alone in the end
another almost-yorker. Naim hits it along the ground towards long-off

shortText: B Fernando to Mohammad Naim, OUT
text: bangs it in the middle of the pitch. Naim goes for the pull but can only top-edge it straight up. Binura moves under it and completes the catch near short midwicket region

shortText: B Fernando to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: length ball angling across, cuts it towards sweeper cover

shortText: B Fernando to Afif Hossain, 1 run
text: short of length angling towards the pads, helps it on its way to short fine leg

shortText: B Fernando to Mushfiqur Rahim, FOUR
text: pierces the off-side field. A length ball angling across, gives Mushfiqur adequate room to free his arms and cut it to the right of the point fielder and beat the sweeper cover

shortText: B Fernando to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: fuller around off, stays back and slogs it towards deep midwicket

shortText: B Fernando to Afif Hossain, FOUR
text: this is poor from Binura on many accounts. It's not only a low full toss but a leg side low full toss. Afif just flicks it fine and picks up four runs
length outside off, cuts it towards sweeper cover. Only a single
fuller outside off, hits it towards sweeper cover
this is turning out to be a brilliant knock from Mushfiqur. Short of length outside off, Mushfiqur gets on his toes and on the top of the ball and cuts it over the point region

shortText: Chameera to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 leg bye
text: fuller outside off, attempts the scoop but cannot get underneath the ball. It hits him on the left leg and rolls towards covers
a yorker. Jams his bat at it and manages to dig it out towards short third man
fuller outside off, slices it towards deep point
fifty for Mushfiqur, off just 32 balls. Fuller at the stumps from Kumara. Mushfiqur gets his front leg out of the way and hits it towards long-on. Along the ground only

shortText: Kumara to Afif Hossain, no run
text: follows Afif with a length ball as the batter was moving towards the leg side. Fails to connect in the end as the ball goes between him and the stumps

that looks out. Good work from Kumara to field it in his follow-through and hit the stumps direct to find the batter short. They are checking upstairs and yes, Afif was way short of his crease. A yorker this time on the leg stump, Afif look to jam his bat at it but think it hit his pads and rolled towards the bowler who charged towards it and nailed the direct hit
fuller around off. Mahmudullah looks to slog it away. Gets an inside edge onto the pads and sneaks in a single as the ball rolls towards the off side
goes for the yorker. Mahmudullah digs it out towards midwicket and they sprint back for the second

shortText: Kumara to Mushfiqur Rahim, (no ball) 1 bye
text: a beamer. Called a no-ball immediately. Mushfiqur takes evasive action. Gets away from the harm's way, was 144kphs. The keeper fumbles and allows an extra run
hits straight down the ground, between the stumps and the non-striker. A low full toss in the line of the stumps and hit almost parallel to the ground

shortText: Chameera to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: fuller outside off, looks to reverse scoop it but misses
fuller outside off, clears his front leg and carves it towards deep extra cover
goes for the yorker but think Mushfiqur took it on the full and opened the face to guide it towards deep point
cracking shot! Fuller outside off and Mahmudullah crunches it through covers. Beats the man in the deep
goes for the bouncer this time. Mahmudullah goes for the pull but the ball hurries onto him. A single to square leg
Mushfiqur takes Bangladesh past 170. Fuller around off, moves across swiftly and scoops it over the keeper

shortText: Nasum Ahmed to Perera, no run
text: good length ball on fourth stump, defended to point.
good length ball on middle and leg flicked to backward square. They set off for a very tight run and just make it in. Direct hit would've been out but the throw to the keeper bounced high.
full on the legs, flicked behind square to the right-hander's side this time for another tight run.

darts this in flatter and quicker at 100 kph on fourth stump and skids on to beat the slog sweep! Clever change of pace by Nasun and he sets off sprinting to third man in an animated celebration for his first wicket of the T20 World Cup in his first match of the tournament.
full on the stumps, flicked away for one.
full again, tickled square to keep the strike for the next over.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Nissanka, no run
text: good length ball outside off stump, guided to backward point.
good length ball on middle, punched to mid-on.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Asalanka, no run
text: full and down leg, misses a flick. No wide called as the umpire says it flicked the pads.
flighted full on off stump, slog sweeps this to deep square leg where Shakib makes a sloppy fumble to turn a single into four.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Asalanka, no run
text: full on the legs, misses a flick.
good length ball on middle, shuffles across to flick behind square.
flighted on fourth stump, uses his feet to drive this over mid-off and sails all the way.

shortText: Nasum Ahmed to Asalanka, no run
text: Nasum darts this in flatter on the body, can't flick it away.
slog sweep this time from the crease as Nasum flights this on middle and leg, it clears the largest boundary today and clangs off the facade.
good length ball on the pads, flicked into midwicket for a pair.
good length ball on fifth stump, goes back to flick to long-on.
full on the body, flicked into midwicket for a pair.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Nissanka, no run
text: good length ball at 126 kph on fifth stump, slapped to point.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Nissanka, no run
text: short outside off, goes to pull and beaten for pace.
back of a length on fourth stump, guided into cover for one.
yorker speared down leg.
full toss on the legs, flicked to deep backward square, diving stop on the rope to keep it to a pair.
full on the legs again, this time flicked much finer behind square and Liton can't cut it off at the rope.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Asalanka, no run
text: back of a length on off, guided into point.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Nissanka, no run
text: Nissanka charges first ball trying to attack a wide ball outside off and an inside edge goes to fine leg.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Nissanka, 1 run
text: another skip down the track to a full ball on fifth stump and mishits a drive in the air to wide mid-on fielded on a bounce.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Asalanka, no run
text: full and speared into middle and leg, flicked to fine leg.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Asalanka, 2 runs
text: flighted on middle and leg, sweeps this firmly but picks out backward square leg to come back for a pair.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Asalanka, 1 run
text: full and flicked to long-on.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Nissanka, 1 run
text: full on middle and off, stifled appeal as it comes off the bat then pad and trickles into midwicket.
flighted full on middle, Nissanka shuffles well across his stumps to sweep this high over fine leg, clears the fielder on the ring safely and it goes for four.
full on the legs, skips down the track and chips this over mid-on for one.
good length ball on fourth stump, punched into the covers.
another skip down the track and lofts this full ball off middle and leg high and deep over wide long-on.
full and follows Nissanka backing away from leg but darts it too far down leg and called a wide.
bowls almost a bouncer slamming this short into the legs and pulled behind square for one.
full on middle, flicked into wide mid-on for one.
overpitched to begin on fourth stump and driven crisply through wide mid-off to the rope.
good length ball on fifth stump at 136 kph, opens the face to run this to third man.
good length ball on fifth stump, guided to deep third man once more.
back of a length ball squares up Asalanka, just pushes his hands away from his body awkwardly and an edge flies just wide of the keeper very fine to the third man rope.
back of a length ball on fifth stump, guided to deep point for one.
full on sixth stump, pushes this through the covers for a pair.
good length ball on middle, goes back to flick into midwicket for one.
short on the stumps, flicked into long-on for one.
good length ball on off, goes back to flick into long-on for one.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Nissanka, no run
text: good length darted in quicker and defended.
another good length ball speared in flat and quick on middle, punched to long-on this time around.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Asalanka, no run
text: full on sixth stump, driven firmly but picks out extra cover on the ring.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Nissanka, OUT
text: who else breaks the partnership but the all-time leader in T20Is?! Flighted full on fourth stump and skids on to beat the sweep. He gave it a little more air this time and threw off Nissanka's timing on the shot. All that experience showing off there by Shakib.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to WIA Fernando, no run
text: flighted even more than the wicket ball on fifth stump, defended back to Shakib.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to WIA Fernando, no run
text: zips this in flatter and fuller on fourth stump, defended to cover.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to WIA Fernando, OUT
text: goodness what a momentum swing! To be fair this was an innocuous straight ball that Avishka made look far more challenging than it was. Flighted full on middle and off, Avishka plays around a straight ball that continues on to middle and leg. Another arm ball, or was it just a stock delivery that didn't turn. Either way, that just needed a straight bat but instead Avishka gets too ambitious. Bangladesh won't care though.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to de Silva, no run
text: full on off, driven to cover.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to de Silva, 1 run
text: good length ball on fifth stump, slaps this into the covers to deny Shakib a maiden.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to de Silva, 1 run
text: good length ball on fifth stump, driven in the air to the cover sweeper.
good length ball flicked into the leg side.
short and down leg. No chance to play.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to de Silva, FOUR
text: back of a length ball outside off, drives on the up and a thick edge splits backward point and short third man to the rope.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to de Silva, OUT
text: slower ball lands full on the stumps, skies a drive trying to clear midwicket but he's through the shot early on a 112 kph delivery and skies this high to the man coming in off the rope. Too easy for Naim holding on to the chance 15 yards in from the rope.
short and wide, carves this behind point for a long single.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Rajapaksa, no run
text: full on middle, driven to mid-off and wanted a run but Asalanka sends him back.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Asalanka, no run
text: length ball on the pads, worked towards short fine leg
length ball on the stumps, pushed towards midwicket for one

length ball down the leg side. Goes for the pull-cum-sweep but misses. Called a wide. There's an appeal for caught-behind. The umpire is unmoved but Bangladesh want to review it. Nothing on the UltraEdge. Not out and Bangladesh lose a review
fuller on the stumps, gets low and paddles it fine. Comes back for the second

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Rajapaksa, no run
text: fuller around off, comes forward and defends

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Rajapaksa, no run
text: quicker around off. Defended on the off side
fuller around off, nudges it towards midwicket. The bowler fields it himself
a length ball outside off, slog-swept it towards midwicket. Not in control and it lands well short to the left of deep midwicket
length outside off, stays back and pushes it towards covers
fuller and wider outside off, down the track and drags it towards long-off
length ball around off, gets low and mistimes it over covers. A single to the sweeper
length ball, wider outside off. Looks to flat-bat but ends up toe-ending it towards the bowler
fuller outside off, dragged towards deep midwicket
doesn't matter, says Rajapaksa as he steps down and goes inside out over extra cover. A 66-metre six
down the track again but gets an inside edge this time. Goes past short fine leg for a couple
dropped by Liton. And it goes for four as well. A length ball outside off, Rajapaksa takes a step across and slogs it behind square leg. Liton runs in but it goes through his hands
length outside off, dabs it towards short third man
fifty for Asalanka. Off 32 balls. A touch fuller outside off, pushes it through covers
use of feet to punch this towards sweeper cover
length ball outside off, slapped towards sweeper cover
down the track and even though it was bowled away from the batter, he reaches there and smashes it straight over the bowler's head
length outside off, cuts hard but a diving stop by cover-point
a slog sweep. Didn't really middle it but that's the shorter side and it goes just over the boundary line, between deep midwicket and deep square leg
fired in but way outside off. Perhaps Mahmudullah was thinking the batter will skip down the ground
length outside off, taps it towards cover-point
fuller ball on the stumps, nudges towards square leg. Sixteen from that, a game-changing over?
length outside off, guided towards third man

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Asalanka, no run
text: a length ball angling in from outside off, slashes at it but gets an inside edge onto the body

another dropped catch. Liton is having a bad day in the field. It was a length ball outside off, Asalanka hit it on the up towards sweeper cover. Liton ran in but was a touch slow as the ball went through his finger-tips
a slower one. On a length but down the leg side. Too far away for the glance

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Rajapaksa, no run
text: short length outside off, and beats the bat as Rajapaksa fails to account for the extra bounce
fuller on the stumps, swings across. Gets an inside edge towards fine leg
another wide. Slower length ball down the leg side. Rajapaksa looks to pull it away but it's not in his radar

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Asalanka, no run
text: a length ball outside off, the batter withdraws the shot thinking it might be wide but no. A good call by the umpire
a slower one. On a length on middle and leg and Rajapaksa picks it up behind square leg. Miles in the air and enough on it to carry all the way
into the stands. Fuller around off and this one has been butchered over the deep midwicket, the shorter boundary. Only 34 needed from 28 now
fuller and wider outside off, trying to deny the batter the shorter boundary. Rajapaksa throws his bat at it, and manages to beat short third man. The fielder in the deep cannot cut it off
gives the charge and drags it towards deep midwicket
a full toss outside off, chipped over the bowler's head
another full toss and this has been helped over extra cover. No one in the deep and that's another boundary for Rajapaksa

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Asalanka, 1 run
text: down the track but Shakib slows it down. Asalanka adjusts and nudges it in front of square leg

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Rajapaksa, 2 runs
text: down the track and slogged towards deep midwicket. That's the longer boundary. Naim makes an excellent stop near the boundary, takes the catch but gets rid of the ball just before stepping on to the boundary cushion. Third umpire is having a close look at it but is happy with the end

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Rajapaksa, 1 run
text: length ball on the pads, flicked behind square leg

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Asalanka, no run
text: length ball on the stumps, defended down the ground

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Asalanka, SIX
text: down the track, isn't to the pitch of the ball but checks his shot and sends it over the long-off boundary

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Asalanka, 1 run
text: length ball on the stumps, flicked towards square leg

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Asalanka, no run

text: digs out this fuller delivery outside off towards point

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Rajapaksa, no run
text: a wide yorker. Rajapaksa jams his bat but cannot connect

a length all outside off. Steered past the diving short third man and Rajapaksa is coming back for the second. Mushfiqur collects the throw and flicks it onto the stumps but Rajapaksa is safe. That's fifty for him, off just 28 balls. On birthday too
a low full toss, digs it out back towards the bowler who fumbles and that's one more to the total

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Asalanka, no run
text: another wide yorker. Fails to put bat onto that
fuller on the stumps and this one has been reverse-swept towards deep-backward point
bowled 'im! Backs away early and exposes his stumps, allowing the bowler slow it down. Goes for the cut but fails to connect and the ball clatters into the stumps
a length ball around off, cuts it towards sweeper cover
down the track but gets a thick outside edge towards deep-backward point. Picks up two more
that's the winning runs. An outside edge goes through the vacant first-slip region. Fuller on the stumps and Asalanka backs away and looks to push at it. A genuine edge that runs away for four
tossed up outside off, driven back to the bowler
fuller and wider, driven to extra-cover on the edge of the circle
a bit shorter, goes back to work this from around off stump out to deep midwicket
slow flight outside off, presses forward and blocks square on the off side
flat now, shorter, rocks back and punches to short extra-cover. There was no deep point back, so Lewis may feel he missed out on a boundary there

shot! Moeen looks to take away Lewis' arms by firing it full and flat at the stumps, but he shows he doesn't need too much swinging room. Just gets his front leg out of the way and shovels it crisply back over the bowler's head. Excellent leverage from the bottom hand
back of a length, angling into off stump, shuffles across to work it to the left of short fine leg
back of a length, angling across to finish on off stump or so, defended back to the bowler

oh wow, what a terrific catch that is! Moeen Ali, stunning. Turns around at mid-off, runs towards the boundary with the ball descending from over his right shoulder. Has to reach for the ball in the end, but he keeps his balance and takes it on the sprint. A change of pace from Woakes, bowled it fuller while angling it across the stumps, and it left Lewis like an offcutter and caused him to skew it high off the outside half of the bat while looking to go over the bowler's head
back of a length on off stump, steps across to work it to deep square leg
length ball slanting across to off stump, presses forward and opens his bat face to dab to backward point, who dives right to make a good stop
slants it wider outside off, gets it to swing in just a touch. Gayle just watches it through to the keeper
tossed up outside off, presses forward and blocks into the on side

down the track now to the flighted ball on off stump, and he picks out the fielder in the deep! Looks to hit with the turn, and he connects well, but he ends up hitting it straight to the man at deep midwicket, who takes it with both hands in front of his chest
flighted ball around off stump, stretches out and defends to midwicket
flatter, drifting in and going with the arm after pitching on off stump. Looks to defend it back to the bowler, ends up playing to square leg off the inside edge
slower, pulls his length slightly back around off stump, stretches out and blocks it back to the bowler
slides on with the arm and beats Hetmyer's attempt at a back-foot flick. Good take down the leg side, and a bit of an appeal, but it only brushed pad

oh, that's super timing from Gayle. Length ball slanting across, and he presses forward and leans into a push, just helps it with the angle into the gap between extra-cover and mid-off diving to his right, and it just keeps going and going thereafter
bam. Drops a touch short, offers a touch of width, and Gayle hammers a cut past the left hand of Roy diving full-length at backward point
slower length ball on the stumps. Looks to press forward and push into the covers, ends up playing slightly in the air but it bounces well short of the fielder at extra-cover
length ball on off stump, blocked to extra-cover
back of a length, straightens a touch towards off stump, cramping Gayle for room slightly. Lets it come and dabs gently into the point region and saunters to the other end
full, slanting into a wide-ish line outside off, and that's not a bad ball with cover point back on the boundary sweeping. Hetmyer eases a drive to that man for a single
nice footwork. Drifts one in towards leg stump and he steps out to swipe it over midwicket

this is excellent batting, taking the sting out of the match-up, and ensuring West Indies have momentum despite the loss of two early wickets. Steps out, this time skips inside the line of an off-stump ball to chip it over extra-cover
flat length ball on leg stump, presses forward to block to extra-cover

gone, picked the wrong length for that shot, and Moeen has two! Flat one sliding on with the arm into the stumps, and Hetmyer, opening up at the hip, is cramped for room on the pull. It isn't short enough either, and he ends up flat-batting it to Morgan at mid-on, stationed right on the edge of the 30-yard circle
flat length ball on off stump, defended into the covers
floated up slow outside off, uses his wrists to whip that back to the bowler
back of a length on off stump, defended into the covers
ooh, some extra bounce in the corridor, from just back of a length. Was looking to make room and punch it on the up through the covers, ends up being beaten
slower yorker, on the pads, clipped to short fine leg

and there's that extra bounce again, plus a hint of shape away from the left-hander. Length ball in the corridor, and Gayle makes a bit of room and looks to thrash it away through the covers with a diagonal bat, and once again the ball goes past his outside edge
short, offers a bit of width, and Gayle puts it away. Uses the width while opening up at the hips to carve it away over cover point

England's catching has been outstanding today, and now it's Malan at midwicket, on the edge of the circle. He tracks to his right and then dives to take it with both nands reverse-cupped. Mills' extra pace does the trick here. Good short ball, getting up around Gayle's back shoulder, and he's late on the pull. Ends up hitting it much straighter than he probably intended, and off the high part of the bat, into the air
length ball, keeps going with the arm, beats the inside edge on the front-foot flick, and hits the front pad, but it's going down leg
length ball close to off stump, defended back to the bowler
fuller, on middle and leg, driven firmly inside-out, back to the bowler
drops a touch short around off stump and Pooran rocks back to pull along the floor to deep midwicket
length ball turning in from outside off, presses forward to clip into the square leg region
slider, keeps going with the arm towards leg stump, presses forward and blocks to midwicket

and there's some vintage Bravo. Short and wide, and he carves it away with that whirling follow-through to hit it up and over backward point and leave the sweeper, who's in front of square, too much work to do

everything's going England's way here. Jordan goes short and wide again, and Bravo unfurls another whirling cut, but this time he hits it straight to the man at backward point, at catching height. Wow. Replay shows it's just about catching height. Bends low to pick it up inches off the ground, with both hands
full outside off, driven to mid-off
length ball close to off stump, defended to extra-cover
hits that hard length close to off stump, and hurries Pollard on the pull. Too early on the shot, and it bounces into the point region off the high part of the bat
full on off stump, and Pollard clips it away to the right of long-on. Two may have been on offer, but they only take one
back of a length at the pads, tucked away to the left of fine leg
slants a fullish slower ball wide of off stump, and Pollard leaves it alone. Umpire signals wide
back of a length on off stump, defended back to the bowler
slower ball, ends up down the leg side, past the attempted flick from Pooran
length ball wide of off stump, and Pooran is beaten while trying to drive through the covers. Extra pace and bounce to beat the angled bat. 143kph
short outside off, looks to jump and hook but realises the line is against him, and ends up leaving it alone. One bouncer for the over signalled

got him, West Indies are six down. Full outside off, inviting the big cover drive, and Pooran goes for it and nicks it through to Buttler. It just feels like a day when nothing will go their way. Snatched at that shot a little, but it was there to be driven in this format
another attempted slower ball ends up down the leg side. Quite a way down leg, and Pooran has a go at a standing sweep but can't connect

haha. Nothing sums up West Indies' approach (it wins a lot of matches, so not knocking it at all) better. Length ball slanting away from off stump, and with West Indies six down in the ninth over, Russell clears his front leg and looks to launch his first ball over mid-off. Doesn't connect
back of a length at the hip, tucked away through backward square leg
length ball angling down leg, looks to flick and misses, gets hit on the pad

and again, looks like Jordan is getting his offcutter to grip a little. Looks to flick off the front foot, and he inside-edges towards midwicket. Pad came in the way of his bat, and bat hit pad on its way to hitting ball
back of a length, angling into the body, misses the flick and it hits him on the thigh pad
back of a length outside off, dabbed to backward point
short, rising ball outside off, and Pollard leaves it alone

bowls him through the gate! Things get worse for West Indies, Russell gone second ball! Rashid into the attack and amongst 'em immediately - looks like a superbly executed slider, drifting in and then skidding on as Russell looked to defend. He left a gap and the ball snuck through, straight into middle stump. West Indies looking thoroughly rattled out there
stays over the wicket, tossed up on middle and leg, Hosein blocks
pushed through, brings the bat down straight and jabs away to leg
tossed up, Hosein opens the face a touch and squirts it towards backward point
flighted legbreak, skips on to hit the front pad and loop short into the leg side
looped up on off, Hosein props forward, steers one through vacant mid-off and they trot the one
short ball into the ribcage, nudged leg side for one
pace off and Pollard steps across, dabs into the off side for one
back of a length, Hosein pushes into the covers and they scamper another quick single
fullish length, 140kph/87mph on leg stump, clipped through backward square
slower ball outside off, Hosein reaches for it tentatively and gets a bottom edge through to the keeper
angling in at pace, thuds into the pads and Mills goes up... think maybe some inside edge on that

oh my, another one holes out! Polly wants a crack here but he's picked the wrong ball, and he sends it hard and flat into the grateful gullet of Bairstow at long-on! Rashid again strikes with the first delivery of his over, West Indies threatening to blow themselves out with plenty unbowled

tossed up, and tossed away! Picks out long-on first ball! West Indies are swinging like a rusty gate, McCoy gone for a golden duck. Absolutely disastrous shot choice, with his team right in the mire. Rashid simply strolling up and accepting candy
beats the outside edge! Flights the legbreak and Rampaul plays just inside it
floated up on the stumps, blocked
nudged off the pads for one to square leg, ironic cheers for the Windies 50
this kicks up from a length, possible a googly, jabbed down from the crease
shortish and tucked away for one
Hosein slashes and gets this away into a gap out towards deep backward point
back of a length, zipping through past the bat as he hangs back
pitched up, slower ball down at 110kph/68mph, clipped off the toes through midwicket
bangs this in with pace on, 142kph and it climbs past the splice as Rampaul attempts to get bat on ball
back of a length, dabbed down behind square on the off side
flights the googly, Rampaul is back and motions it through to the keeper

dirty heave and Rampaul is castled! West Indies have Wile E Coyote-d themselves into oblivion in their World Cup opener, bowled out for just 55 inside 15 overs! Rashid pockets his fourth with a legbreak that dips and spins to hit the woodwork as Rampaul swings like a barn door in a gale. England's spinner was held back until halfway but ends up with figures of FOUR for TWO
tossed up and punched into the covers
full, fast and drifting in, Roy looks skittish but jabs one through mid-on
length ball, defended coming across on off stump
thrashed through the covers, England get their first boundary as Buttler steps out and pounds a drive
fired in quick, 95kph and Buttler punches this to mid-off
arm ball to finish, sliding in off the fingertips, Buttler defends
fullish length in the channel, 132kph/82mph and tapped away
Roy gets slight squared up coming across, squirts a thickish edge to backward point on the bounce
good length angling in on the stumps, prodded back towards mid-on for one
length on fourth stump, 133kph and Buttler steers it away square
overpitched and Buttler rams through point! Slightly wide and he just reaches out and fizzes the hands
short of a length outside off, dabbed to backward point
smashed over extra cover, goes all the way! Roy tucks in with his first shot in anger - and quite a stroke that is. Plants the front foot and takes Hosein to the cleaners
fired down outside off, 94kph, punched to long-off for one
jabbed into the covers and they scurry one
