pushed through and Roy punches this past extra cover, Buttler wants two but won't get it
angled in flat and nudged leg side
darted on the stumps, worked away through midwicket

flipped straight to midwicket! West Indies have the breakthrough... Just a touch of pace off from Rampaul, cutting his fingers down the side and Roy was through his flick early, could only pop a head-height catch to Gayle
pitched up on middle and leg, defended
fullish, Bairstow is across, shows it a straight bat
punched crisply down the ground, gets it past mid-off and the ball gallops away for four!
slightly wide and hammered through point now! Length ball and Bairstow just sits in the crease and throws the hands
slower ball, length on the stumps, nudged away leg side

jabbed back to the bowler! Angled in flat, no turn from the arm ball, Bairstow was looking to clip it for one and got a thickish inside edge - it almost didn't carry but Hosein got down well to take a low catch to his right. Is there a wobble in this chase after all?
over the wicket, pushed through leg side and comes off the pad
length outside off, no turn and tapped to cover
flicks this with the angle fine of the man on the edge of the ring for a couple
fired in on the pads, Moeen nurdles into a gap in front of square
little bit more air on middle and leg, Buttler works it around the corner for one
over the wicket and slanting across, Buttler opens the face and swipes a couple behind point

mix-up and Moeen is a long way from home... Buttler declined the run with his partner three-quarters of the way down and although McCoy had to collect the throw from short third and relay it into the stumps, Moeen looks short. Yes, gone! Tried to scramble back but isn't quick enough and England lose their third in the Powerplay (and you all know what that stat means)
length ball on middle and leg, pace off at 119kph and tucked leg side
pace off again, 105kph/65mph up towards the blockhole, Buttler drags a slog leg side to the sweeper
Buttler looks to move across and scoop, McCoy responds with a slow full toss that the batter misses... but he's been pinged for a front-foot no-ball in the process
short ball in the channel, Livingstone plays a no-nonsense dab past backward point
another slower delivery on the pads, nudged to midwicket

Hosein takes a stunner! Leading edge from Livingstone, but it was travelling... only for Hosein to leap across and snag the ball one-handed to his left. There's some discussion between the umpires, Aleem Dar wants to be sure that Hosein didn't ground the ball as he came down - but the soft signal is out. Chris Brown, the TV umpire, is taking several looks at this, but he's eventually satisfied. Don't think you could prove his fingers weren't underneath the ball as he put his hand down
over the wicket, lobbed up on off, Morgan prods it through mid-on
dragged down slightly and slapped through point, there's a sweeper out there
tossed up full, clipped to long-on
round the wicket and cut for another single to the man at deep point
pushed through at 93kph/58mph, Morgan tucks to leg - Hosein is finished for the night, finishing with a very creditable 2 for 24
shortish, angling across and Buttler runs it away behind square
dug in short and Morgan rides it, tucked to midwicket
goes full with pace off, I think, dinked wide of extra cover for another single

swung leg side, did Walsh get fingertips to that? I think he did, but he was flying, a brilliant effort from the substitute fielder at deep backward square - the boundary brings up England's 50 and brings them within touching distance of victory
short ball again, tapped down this time
finishes with a quick bumper, Morgan pulls and misses - vociferous appeal from behind the stumps but the umpire isn't interested
short slower ball outside off, and Buttler brings his wrists into a fierce chop that sends sweeper cover sprawling to his left to stop it

and that is that. Pollard bangs it short outside off, gets it up above shoulder height, but at his pace Buttler can still adjust to get on top of the bounce and smack a pull to beat long leg to his left
full at the stumps, comes forward and drives nicely through the covers. Hint of swing
good length at off stump, 137kph, driven to mid-off
terrific shot! He's nailed that. Full outside off, comes forward and drives powerfully wide of mid-pff
through the off side again, it's finding the middle, Starc full with a touch more width outside off, it doesn't swing back, Bavuma gets well forward and drives square through point
edged this time, reaching out away from his body, but it's safely down to third

shortText: Starc to de Kock, no run
text: short and wide, but doesn't get any timing as he drives off the back foot to cover. Good start for South Africa
over the wicket, full and straight, clipped out to deep midwicket
round the wicket, angled in full at leg stump, pushed down the ground
through him! Maxwell strikes. Pushed through a touch quicker, but think he's basically missed a straight one. It did turn a little, very awkward position Bavuma got himself in

shortText: Maxwell to van der Dussen, 1 run
text: full outside off, whips it with the wrists through midwicket
round the wicket, short outside leg stump, pulled powerfully backward of square but deep square can intercept. Gets away with that

shortText: Maxwell to van der Dussen, 1 run
text: on the back foot and works into the leg side

shortText: Hazlewood to van der Dussen, OUT
text: edged, caught behind! He strikes first ball. Lovely delivery, in the channel outside off, a Test-match length, van der Dussen pushing off the back foot and it's through to Wade
another edge! Back of a length outside off, pushing away from the body, but this goes wide of the single slip

shortText: Hazlewood to de Kock, no run
text: back of a length at middle and off, 136kph, gets an inside edge into the pads as he aims to work it away

shortText: Hazlewood to de Kock, no run
text: takes the pad again as aims to whip to the leg side, Hazlewood making sure he doesn't give a drive ball

shortText: Hazlewood to de Kock, no run
text: a middle-and-leg line, punched off the pads to midwicket

shortText: Hazlewood to de Kock, no run
text: fuller outside off, slices across the drive a little bit and it runs to point. Superb over from Hazlewood
full outside off, pushed to mid-on
uses his feet and works it off the stumps out to deep midwicket

shortText: Maxwell to de Kock, no run
text: round the wicket, gives himself room to the leg side and drives to cover
dragged down too short, he rocks back and pulls it over wide mid-on

shortText: Maxwell to de Kock, no run
text: steps to leg again and square drives, can't beat cover for the second time in the over
reverse sweep, a bottom edge saves him from a very big lbw shout, scuttles away through short third

he's played it on! What a way to go. He moved across well outside off stump to scoop a back-of-a-length delivery, plays it into his thigh pad, it bounces into the crease and the backspin takes it into the stumps. Blimey, de Kock will feel a bit hard done by there. One of the more curious 'bowled' dismissals you'll see
back of a length outside off, cut off the bottom edge into the pitch
punched off the back foot square to backward point
touch fuller, outside off, he's across the crease and defends to midwicket
full at off stump, 140kph, defended to cover
another good delivery, nips back from just short of a length, defended to the leg side and it's a wicket maiden. Brilliant stuff from Hazlewood
short of a length, straight, played into midwicket
fuller, at the stumps, pushed towards mid-off
strangled appeal for lbw...he shuffled across the stumps and went to pull to the leg side. Struck outside the line
well timed! That's a superb shot. Just back of a length outside off, Markram drives it on his toes wide of mid-off
goes fuller, drives and the inside goes into his boot then to the off side, some hesitancy over the run but it's safe in the end
full and straight, a punchy on-drive can't quite beat the infield
full at the pads, bobbles to the leg side
very full outside off, driven into the pitch and it goes out to cover who can't quite get it with a dive
steps back to leg to a delivery outside off, square cuts through backward point, a superb save by Marsh running around the point boundary...full-length dive and flick back
touch quicker, 94kph, and slides on, he's able to work it down to long-on
strikes this well, it's a slog-sweep from outside off but it goes very square...perfectly between the two deep fielders
a short delivery pushed through, he goes for the pull and gets a bottom edge into his pads
full at off stump, he's right across the stumps and clips into midwicket. Was a slower ball at 114kph
great shot! Full outside off with some width, threads the drive wide of mid-off. Power and placement
tucked off the pads backward of square down to long leg
short on off stump, stands tall and punches off the back foot to cover
the bottom hand comes into play as he shovels this down to long-on
taken at backward point! Full at off stump, he's aiming to the leg side, the bat face closes, takes a leading edge and is well taken diving forward
length ball outside off, driven square and finds backward point
full on the pads, wrong line, clipped in front of square through the leg side
between the wickets there's been some great drives today, this is another as Markram gets a stride forward and places it between cover and mid-off
goes short, looked a slightly round-arm action, drags a pull down to long leg
a straight full toss, not quite coming out right for Starc, but only costs a single as it's clipped to deep midwicket
that one nearly gets through! Full at leg stump, hint of shape, Markram makes to get the bat on it
round the wicket, full at the pads, clipped to short fine leg
tucks a straight delivery through midwicket and the placement allows the second
worked into midwicket
short of a length outside off, can't beat cover with a back-foot drive
flicks a straight delivery to deep midwicket
full and straight, driven down to ground to long-off
good length and sliding into the pad as he gets deep and looks to flick
full and pushed through at the toes, gets forward and flicks it between deep square and deep mid
full and just outside off, driven into the pitch and to Zampa's left. He lunges to stop it in the follow through but can't collect
short of a length and pushed through quick outside off, backs away and punches to sweeper
short of a length and tight at the body, cops that on the thigh as he looks to punch through midwicket off the back foot
good length at middle stump, flicked to midwicket off the front foot
short of a length outside off, steps out and punches to long-off
short at off stump, clears the front leg for the pull, gets a thick outside edge to deep midwicket
good length and skidding on at middle and leg line, gets an inside edge onto pad as he looks to whip off the back foot
good length at leg stump, hurriedly flicked to deep midwicket

close run-out chance off his own bowling. Good length outisde off, reaches out and pushes this to Maxwell's left, around the short midwicket area. He's onto it quickly with his left hand and then turns ever so quickly as he switches the ball to his right hand and has a shy at the non-striker's. Miller was diving and possibly out with a direct hit
shot. Short and wide outside off, Markram rocks onto the back foot and slashes this firmly past backward point

run-out appeal. Short of a length outside off, looks to squeeze that to third man and gets an inside edge in Wade's direction. They sneak the run, he hits the stumps direct at the non-striker's, but Miller had stretched and made his ground easily
full and just outside off, mistimed drive off the toe-end, to mid-off's left
good length and just outside off, nervous flick to midwicket's left and yet another tight single
good length at middle stump, pushed uppishly to long-on
good length and just outside off, closes the face and nudges this into the vacant midwicket region with soft hands
short of a length and tight at leg stump, he shapes to pull but that has skidded on and kept low. Thick edge to midwicket
full and just outside off, jams it down to long-off with the turn
googly, tossed right up at middle stump. Gets to the pitch of that and opens the face to run this to extra cover's right. Marsh dives but it evades him

lbw looks plumb and is given, but Miller reviews immediately. Has he got bat on that or is he counting on it pitching outside leg? Remember, Zampa is over the wicket to him. He's been struck in front of the stumps trying to sweep a full ball from middle stump. No bat on it says third umpire, and that is a slider from Zampa. Not a legbreak. So it's gone on straight from a leg stump line and caught Miller's bent back leg on the thigh, right in front of middle stump, which would have been knocked back if the leg wasn't in the way. Plumb.
short of a length and skidding low on in the corridor, shapes to cut and just manages to get it away off the inder-edge
good length at middle stump, gets forward and whips against the turn towards long-on

got him! Pretorius looking to cut again, but unlike the last one, this is a climbing legbreak at pace just outside off. You'd argue it's still too close to cut. He's had a hurried flap at it and got a decent amount of outside edge on it. Neat grab from Wade
good length and just outside off, walks into the line of this and shovels uppishly to long-on
good length and just outside off, gets forward and defends to extra cover

oh dear, this is turning into an embarrassing first day for South Africa. Short of a length ball just outside off, he stabs it towards point who has a shy at the non-striker's stumps and misses. Maharaj wants the overthrow but Markram's got his back turned on him as he was stretching to get back from the previous throw. Maharaj has hared down already and then slips as he looks to turn back. The throw is very wide at the striker's end but Maharaj's recovery time means Wade can hold it to his right, turn to his left and take aim, before diving to the stumps to break them well before Maharaj can come close
short of a length and across the corridor, left alone

looks like he's struck him on the helmet. Banged in short and headed towards his throat. Rabada takes his eyes off as he makes a late to decision to duck it, but that is an awkward line and hits him around the chin area. He's on his feet and shows the thumbs up as Cummins checks on him
good length and just outside off, punched to extra cover off the back foot
full at middle stump, steps out and drills it along the turf to deep midwicket
good length at middle stump, defended off the back foot
good length at middle stump, flicked to long-on with the turn
short and wide outside off, gets the toe end on his cut, straight to point
full at leg stump, leans in and flicks to deep midwicket
yorker length at middle stump, clears the front leg and jams it into the covers

sweet! Markram playing a different game at the other end, keeping his team in this. Short of a length and just outside off, and he gets the front foot out and is so stable as he swings this over the midwicket boundary with a pull
low full toss outside off, looks to carve it through cover, gets it off the inside part of the toe end to long-on
full and very wide outside off, left alone
good length and tight at middle stump, backs away and pats it down the pitch
slapped past mid-off! Signs that is a pretty good batting pitch. Good length and across the corridor, but sits up and comes on nicely. Rabada backs away and sends this past Markram's face on the up
low full toss at leg stump, following him a little. Looks to flick and gets a leading edge back towards the bowler
yorker at leg stump, pushed down the pitch

one goes Starc's way at last! This will feel good. He's around the wicket, looking to fire in the yorker. Misses out marginally - it's headed down leg and is at driving length. Markram wants to use his pace and angle to chip this between deep midwicket and long-on, but he's managed to find the former with precision. Looked good but he's fallen short of batting through the innings
yorker nailed at off stump, with some dip inwards. Jammed down the pitch
full and dipping into leg stump, clears the front foot for the slog, but that's come off the inside half of the bat
good length and moving away from the corridor as Rabada clears the front leg and looks to hit it over the bowler
good length and just outside off, looks to lift that over extra cover but the bat turns too much and this plonks into the turf in front of sweeper
low full toss at off stump, opens the face and carves this to third man's right
yorker following him down leg side, flicks it onto his pad and it trickles down to Cummins
high-ish full toss on leg stump, swings across the line of that and gets it close to the sticker. Two to long-on's left
slower bouncer, pitching outside leg and rising at the head. Ducks to leave that
full and into the pads, looks to flick and can't make connection
full and wide outside off, can't get bat on it, but Wade doesn't gather cleanly
full and at the stumps, patted past the bowler with a straight bat
full and just outside off, clears the front leg and drives to long-on's right

swatted over long-on, one-handed! Very baseball. Lovely full toss at a leg stump line, watches that closely and swings in long-on's direction. It's come right off the middle and has enough to clear him by some distance
yorker tailing in furiously at Rabada's toes, manages to save them and squeeze this towards short fine off his pads
easy grab at extra cover. Full and at the stumps from around the wicket, closes the face and gets a leading edge for Finch to grab
yorker from around the wicket, curves away from off stump as Shamsi backs away to protect his toes and has a flap at it. Beaten, but Rabada alert to get to the other end

run-out appeal at the non-striker's end. This is a full toss following Rabada down leg, he hauls it to deep midwicket's right and Shamsi comes back for the second, puts in the dive, and makes his ground before the ball's arrived at the stumps
over the wicket, short outside off, punched at the top of the bounce into the covers
tight run! Finch might have been gone with a hit. Warner pushed it into the off side and set off. Maybe just home
uses his feet and walks at Rabada then lobs a short-of-a-length delivery into the air on the leg side but it falls safely
that's quick...141kph, short outside off, zips over Finch's top edge as he fences at it
back of a length at off stump, 141kph, defended on the back foot
angled well down the leg side
fuller, Finch's footwork not great as he comes forward, takes a thickish edge to the leg side
full outside off, beats the edge as Warner aims for a booming cover drive
full at middle, worked off the pads into midwicket
back of a length at off stump, 142kph, played into backward point with an open face
back on the stumps, tucked to the on side
pushed down the leg side, excellent one-handed take from de Kock
taken at third man! Wide outside off, Finch threw everything into a drive, it skewed off the top edge and was neatly taken as Rabada moved to his left
over the top edge! Some heat on that one. Short of a length outside off, Marsh going after it straightaway
short, at the body, and he latches on with a pull through square leg. That will make him feel better
back of a length at off stump, played square into the covers
keeps it short on off stump, defended on the back foot
full at off stump, a trade-mark punchy cover drive from Warner beats the inner ring
drags the length back, on middle and leg, cramps Warner for room and takes the thigh guard...145kph that one
oh dear! That's a big full toss, Warner manages to play it into the off side and looks for the no-ball call but the square leg umpire says it's okay
full and square, whipped strongly in front of square and runs over the quick outfield
back of a length, straight, Marsh swings across the line and it takes him high on the pads
full at off stump, driven firmly back to the bowler...phew, 150kph (93mph)
short of a length, goes for a pull and it hammers into his hip...that will sting
back of a length at off stump, 143kph, defended
full at the stumps, driven firmly into the pitch and bounces up to the bowler. Good comeback after the boundary
width outside off, Warner takes advantage with a square drive through point
short of a length, goes deep in the crease and defends to cover
well caught! The gamble pays off to keep Rababa on. Full outside off, Warner goes for the drive but slices the shot and can't keep it down or get it wide of the fielder at backward point
back of a length outside off, driven into the covers
a bouncer, angled over middle and leg, looked very short but is judged legal

short on off stump, that's a superbly controlled pull shot as he rolls his wrists and sends it backward of square...it almost gets flicked back by Pretorius, but trickles into the rope. Well, appears the third umpire has said it was cut off. I must need my eyes testing
pushed off the pads into midwicket
full on the pads, clipped into the on side
fraction short of a length, driven off the back foot to long-off
full and straight, driven to the bowler
goes back outside leg stump and straight-pulls this down the ground, not quite where he was aiming
flicked off the pads to square leg
over the wicket, full outside off, driven sweetly through the covers and gives the sweeper some work
on the stumps, worked off the pads backward of square
full outside off, connects well with a reverse sweep but straight to short third
goes back to a short delivery that doesn't quite bounce, pulled to deep midwicket
worked off the pads through square leg...wanted the second but they decline
goes for the reverse sweep again and again hits it well but straight to the fielder at backward point
round the wicket, short on off stump, leans back and drives to deep cover
stands outside leg stump and drives firmly to long-off, and very good running makes the second
again stays leg side of it, drives to long-off
comes down the pitch and plays down the ground to long-on
taken at deep midwicket! A full delivery, angling into the pads, Marsh opted for the leg side and tried to clear deep midwicket but it came off the bottom of the bat
there's some edge in this as he works it from outside off, but it was reasonably well controlled towards short third
worked off the pads to deep midwicket
full outside off, drives down the ground...Australia need a few calm overs
clipped off the toes through square leg
this slides across outside off, Smith opens the face and it runs through short third
full outside off, goes across the crease and defends

goodness me! Lucky on two fronts. Gets a big inside edge past the stumps as he drives, then it would have been tight for a run out after David Miller swooped from short fine, but the throw was a touch wide and de Kock couldn't gather it. Maxwell would have been out
back of a length outside off, punched to deep cover
beats the edge as he plays off the back foot against a short-of-a-length delivery that zips through
on off stump, pushed through the covers
length ball outside off, square drives into point
full at off stump, that on-drive sounded good off the bat as it went to long-on
full and straight, flicked off the pads to deep midwicket
good length and into leg stump, flicked through square leg
back of a length at middle stump, punched to long-on off the back foot
good length at leg stump, gets forward and turns it into vacant midwicket. Maharaj tracks it down himself with a sprint
good length and straight on at the pads, punched to long-on from deep in the crease
good length and some grip this time, turns it away from off and Maxwell can't get enough with his jab towards long-on
appeal for catch being down leg but they won't review it. Good length and sliding on with the arm as he looks to flick off the front foot, nice take from QDK. It was off Maxwell's pad
uppish but wide of Pretroius' outstretched left arm. Good length and sticking a bit as Smith gets forward to drive. It ends up safely at mid-off
good length and into off stump, shuffles and whips to deep square
offcutter at a length on off stump, shuffles and touch and goes with the turn to deep midwicket
good length outside off, leans in and carves this out to sweeper cover
good length outside off, leans into the line of this and punches firmly to sweeper cover
good length and just outside off, drives on the up to sweeper cover
tossed up and slowed right down as it skids on with the arm at leg stump, wanted to drive through cover with the turn, but this is off the inside half and at midwicket
length and into the stumps, driven to long-on off the front foot
just short of deep midwicket! Gets this to dip on a good length, Maxwell splits his legs and looks to heave it leg-side. Miscues it completely

lovely placement. Backs into the leg side in anticipation of Maharaj pushing it into his body. And into his body it is. At a good length, but Smith is deep in the crease and punches this over extra cover off the back foot
good length at middle stump, swept to deep square
good length on leg stump, whipped to deep midwicket

swatted over backward point! Puts pressure on Shamsi straight away and they can get this over out of the way without risks now. Good length and at off stump, gets low, gets his right leg well into the off side to create room and reverses this
tossed up at off stump, driven past the non-striker to long-off
good length and flat at off stump, flicked to midwicket off the front foot
tossed up outside off, leans in and drills this past Maxwell's head, long-off cleans up
good length at middle stump, gets another reverse hoick out, but along the ground to deep backward point
short of a length and across off stump, backs away and slices straight to backward point
short of a length and into the pads, looks to swipe that with the angle and gets it off the thigh guard
good length and outside off, 141kph. Comes on nicely as Smith crouches into a flowing square drive. Straight to point

shout for lbw and a good one, I thought. South Africa won't review it. Good length and slanted into off stump, he shuffles to flick and is caught in front. But on the thigh guard, so possibly going over
swung away over midwicket. Marginally short outside off, shuffles and pulls it - a bit off the inside half - and gets it over the only fielder in that region

sensational work from Markram! My word. They don't have the runs but South Africa have been world class in the field. It's another short of a length ball in the corridor and this time Smith gets good connection on the pull. But it's straighter than the last shot and Markram is fielding about 20 yards in from the long-on boundary. He bursts to his right and keeps his eyes on this until the last moment. By the time he's prepared for this stunning full-stretched dive to his right, the ball is behind him. But he's got two hands safely around it to grab inches from the ground. Superb, superb stuff. Add this to the list of SA's heroics in the field already after that Bavuma catch in the warm-ups
short and up at the ribs, pulled firmly to deep square's left and Rabada puts in a slide to get behind that
good length and turning in from off stump, clattered back at the bowler who sticks out a boot. This is Shamsi's boot, mind you, it's doubled up as a phone in the past. Now a shield, apparently...

Shamsi takes off! Maxwell's success with the reverse sweep is over for the day. This one a switch hit, actually. This is full, pushed through at middle stump, and he's ended up outside its line at off stump. Swings furiously at it but he was playing catch up, that slid through and split the stumps. 50th T20I wicket for him
full at middle stump, leans in and flicks to deep midwicket
tossed up at leg stump, gets on a knee and plays the reverse paddle, straight to short third

oooh tight. Tight. Stoinis saved by the slowness of the surface. He's pinned deep in the crease trying to push this incoming ball through square leg. But it's not quick enough to trouble him and he manages an inside edge
full at leg stump, gets forward and flicks to deep square
low full toss at leg stump, punched out to long-on's right
yorker across off stump, gets low and chops it to third man's left
full and into leg stump, flicked out to deep midwicket

past mid-off and into the boundary! Not to be this time for Markram. Offcutter at a length just outside off, drives on the up and loses control. But it's to Markram's right and dipping in front of him. He looks for the catch, as is probably right at this stage, but he can't get under that and it bounces away from under him
yorker at off stump, squeezed hurriedly into the covers

superbly done. Expert limited-overs batting from Wade that. Short of a length and across him outside off. He shuffles a long way into the off side but doesn't lose balance or his eyes on the ball. Manages to ramp it wide of short fine
he shuffles to try and open up the boundary over square leg, but swats this straight to deep midwicket on the bounce. Good length ball wide outside off and he sort of fell into the line there
full and wide outside off, driven firmly to sweeper cover
called wide! Oh that's a close one. Full floaty slower ball just by the tramline. Wade has a hack at it and is beaten. Looked to be under his bat, but was also just past the tramline. Tough call
good length outside off, shuffles and hammers this on the rise to long-off
full slower ball outside off, shapes for the ramp again after going a long way into the off side, but is forced to jab this behind point
slower ball at a length outside off, walks into the line and crunches along the ground to long-on's left
full slower ball, very wide outside off from around the wicket. Gets a strong base on one knee but can't manage to get more power on this boisterous drive. Straight to long-off
misses out. Knee height full toss across off stump and Wade has a big slash at it. Helps to have Nortje's pace because this has sliced off the face and to deep backward point

dropped in the follow through. Very sharp opportunity, just does well to get a hand on it. He's missed his length again though. This is overpitched at off, front leg out the way and crunched aerially back at the bowler. He sticks out his right hand
missed length again but he's set a field for this. Another knee high full toss outside off, can only get it out to deep extra cover
overpitched and wide outside off, throws his hands at that and gets a thick outside edge on the bounce to deep backward point

drags it over midwicket! Nortje's length is off yet again and this time the field isn't set for it. It's a slower ball, but it's dropped short outside off and gives Stoinis enough time to swing at it. It's off the thick inside edge but it's enough because there's no one in the deep there
full and just outside off, shuffles and drives off the toe-end to long-off
they sneak a second from deep midwicket. Loopy slower ball outside off, met on the full and dragged to deep midwicket's right. He's all the way back on that big boundary and can't stop the second

get out of the way! Absolutely hammered past the umpire. It's a good length ball at off stump at a lovely hitting pace. And a lovely hit is. Deep in the crease for a big swing at it and it's about waist height, but it has whistled past everyone into the straight boundary
good length and just outside off, driven firmly but straight to mid-off
finishes it off! Full toss at middle stump, just had to get it in front of square with this slog, and he manages to do that. No one at the midwicket boundary and that trickles in
swinging back in to the left-hander. Huge, excitable appeal but the Dutch sneak a bye as the keeper fails to collect
tucks it past fine leg and scampers back for two - first runs off the bat for the Dutch
tailing back into the pads once more. A faint inside edge likely saves him from lbw

struggled for timing as he pushed it into the offside and set off for one - direct hit and we go to the third umpire. Replays show he's well out! Sri Lanka strike, they look really up for this contest
up and over extra cover. Captain Shanaka leapt to his right in the air as he tried to pluck it out of the air but it's got just enough elevation to clear him. First boundary for the Dutch
drags that one too far down the offside
keeps a little low, and he misses the cut. Electric start
expansive front foot drive to short cover
good length, didn't quite know whether to come forward to it. Pushes tentatively at it and is beaten all ends up
reached at that one. The hands went, the feet did not. Another swing and a miss
tried the same shot and was nowhere near in control of it - the faintest of bottom edges that trickles past the keeper and just beats fine leg to go for four
that looked a bit too quick for him, but it was the wring line. Down legside, and it just clips his waist and races away to fine leg. That was leg byes but he's given it runs
thwacked him on the thigh and he scampers through. That's one really is a leg bye
worked into the onside for one
spinning away from the left hander - Hasaranga in the covers moves sharply to his right to keep it to one

cleans him up! That might have been the carrom ball; well it certainly was a wicket ball. Cooper raced down the track and watched the ball slip underneath the bat and rattle into middle stump. Sri Lanka surging!
uses his feet to nurdle it into the onside to get off the mark

oh my, the carrom ball does the trick again! It looked like a long hop and Myburgh read it as such, shaping to heave it over midwicket. Instead it races through and clatters into middle again. Netherlands are reeling!

shortText: Theekshana to de Leede, no run
text: lovely bowling. That was the wrong'un, and de Leede played down the wrong line. Beats the outside edge
yorker, Ackermann was fully focused on digging it out
another yorker, brilliantly executed. Manages to get bat on it, just
bangs this into the surface, punched into the offside
freed his arms and attempted to clobber it past extra cover. Straight to mid-off
this time he connects as Kumara misses his line for once. It was a half-volley, and Ackermann set himself up outside leg and hammered it over his head into the sight screen
drags his length shorter, forcing him to defend

shortText: de Silva to de Leede, 1 leg bye
text: prances down the track, bat was nowhere near ball and it strikes him on the pad, but he's far enough out to survuve
brings out the broom, which you'd do too if you hadn't a clue where the ball was going. Makes good connection and clears the in-field on the legside
plumb - no point reviewing that, really, but he does!. Landed on middle, looked to have hit him on middle and was crashing into middle and leg. Pointless review, and they've lost it

shortText: de Silva to Edwards, no run
text: that spun back in and just clipped the inside edge to save him
gets the sweep out and connects, but it's fielded very well at backward square

shortText: de Silva to de Leede, OUT
text: that's gone, too! Spinning back in and clipped the pads, and the umpire raises the finger! Bas de Leede decides against reviewing, and that's half the side gone
chips it smartly into the onside, which was rather surprisingly vacant - I almost forgot we're still in the Powerplay! Picks up four
runs this to third man and puts van der Merwe on strike

shortText: Chameera to van der Merwe, no run
text: timed to the covers

shortText: Chameera to van der Merwe, no run
text: takes the pace off completely, just 113 kph. van der Merwe was clueless, and got beaten as he looked to drive

shortText: Chameera to van der Merwe, OUT
text: banged into the surface and absolutely reared up. Looked as if it took the top edge before the keeper caught sharply, and Sri Lanka review. The replay shows a faint nick, and that's it for van der Merwe - the Dutch are six down!
ends with a bouncer - and that ends a spectacular Powerplay

shortText: de Silva to Edwards, no run
text: another googly, Edwards brought out the reverse sweep but didn't get much bat on it
the conventional sweep this time, and deep square leg collects
that kept straight, nudged into the onside

shortText: de Silva to Seelaar, no run
text: took a big strike out on a ball tossed up and spinning in. Gets an inside edge on it

shortText: de Silva to Seelaar, no run
text: driven back to the bowler
that's plumb. Skids right through and there's no doubt about that. Netherlands lose their seventh
slashed at a wide one and missed
banged on the helmet, took his eye off the ball and paid the price - struck right on the badge. The physio's out there
full toss, driven to the offside
another bouncer at 147kph - this can't be fun for the lower order. Lucky it's missed everything
slower ball back of a length, just 106kph. Worked into the onside
rapped on the pads, a big appeal but it looked to be going down leg. They've reviewed, for the fun of it, apparently. Yeah, it's missing

shortText: de Silva to Edwards, no run
text: reverse sweep, first slip collects on the bounce

shortText: de Silva to Edwards, no run
text: tossed up, defended
shapes up for the sweep and gives it a nice whack. Square leg collects in the deep

shortText: de Silva to Klaassen, no run
text: defends tentatively down the ground. Still clueless about picking the delivery out of the hand, it seems

shortText: de Silva to Klaassen, no run
text: that was better read, and blocked

shortText: de Silva to Klaassen, no run
text: another tight over ends with a defensive prod into the offside

struck on the pads again and the umpire raises the finger. If he hasn't got an edge on that, it's plumb And he hasn't, so he's not going to survive this. Yep, ball tracking confirms this, and Netherlands lose another wicket and their last review
swing and a miss

little nick and that's the ninth wicket! Netherlands are one away from being bowled out inside the first 10!. tried to punch it into the offside, but it takes a feather off the outside edge and goes through to the keeper for a straightforward catch

shortText: Kumara to van Meekeren, no run
text: full on off, driven tentatively towards mid-off

shortText: Kumara to van Meekeren, no run
text: back of a length in the channel, has a swish at it with feet static, can't connect

yorker that tails into him, he thinks it's good and is appealing - it's given and Netherlands don't have a review left - so that means this is the end of the innings, at exactly the 10-over mark. For what it's worth, I think it was sliding down, but it's not likely to make much difference.
length ball on leg stump, can't connect with his flick but it rolls to short fine leg off the pad
full outside off on a fifth stump line, he was looking to drive through cover, gets it off the toe end through a vacant third slip region. Even luck not going Netherlands' way
and now a leading edge - but it falls safe. Good bowling, angling into him and straightens, he's looking to flick through midwicket, gets a leading edge that pops between cover and point
and swing again, into the right-hander this time, who plays all all over it and inside edges onto pad
length ball on off, steered to backward point
beaten outside off. Nice angle away from him in the channel and on a length, he ends up feeling for it and can't lay bat on ball
full on the toes, flicked to past short midwicket but mid-on fields to his left
length outside off, chops it towards mid-off - not timed well which allows them to sprint a quick single even as mid-off is swooping in

holes out to mid-off and that's some cheer for the Dutch. Skipped down the track and had a wild slog at this, gets a leading edge that swirls high and settles into the hands of the fielder comfortably.
fuller on off, punched to cover
length on the stumps, clipped through midwicket on the back foot
length ball on the stumps, defended into the offside
full and wide outside off, slashes it to third man, getting low and throwing a horizontal bat at it
fuller outside off, lashed with force to cover's left, who dives and stops it. Not well timed

shortText: van Meekeren to Perera, no run
text: that's some wheels by van Meekeren. Back of a length going across him in the channel, goes past too quick for him to connect with the attempted pull
gorgeous. Full on off, just leans into a punch that goes to the bowler's right but not close enough to mid-off, and runs all the way to the boundary

shortText: van Meekeren to Perera, no run
text: full on off, launches a booming drive at it, but it's not as straight this time and mid-off fields

shortText: van Meekeren to Perera, no run
text: good length on the stumps, tucks him up for room, punched to cover from close to body. They consider a single but there isn't one there.
another quick bouncer, but this time it's going too far over the batsman and it's a wide. Banged in short outside off, but it's gone well over Perera's head
full on the pads, whipped it with a wristy flourish and beats short fine leg to his right despite a dive by the fielder. No one back at th eboundary there so he'll collect four
full and into him, clipped towards mid-on
another good bouncer, on a fourth stump line, and he has to get his head out of the way in a hurry as it climbs on to him quickly

top edge falls safely. Interesting choice of shot with deep square leg back, but perhaps fortunately for him, he didn't middle this back of length ball coming into him, and only top-edged a pull over the in-field
length ball into him, tucked through midwicket

strays down the pads, he misses the flick. Could have flicked pad on the way to the keeper, who is appealing for it. No wide given. Netherlands have reviewed it. Might as well. I'll be vastly surprised if there is bat on it. Yep, no bat. But Ultra-Edge confirms it flicked the thigh pad. No harm in taking a review on a smidgen of a chance when you're defending only 44 I guess.
good length on leg stump, he misses the flick and it goes off thigh pad towards the gully region
short but on leg stump, and with fine leg in the circle, all he had to do was beat him. He pulls well enough to do that and collect an easy boundary
swish and a miss outside off. Length ball going across him, was looking to punch, balls sneaks through inside the line
back of a length outside off, chopped towards mid-off. Again, the timing's not great on this

that's another good short ball. He's copped a blow on the grille. He was too early into the pull, and that thudded right into the grille, think Glover took pace off that bouncer. Still got it to rise steeply enough. Physio out to attend to Asalanka.
good length nipping across him, he aims an adventurous slog across the line at it but bat only meets air

shortText: van Meekeren to Perera, no run
text: full outside off, drives it back to the bowler off the inside half, and the bowler fields on his follow through
slashed over cover. Given the room and the length to have a go at this, too short outside off and he cuts it powerfully
fuller length on the stumps, pushed to mid-off. They sprint a quick single

caught at mid-on. Asalanka hasn't looked fluent in his stay and he perishes with another slog across the line. Length ball on off, not really there for the pull, he goes for it anyway, gets a top edge that balloons up for an easy catch

another short ball but this time Kusal is expecting it, transfers weight back nicely and unleashes a ferocious pull that has enough power to make up for the lack of timing, sending it to the fence in front of square leg
fuller outside off, on the front foot now to lash this through mid-off for another boundary
full on the pads, flicked to midwicket
too far outside off and moving away further, he'll have to re-bowl that
back of a length on a fifth stump line, left alone
good length on off stump, punched between cover and point
another wide. Put some effort into that, dug in short, but it's too far outside off again
fuller outside off, drives crisply on the front foot but can't beat cover
good length on the pads, clipped to short midwicket
length on the pads, he gets inside the line this time and flicks to fine leg's right. They take two and scores are level
and that's it. Good ball by Klaasen, short and rising up to the throat, but dealt with well by Avishaka, who rises up on his toes and pats it down towards fine leg for the winning single.
length ball around off, defended towards backward point for a quick single
length ball around off, defended from the front foot. Straight towards point
a touch fuller and wider. O'Brien drives it towards cover
length ball on the stumps, turns it towards deep square leg
a touch fuller on the stumps, defended towards short midwicket
length ball around off, defended
length ball pitching way outside leg and shaping further down. A good diving take from the keeper
a length ball nipping back. O'Brien hops and gets an inside edge on to the pads
length ball on the stumps, flicked towards deep square leg
length ball around off, stays leg side of the ball and punches towards cover. A good stop there
a touch fuller on the stumps. Stirling backs away and slashes it through cover-point. Wasn't in full control but got enough bat on it
length ball outside off, Stirling dabs it towards short third man and sets off
short of length outside off, pulls it towards mid-on
length ball outside off. Stirling looks to swing it towards midwicket and misses
now that's some shot! A length ball around off, Stirling stands still and punches this over wide mid-on, holds the pose and it carries all the way
another length ball, much more bottom hand involved this time but the bat rotates in his hands. A single to midwicket
length outside off, pushes it towards short third man. Was looking for a single but no run there
banged short, and it comes way slower off the pitch. KOB pulls it to the right of deep midwicket for a couple

length ball, KOB backs away a bit but fails to middle it. In the air but falls just short of the cover fielder as he goes for the catch. Two more to the total. O'Brien is looking at the bottom of his bat
fuller on the stumps, Stirling backs away and lofts it over extra cover. A couple of bounces and over the boundary line
almost a repeat of the last ball with an even better connection. Backs away and lofts it over extra cover once more
fuller on the stumps, Stirling nudges it towards covers and sets off
fired in on middle and leg, tucked away towards deep square leg
fuller on the stumps, defended on the front foot
third four of the over. Fuller outside off, Stirling gets low and sweeps it behind square leg
length ball on the pads, tucked away behind square leg
length outside off, moves across and looks to slog it towards deep square leg. Fails to connect
fuller outside off, a cutter at 123kph. Stirling looks to go over wide mid-off but the bottom hand comes off. Gets two as it had enough on it to go over extra cover
short of length outside off, Stirling waits this time and punches it over covers for four
length ball on the stumps, defended on the leg side for a single
fuller outside off, clipped towards deep midwicket
fuller outside off, O'Brien just times it over extra cover and picks up a boundary
a length ball outside off, steered towards cover-point for a single
fuller outside off, opens the face of the bat to work it towards point. A quick single there
fuller outside off, in the slot for O'Brien who smashes it over mid-off. One-bounce four. Fifty comes up for Ireland
length ball outside off, defended towards covers for a single
length outside off, dabs it towards cover-point and set off
length ball outside off. Punched towards long-off
slower one, length outside off. Pushes it towards covers
length ball on the stumps, Stirling was moving towards the off side but manages to flick it towards square leg
length ball outside off, pushes it towards covers. A bit of a fumble there
fuller on the stumps, turns it towards wide long-on. Another single
fuller outside off, KOB stays back and forces it towards sweeper cover
length ball angling towards the pads. Backs away and pushes it towards long-off

Scholtz provides the breakthrough. Fuller on the stumps, Stirling came down the ground and aimed to clear long-on. Didn't get enough power behind that and Loftie-Eaton takes a good, sliding catch after running to his right
length ball on the stumps, flicked towards square leg
fuller on the stumps, pushed towards long-off to open the account
length ball on the pads, goes back and flicks it towards deep square leg
length outside off, stays beside the line of the ball and punches it towards deep point
length ball angling in. Punched back towards the bowler
length ball outside off, stays back and punches it towards sweeper cover
length outside off, punches it uppishly towards extra cover
KOB holes out. Fuller on the stumps, KOB picks it up and looks to go over the deep square leg fielder. But it didn't come from the middle of the bat. van Lingen makes no mistake
length ball outside off, punches it towards extra cover
length ball outside off, steered towards sweeper cover
length ball around off, punched down the ground

shortText: Ya France to Delany, no run
text: length ball on the stumps, defended back

shortText: Ya France to Delany, 1 leg bye
text: length ball on the pads, misses the flick and sets off for a leg-bye as the ball drops towards the short leg region. The keeper is quick to the ball and has a shy at the stumps. Balbirnie was nowhere in the picture but no direct hit there

shortText: Ya France to Balbirnie, no run
text: length ball outside off, pushes it towards covers

shortText: Ya France to Balbirnie, no run
text: length outside off, stays back and defends it towards covers
length ball sliding down the leg side. Called a wide

shortText: Ya France to Balbirnie, no run
text: an appeal for lbw but denied. A length ball around off, Balbirnie goes for a sweep but misses and is hit on the pads. Was the impact outside off? Namibia opt not to go for the review
good length ball on off, defended.
good length ball defended.
good length ball on off, defended back to Frylinck.
full and tailing down leg.
full on off, flicked gently into midwicket for a tight run.
good length ball back of a length on off, goes back to punch to long-on.
full on fourth stump, driven to wide long-off.
full on the legs, chipped in the air toward deep midwicket.
full and straying well down leg, Balbirnie with a tickle sweep gets it through fine leg for a boundary.
good length ball on the legs, flicked into midwicket.
full on fourth stump, driven to long-off.
good length ball on the legs, flicked into midwicket.
good length ball on fourth stump, flicked into midwicket.
back of a length on fifth stump, opens the face to guide this straight to short third man.
full on middle, flicked in the air over midwicket.
short outside off, cuts this off a bottom edge into the ground short of the keeper Green.
good length ball on middle, punched to extra cover.
full and wide, driven through the off side to the cover sweeper.
full and wide, driven square behind point and the sweeper has a long way to track it down before relaying in for two.
flighted full on the legs, Balbirnie breaks out his trademark sweep and clocks this high over backward square.
good length ball on the legs, flicked through square leg for one.
darted in on a good length on off, defended.
good length ball on leg stump, Delany backs away to access the off side but picks out cover.
good length ball on the legs, stays stationary this time to pull behind square.
fullish length on off, backs away and drives straight to cover.
good length ball on off, defended into midwicket.

what movement off the pitch! Wiese bowls a length ball on fifth stump that jags back sharply as an offcutter and pierces the gap between bat and pad on Delany's ill-fated slog and clangs into leg stump.
full on off stump, driven to long-on.
good length ball punched to extra cover.
good length ball on fourth stump, punches it to extra cover again.
offcutter on fifth stump, punches it to extra cover again.
119 kph yorker on off stump, jammed out through point.
full on the legs, flicked in the air through midwicket for a pair. Direct hit by Frylinck from the boundary at the striker's end but Balbirnie was in.
length ball follows Balbirnie backing away from leg and is beaten trying to pull.
good length ball on the legs, flicked to midwicket.
full on off, backs away again and drives back to Trumpelmann, who fires a very unnecessary throw at the stumps that hits and ricochets for an overthrow.
length ball on middle, pulls this high behind square and deep midwicket has to trek some distance to relay it in for a pair.

full and angled into the pads, Balbirnie misses a slog and a huge lbw shout is upheld but Balbirnie goes for the review. May have been sliding down leg, and also was hit quite high on the belt line while crouching down to slog. Ball-tracking shows three reds as the bounce on this pitch just isn't there today.
good length ball on seventh stump, goes to slap this and is beaten.
good length ball on fifth stump, slaps this through cover for one.
full on off stump, driven to long-off.
full on the legs, goes to slog and misses as the ball caroms to point off the pads.
slower ball at 107 kph lands full on middle, Campher way out in front of a slog and is castled! Ball skids into leg stump and Frylinck roars with a fist pump!
full on off stump, driven to long-on.
good length ball on fifth stump, guided into point.
full on the stumps, heaves this through backward square leg and Frylinck's dive at the rope is in vain. Crucial boundary for Ireland.

offcutter back of a length on fifth stump, Tector's timing is thrown off by this 114 kph delivery and an attempted back foot punch goes awry as Tector is cramped for room with the ball cutting in a touch. Thin edge goes through to Green.
good length ball on the pads, flicked into midwicket for one.
good length ball on off, slapped into the off side for one.
full and wide, searching for yorker, Rock squirts this out behind point for a pair.
length ball on off stump, Rock backs away and drags a heave to long-on.
good length on fourth stump, slapped toward long-off.

leg stump yorker sends Rock on his way. Pinpoint accuracy from Smit. Rock backed away a touch from leg stump trying to squirt this out through point but Rock can't squeeze this out and it ricochets off the toe of the bat into off stump.
good length ball follows Singh into his body and he pushes it out to long-on.
full and wide, driven in the air well short of long-off.
yorker on middle, jammed out past the bowler to long-off.
back of a length on middle, Simi charges and punches to extra cover.
good length very wide outside off, slapped into the covers for one.

How good from Wiese off his own bowling! Length ball offcutter on sixth stump, Singh charges but mistimes this into the ground into silly mid off. Wiese charges forward and collects on one bounce before underfunding point blank into the stumps with Adair well short trying to complete a single.
short on the stumps, pulled flat to deep midwicket.

chaos off the final ball! Singh tries to scoop this and mistimes it into short midwicket. Wiese fields off his own bowling and rather than just let the single go, flicks past the keeper for the first run and an overthrow. The ball is tracked down and relayed to the keeper. Both batters are at the same end as Singh hasn't kept going for the third. But Green rushes a horrendous throw that skids along the ground which Williams can't collect standing adjacent to the non-striker's stumps. It means Singh can come back for a third. Wiese is beside himself. How crucial will those last runs be?
a bit of movement in the air as Little goes full. A low, dipping full toss around off. Digs it out towards short midwicket
fuller around off, a bit of shape in. Punched towards extra cover
length outside off, punched towards point. An early and loud call of no from Williams
fuller and wider this time. Williams reaches out for it and slices it aerially towards third man
length outside off, Green fishes at it and gets beaten
fuller on the stumps, misses the flick and is hit on the pads. An appeal for lbw but denied. It looked close to me but Ireland decide not to review. Replay shows it was sliding down
length ball in the line of the stumps, defended
length ball around off, punched towards cover
length ball at the stumps, defended from the back foot
over the bowler's head. Down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and punches it through the line
fuller on the stumps, stays leg side of the ball and pushes it towards mid-off
length ball around off, pushed towards cover-point where Tector makes a diving stop to prevent the single
length ball outside off, looks to punch but is a bit late on it. The ball takes the inner edge and bounces towards the keeper
fuller but sliding down the leg side. Green cannot connect the flick
length ball around off, tucked away towards midwicket and they sprint back for the second
length ball around off, mistimes the punch back towards the bowler
length ball around off, defended back towards the bowler
almost a yorker. Digs it out towards mid-on and sets off
another wide. A touch shorter but angling down the leg side. Green attempts the pull but no connection
short of length on the pads, tucked away towards midwicket
fuller outside off, enough room to free the arms and Williams smashes it over covers
length outside off, punched towards extra cover where Stirling makes a diving stop to his right
this time he finds the gap. A length ball outside off, backs away just a touch and punches it to the right of the cover fielder
length outside off, uses his feet and cuts it past cover
length outside off, taps it towards cover-point
length ball on the pads, flicked towards square leg
a slower one but a full toss. Green misses out and hits it towards point
length ball on the pads, flicked behind square leg for a couple
length ball around off, defended towards cover-point
length ball around off, defended towards mid-off
short of length outside off, pulls it down but Balbirnie dives to his left at short midwicket to make the stop
length ball on the pads, flicked towards deep-backward square leg for another couple of runs in that region

an excellent catch by O'Brien. It was full around off, in the slot for Williams and went after it. He hit it hard but didn't get the elevation to clear mid-on. O'Brien timed his jump perfectly and took it overhead with both hands
fuller around off, comes forward and defends it towards cover
length ball around off, punched towards mid-on
length ball in the line of the stumps, defended on the leg side
fuller outside off, driven towards mid-off
fuller on the pads, clipped towards deep midwicket. A bit of a confusion in the middle but all safe in the end as Green puts in the dive to make it
length ball on the pads, flicked towards deep-backward square leg
length ball outside off, looks to punch off the back foot. Gets an under edge on to the pads

an appeal for lbw but the umpire is unmoved. A touch fuller on the stumps, Erasmus looks to push at it but is beaten. The height wasn't an issue, and replay shows it would have been out on review. Adair is holding his side
a length ball on the stumps, punched towards midwicket
length outside off, Green pushes at it, gets a thick outside edge through the vacant slip area. A welcome boundary for Namibia
length ball outside off, punched towards extra cover

shortText: Simi Singh to Erasmus, no run
text: fuller around off, pushes it back towards the bowler
fuller outside off, hits it along the ground towards long-on

shortText: Simi Singh to Green, no run
text: pitched up once again. Green goes hard at it but cannot beat extra cover
length outside off, cuts it towards deep point

shortText: Simi Singh to Erasmus, no run
text: fuller outside off, drives it towards cover-point

shortText: Simi Singh to Erasmus, no run
text: length ball outside off, punched down the ground but Simi moves across to make the stop
length ball around off, punched towards long-off
fuller around off, drives it towards extra cover
length outside off, uses his feet and punches it towards sweeper cover
a length ball outside off, pulls it towards deep midwicket for a couple
a length ball, room outside off, cuts it towards deep cover
length outside off, punched square of the wicket on the off side
down the track but gets too close to the ball. Works it towards deep square leg and dives back to complete the second run
use of feet once again. This time he pushes it towards long-on. Only a single
down the track and hits it to the right of the bowler for one more
length ball outside off, use of feet once more to work it in front of square leg. Two more to the total
once again comes down the track and pushes it towards midwicket. Simi Singh fields himself and is quick enough to prevent the second run

shortText: Simi Singh to Green, no run
text: fuller around off, hits it to the right of Simi who makes a tumbling stop
length ball angling down. Goes for the sweep but misses. Will have to be contend with a wide
good length ball on middle, comes down and flicks through wide long-on for a long single.
full on the legs, clipped into midwicket for one.
Back of a length on fifth stump, pulled flat to deep midwicket and fielded on a bounce.
length ball on off stump, pulled tamely to deep midwicket for one.
good length ball on off, guided to backward point.
good length ball on fifth stump, slapped behind point for one.

shortText: Simi Singh to Erasmus, no run
text: tries to reverse paddle a full ball on fifth stump but misses.
full on the stumps, flicked to deep midwicket into a gap for a well-run pair.
uses his feet to flick a good length ball off fourth stump through wide long-on but Campher charges well to deny the second.
flighted full on fifth stump, sweeps and misses, fumble by Rock to allow a bye.
full on the legs, chipped in the air over midwicket in the ring and they run another tight pair.
full on fifth stump, driven to long-off for one.
crucial boundary by the captain! Short and wide, cuts hard and pierces the gap between backward point and deep third man who is unable to cut it off at the rope.
full into the legs, flicked through midwicket for one.
yorker on middle and leg, jammed out to Little.
full on fourth stump, driven to long-on.
good length ball defended back to Little.
classy shot! Back of a length ball on fourth stump, uses the pace and guides this between short third man and backward point, timed to perfection to the rope.
Green charges first ball and drives a full and wide ball over extra cover, stops short of the rope and relayed back in for a pair.

Kevin O'Brien with a carbon copy effort at mid-off. Identical catch he took leaping in the Powerplay to dismiss Williams as he tag teams again with Campher.  Fullish length, Green tries to clear O'Brien on the ring but mistimes the drive and it flutters up for O'Brien to backpedal and take another smart catch reaching high above his head.
good length ball punched back down the pitch and bounces over Campher to mid-off for one.
good length ball punched straight for one.

missed runout! back of a length and they try to tap and run into backward point. Tector charges and underhands from 10 yards and Wiese would've been out by three inches if it hit but it goes just wide.
good length ball guided away through the ring more safely this time for a single.
back of a length ball on fifth stump pulled through deep midwicket for a pair.

huge blow! From a huge man! Length ball on fifth stump heaved high to wide long-on. KOB leaps up trying to slap this back in but can't pull off his third catch of the day. He got fingertips to it in the end and landed on the rope regardless as it is parried over the rope.
bang bang! The pendulum swings fully Namibia's way! Another length ball swatted high and deep onto the Industrial Road over square leg. Towering blow!
good length ball chopped behind point for one.

good length ball on fourth stump squirts between bat and pad and brushes off stump, but the bails won't come off! Balbirnie is calling for a DRS review for caught behind but it looks to have clearly missed the bat and shaved off stump. Clear daylight between bat and pad on all replays. Massive spike on UItraedge as the ball passes the stumps at 128 kph. But the bails stayed on.
good length ball outside off, guided behind point for one.
full on the legs, flicks through midwicket for one.
slower ball lands full on fifth stump, driven to the cover sweeper.
back of a length on fourth stump, guided to short third man for one.
full on the legs, driven to long-on.
full on the legs, misses a flick, ricochets off the pads behind square for an extra.
goes for slower wide yorker, doesn't get it full enough and it's driven high over extra cover for a pair.
back of a length on sixth stump at 126 kph, Erasmus swats at this and misses.
back of a length on off stump, goes back to flick into midwicket for one.
full on fifth stump, big heave but skittles along the turf for one through midwicket.
short on the body, pulls this to deep backward square for one.
goes for wide yorker, winds up as a low full toss sliced to deep third man for one.
yorker on fifth stump, guided out to deep third man.
full on middle, chips this over mid-off for a pair after a fumble by KOB coming in off the rope trying to deny the second.

ohhhhhh how elegant! Class of Erasmus! Skips down the track to drive a full ball high over Singh down the ground and holds the pose with a high elbow. Julian Baard, Stephan's dad, is dancing in the crowd on camera!
good length ball on the stumps, punches through cover for one.

shortText: Simi Singh to Wiese, no run
text: charges a leg break from Simi darted into the legs, punched back to Simi.
darts this down leg. Ireland crumbling now.
short and slices another leg break behind point to short third man for one.
fullish length on the legs, chipped inside out over cover.

he scored a 50 against Ireland in a losing effort at the Qualifier two years ago, but now Erasmus has scored a 50 on the cusp of what will be Namibia's most famous win! And brings it up in style with a lofted extra cover drive! His father Francois is on his feet in the stands clapping with pride!
full on off, driven to long-off.

Namibia have defeated a Test nation to advance into the Super 12 stage of the T20 World Cup! Full and wide Wiese punches this high over cover. The fielder out there was cheating in off the rope looking to cut off two and it sails over him to the rope on one bounce. Wiese pumps his fists! Erasmus looks like he might be choking up right now! What a moment!
swing from the outset, and a hard-handed jab takes a thick outside edge down to third man. Probing opening

very full, clipped to mid-on... and a chaotic run-out! Oh my word, it was so chaotic the cameras couldn't keep up. An automatic sprint to the far end, Ilyas didn't respond at all, and Cross had the luxury of strolling to the stumps to flick off the bails. Calamity! The main man is gone without scoring!
back of a length, thuds the pad and deflects to the leg side

shortText: Wheal to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: shaping into the pads, worked with the angle to the leg side
flicked dismissively high off the pads! That's a connection and a half, deep in the crease, whipping with the angle, high and mighty over fine leg!

shortText: Wheal to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: good finish, tight line and length, bending in to off stump and blocked back down the pitch. An all-action first over!
wicket-to-wicket line, thumps the pad, half an appeal but probably going over leg stump
nudged off the legs, backward of square, into the gap
good probing full length, on off stump and pushed back up the pitch
pushed back through the line

shortText: Davey to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: eased into the on-side, gliding through the stroke, Davey keeping it full and true to the right-hander
on the back foot, pressed down to backward point

shortText: Sharif to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: full length, a slapped drive through the line, straight into the covers
tight line on off stump, angled bat in response, out to point
solid line and length, good use of the facilities so far from Scotland's seamers
full length, finds a bit of nip off the seam, back into the inner thigh, very tight lines

hacked off a good length, straight to mid-off! That's reward for disciplined bowling! Prajapati felt obliged to take it on, inject some urgency in this Powerplay, but his wild swing took the splice for a simple lob to Munsey. Scotland are rampant at the moment!
angled bat, solid block, nudged out to the leg side
banged into the deck, back of a length, tucked off the hips to square leg
flicked to the leg side, as Wheal probes on a middle-stump line

shortText: Wheal to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: full length, clipped to the on-side, short midwicket intercepts

shortText: Wheal to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: lovely line and length, Scotland doing nothing more complicated than hitting the pitch with an upright seam at the moment. It's working...

shortText: Wheal to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: right up to the toes, dug out with a firm push through the line, Wheal leaps in his followthrough and parries to mid-on
full length once more, inviting the drive, but it's just a single to mid-on. Four overs gone, and Oman are looking a bit stuck
leg-sided, and that's a rare offering to the Oman cause. Just a little tickle off the pads, very fine and away to the rope

shortText: Davey to Aqib Ilyas, 1 leg bye
text: another one bending into the pads, but a fatter deflection this time, to the man at short fine leg
angled bat, poked to the on-side, sharp single
ping! Davey strays into the toes again, and this time Ilyas lifts his back leg for extra leverage, as he flicks high and mighty over backward square!

shortText: Davey to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: hides the ball outside off this time, as Ilyas swings with flat feet and can't connect
chopped into the covers, another single to end a better over for Oman

shortText: Sharif to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: tight line, full length, opens the face on the back foot to push to point

shortText: Sharif to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: swivels into a pull, can't connect properly

shortText: Sharif to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: attempted slap, backing away, can't connect. Sharif is hitting a good length here
wider line, dabbed through backward point, beats the close fielder as third man sweeps round to tidy up
Rock the Kasbah! Sharif don't like it... but that's a fine strike, planting the front foot and smoking firmly through long-off

shortText: Sharif to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: outside off, a play and a miss, that's the Powerplay done, and it's still advantage Scotland... but there's a regroup taking place.
goes inside out, towards sweeper cover

shortText: Watt to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: fired in a touch quicker, and he works it towards short midwicket

shortText: Watt to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: flat again, into him from wide of the crease, pushed towards the man at short mid-wicket yet again
fuller, outside off, and he drives this towards long-off

shortText: Watt to Mohammad Nadeem, no run
text: length, around off, and driven towards cover-point
no short midwicket for Nadeem, and he can ease a fullish ball towards wide long-on
short in length, punched away towards deep midwicket
fuller, driven towards extra cover. A diving effort, but just unable to stop it

shortText: Greaves to Mohammad Nadeem, no run
text: length, angles in. He looks to cut it away, but misses. Not far from the top of off!
flatter, around off, and whipped away towards deep midwicket
fuller, and driven towards long-on with the incoming slant

shortText: Greaves to Mohammad Nadeem, no run
text: length, around off, and driven back towards the bowler

shortText: Watt to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: bowled from way behind the popping crease. Driven towards cover

wide of the crease, swept in the air! Just makes it to the long leg boundary, with short fine leg and deep backward square leg converging on it. Greaves in fact, just running past it as it bounces past him

shortText: Watt to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: driven firmly down the wicket to the bowler's left, and he stops it on his followthrough

just beyond short fine leg's reach! Flat again, and down the leg side. He looks for the sweep, but gets the toe end. It scoops up, but just goes behind Wheal at short fine. He puts in a jump, but doesn't time it well enough

shortText: Watt to Mohammad Nadeem, no run
text: driven back to the bowler
full toss, driven to long-off
angled towards the pads, and worked away towards deep square leg

shortText: Leask to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: flat, and he plays the paddle sweep. Straight to short fine
floated around off, and he slices this away as he looks to clear long-off. Easy catch for Munsey, and that's the wicket of the well-set Ilyas! Relentless pressure from the spinners pays off

shortText: Leask to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: oh, some turn across his blade! Just on a length around off, and Maqsood doesn't help by staying rooted inside the crease, and it goes past the outside edge
fuller, around the pads, worked away towards deep square leg
tossed up, outside off, and he drives this towards sweeper cover
shot! Wheal puts one in Nadeem's wheelhouse, on a length just around off, and he has absolutely whacked it over mid-wicket. Emphatic!
length, around off, and he defends this time towards mid-wicket. Easy single
length, and dispatched! Stand and deliver from Maqsood. Doesn't have long-off in place, and he can easily loft this over the head of mid-off
slower ball, and he works it off his pads to the right of short fine

shortText: Wheal to Mohammad Nadeem, no run
text: length, around off, and he defends this back down the pitch
short, into his body, and he works it off his hips towards mid-wicket. They choose to take a comfortable single
worked towards deep square leg with the angle into the pads

shortText: Leask to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: length, goes back to cut, but cannot beat backward point

shortText: Leask to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: fullish, around the pads. Off his pad as he looks to flick this. Wants a single, but Cross is very quick to get across to it. In the end, a slightly panicky attempt to get home
worked off the edge, and just clears short third! Wheal puts in a jump, but it just clears his fingertips. Some chances do need to be taken at this stage

shortText: Leask to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: full, flat, and driven back to the left of the bowler
driven down the ground to long-off
flat, around the pads, and worked away towards deep square leg
clears cow corner easily! Just a bit more flight this time from Watt, and Nadeem just clears his front leg and swings freely. Right off the middle of the bat

gone this time! Nadeem goes for a drive inside out, but fails to keep it down. Great bowling by Watt. The easier option would have been to bowl this flat, but he gave it a bit of flight and also kept it outside off. Nadeem has taken the bait, but failed to clear cover. That ball was travelling quick, though, making the catch all the more remarkable. Berrington making it look ridiculously easy.
length, around off, and Goud guides this towards deep point. Wants two, but they settle for the single
fuller, around off, and he works it off his pads. Very elegant and wristy batter, the Oman captain

shortText: Watt to Sandeep Goud, no run
text: Watt goes wide of the crease. Full. Driven back towards the bowler

shortText: Greaves to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: length, around off, and he backs away looking to go inside out. Misses out on contact
cut away to the left of point. Quick single taken

shortText: Greaves to Sandeep Goud, no run
text: length, around off, angles back in, and he defends back down the wicket
Goud down the wicket, and works it away towards midwicket with the angle into him

shortText: Greaves to Sandeep Goud, no run
text: good response. Full, just outside off, and he drives it to backward point

shortText: Greaves to Zeeshan Maqsood, 1 no ball
text: it's a full toss, and he has spanked this right down deep square leg's throat. They are checking for height, though! Greaves has a sheepish expression straight away. I think he realises this will be a no-ball! And that's the call, indeed. Above waist height, because Maqsood was upright in his crease. And a free hit to boot!
length, around off, and he plays the late cut. It speeds away, but short third is quick to scamper across and reel this back in. Great cricket all around

slower ball, and skewed straight up. Mid off wants to take it, but fails to get anywhere near it. That's Coetzer, the captain! May have lost it in the lights. Right off the toe-end, and got a fair amount of height. He recovered well enough to have a shy at the stumps, and that would also have accounted for Maqsood!
flicked away with a little shuffle across the stumps. Good shot, but just one run
short, and he guides this past point and short third. Great shot! Oman scrapping and fighting to pile up some valuable runs at the moment

shortText: Sharif to Zeeshan Maqsood, 1 leg bye
text: length, around leg stump, and he works it away towards square leg

whipped off his feet, but straight towards deep backward square leg! It's a whippy, wristy shot that all Oman batters appear to play, but they do often play it in the air. Then it becomes a matter of chance. If there's a fielder stationed there, they don't get many second chances, do they? Another vital wicket, though you feel this is where Maqsood will make the difference. As could the extra batter they have played today
length, around off, and he drives this towards deep point

shortText: Leask to Naseem Khushi, no run
text: fuller, around leg, and he sweeps. Cannot get it past short fine leg
length, towards deep point
full, outside off, and he drives this towards long-off

swings across the line, and this has gone quite high. MacLeod runs in from mid-wicket, and takes a comfortable catch. You have to question the shot, though. Wild hoick to one that was floated outside off!

shortText: Leask to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: length, cut away, but straight to point
driven firmly through the off side. Diving stop from Sharif going across from extra cover, and stops the boundary
fullish, worked towards point. They scamper a quick single. Berrington is so quick to get to the ball, and under-arm it at the striker's end. He would have been home, though
fuller, around the pads, worked away towards deep square leg

shortText: Watt to Suraj Kumar, no run
text: full, around off, and he looks to work it away towards short third. Misses
length, goes across the line. Uppish, but short of deep mid-wicket
full, around the pads, and worked towards deep mid-wicket
fullish, played inside out towards sweeper cover
slow, in to the pitch, and he comes jumping out to thrash this. Ends up dragging it towards square leg
full, around off, and he slaps this away towards deep point

shortText: Davey to Suraj Kumar, no run
text: full, around off, and he drives this firmly, but straight to point. There was no protection behind him, which will annoy Suraj. Could have picked up runs if he had just placed it past the man there
