short, and he takes on the short ball. Off the edge, and Wheal at fine leg goes low to his left to pick this up. Great execution from Davey. A clever short ball which cramps him for room and just hones in on his helmet badge. Tough to get enough control when you take that on.
fullish, driven towards the bowler

shortText: Davey to Fayyaz Butt, no run
text: slower ball, outside off, goes away off the seam. Wild heave, and a miss
slow, into the pitch, and he looks to swing across the line. Bunted on the bounce towards midwicket
fullish, driven towards long-off
length, and he has just carted this over deep square leg. Deep into the stands! This man has some strong forearms, because he has absolutely muscled this one out of sight!
looks for the yorker, and ends up bowling a low full toss. Whipped away. Goes on the bounce to MacLeod at deep midwicket
'catch it' is the call...and just short of short fine leg! Yorker outside off, and Butt was looking for the dink over the man at short fine. Got the top edge, but not with any pace

shortText: Sharif to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: full, angles across him. Maqsood looks to spank it through point, but fails to make contact
fuller length, just outside off, and he is able to squirt it away towards deep midwicket

shortText: Davey to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: Maqsood looks to go for the reverse lap, but that's a good length ball just angling across him. Fails to make contact with this

bashed over extra cover, but Scotland have pulled off another good catch rather well! Davey goes length, and wide of off, and Maqsood gets a good bit of wood on this. It looks like it's headed for six, but MacLeod runs across from wide long-off, and then plucks it off the air just inside the ropes. Perfectly timed jump and then cushions his landing easily too. That's a big wicket for this final over!

shortText: Davey to Bilal Khan, 1 run, OUT
text: yorker, driven back firmly. MacLeod gets across from long-off, and he is run out as he looks for the second, that never was! Bilal ran immediately after touching down, and then had to cut his idea short, but by then it was too late. A good bit of fielding, as MacLeod sent it in immediately
another near-catch, but this has gone for four! Back of the hand slower ball, and short into the deck. He flogs it across the line, and Leask dives in from deep midwicket, but just sneaks under him

full, outside off, and struck straight at cover-point! The shot was there for the taking, but he fails to keep it down, and it's a sharp catch, as Oman are bowled out off the last ball of this innings

shortText: Bilal Khan to Munsey, no run
text: clobbered into the off side, full length on off stump, and straight at mid-off
fired down the leg side, and that's a freebie to open Scotland's account. A fumble from the keeper too. Nerves...

shortText: Bilal Khan to Munsey, no run
text: cuffed into the covers, on off stump again
panned off the front foot, firm strike, but a superb sprawling stop from the captain in the covers to cut off a certain four

shortText: Bilal Khan to Coetzer, no run
text: kneels into an energetic flog into the off side, not timed but the intent is plain

shortText: Bilal Khan to Coetzer, no run
text: oof, that's a beauty! Left-arm over, tight line on off stump, shaping across the right hander, and climbing off the seam. You do well to nick those
curling in on off stump, good yorker length, open face out to point. A tight first over after that wide
hits the deck hard, Coetzer swings into a cramped pull out through midwicket

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Coetzer, no run
text: yeehar! A flat-footed hack, outside off, swinging away, no contact despite the grand intentions
banged in short again, angled down the leg side, pulled without timing through square leg
angled into the legs, Munsey works this one behind square for the single
wide yorker, slammed out through the off-side, but that's a steepling leading edge, and caught at point. But it doesn't count
wild wide! Can't get close to that, outside off, the Free Hit still stands

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Coetzer, (no ball) 1 run
text: pitched right up to the blockhole and Coetzer gets good bat through the ball, as Munsey ducks at the non-striker's end before jogging the single

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Coetzer, no run
text: thuds into the top half of the bat, there's pressure everywhere
anchored in the crease, cuffs a firm cut through point! That sat up outside off stump, begging to be biffed

shortText: Bilal Khan to Munsey, no run
text: fuller length, dug out on off stump

shortText: Bilal Khan to Munsey, no run
text: on the back foot, punched back through the line of the ball

shortText: Bilal Khan to Munsey, no run
text: sharp bouncer, Munsey takes evasive action, just a reminder that he's got some wheels
full length, shaping away on off stump, a scuffed hack to the on-side, not quite to the pitch of the ball, but another single to the cause. Singles are pretty much all Scotland need at the moment
... but boundaries help no end! Slammed on the up, with mid-off up in the ring, seizing on the full length, and climbing through the line, through long-off
on the back foot, and clattered out through point. That was too short, too wide, and too easily paced. Biffed

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Munsey, no run
text: better line and length, tighter and fuller

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Munsey, no run
text: solidly into line to defend to the off side
reverse sweep! Exceptionally played, and selected, kneeling to the off-stump delivery, and pumped through backward point

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Munsey, no run
text: full length, and blocked back down the pitch

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Munsey, no run
text: pressed off the back foot, to the on-side, the bowler leaps across his crease to gather
opens the face on the full length, clouted hard into the covers, Jatinder intercepts
on the back foot, and that's sublime! Up on the toes, it wasn't outrageously short, but Munsey was so quickly into position, for a spanking drive through the covers

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Munsey, no run
text: fenced into the off side, that's a tighter line to the left-hander, who blocks with high hands on the back foot

Banged in short, and hoisted straight to backward square! Munsey was lured into the pull, tried to roll his wrists over the shot, but actually timed it too well, it travelled straight to Jatinder, metres in from the rope, and Scotland's serene start is dented

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Coetzer, no run
text: full length, firm push back through the line

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Coetzer, no run
text: sharp pace to finish the over! Zips over the top of the stumps, and the attempted pull, as the keeper leaps to gather. Lively times!
round the wicket, speared in towards leg on a full length, pressed to the on-side
opens the stance and clears the front leg for a biff up and over the ring, doesn't time it but clears the infield easily enough. Useful runs
attempted pull down the leg side
gives himself room as Zeeshan follows him into the legs, and pumped out to wide long-on with a flowing pull

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Cross, no run
text: darted into the leg stump, met with a vertical bat and a push to mid-on
swept, behind square for the single.
Heaved high over the covers! That's vast, bouncing off the canopy at wide long-on, as Coetzer backs away to leg to free his arms for a lusty smite!

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Cross, no run
text: angled bat, open face, out to backward point
nudged behind square with a cross-batted paddle, up on the toes to control the stroke
flashed over the covers, inside-out once more, but that slows up after pitching as two fielders converge in the deep
biffed into the hospitality stand! A swing across the line, Butt is too short and too wide, and that's dismissively high and handsome!

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Coetzer, no run
text: clawed out to the leg side, fuller length outside off
flogged with rampant power, hard through extra cover! Coetzer is not messing around now... full pedal-to-metal stuff as he greets more width with another claymore-like slash to the rope
loops up and bites on pitching, Cross pokes with hard hands as the ball pops into the off side

shortText: Khawar Ali to Coetzer, no run
text: too short and wide, and that is clobbered straight at short cover. A let-off
tighter line, back of a length, pulled round the corner to square leg
short, easy pickings on that length, another greedy smash across the line to deep midwicket
up on the toes, pushed to deep cover with flowing lines in the stroke. Compact
punched off the back foot to the on-side. Five singles is just the ticket as Scotland enter cruise control
on the back foot, tight lines, pushed to mid-on with a high elbow
full toss, on the legs, that's not going to crank up any pressure, as Coetzer walks inside the line for a flick to backward square
much better ball, line and length, and cutting in off the seam, Cross watches it carefully and defends to the leg side

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Coetzer, no run
text: big nip off the seam! That saws the batter in half as the keeper goes up for the catch... but there's no inside-edge, all seam movement

clattered into the stands once more! This is how to march into the main draw! A fractional error in length, and Coetzer's weight is already on the back foot, gagging to unleash those forearms, high over midwicket!

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Coetzer, no run
text: punched off the front foot, better line and length. But it's another nine runs off the over, and the requirement is being whittled down at a steady rate

shortText: Khawar Ali to Cross, no run
text: good pace through the air, biting on off stump, and played into the off side with an angled bat
swept firmly, in front of square. Nadeem intercepts in the deep to cut off the second
flogged hard into the off side, waiting for the ball to arrive in his slot, and gathered at wide long-off

shortText: Khawar Ali to Cross, no run
text: pressing forward, head over the ball
attempted sweep, a bit muffed, but gets the single behind square

bowled him! Right on the stroke of drinks, Coetzer has played round a full one, was maybe playing for turn, but that skidded on, past the inside edge, into the pads, and onto the stumps. A big wicket at an important time for Oman...
length, worked with the turn towards deep square leg

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Berrington, no run
text: length, turns across him from around off. Punched back to the bowler

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Berrington, no run
text: a little shorter in length, tossed up. Driven to cover
short again, and he can hang back and punch this to long-off

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Cross, no run
text: full, wide, and he looks to drive
length, punched out towards deep cover
sweeps from outside off, and gets it down to deep backward square leg

shortText: Khawar Ali to Berrington, no run
text: tossed up, and didn't really get up. Outside off. Berrington goes for the swat through covers, but it slips under his bat
quicker, straighter, and he goes off the inside of his bat towards square leg. Quick single pinched in the process

shortText: Khawar Ali to Cross, no run
text: tossed up, driven to cover

shortText: Khawar Ali to Cross, no run
text: that could be close! Not given leg before, but they go for the review. Cross went for the sweep, but played all around it. Certainly did pitch in line, and might even have been on target. The only questions could be about whether it got a bit of glove along the way, or was too high. Replays confirm the same. It misses the gloves, but it was going over the bails.
tossed up, and he shuffles across to sweep hard towards deep backward square. Some quick running fetches them two
looks for the cut. Goes in the air, and just beyond Ilyas' reach at point. He looks to dive backwards, raising his right arm, but it has just cleared him!
driven towards long-on
length, around off, dragged towards midwicket

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Cross, no run
text: length, around off, and flogged away towards cover. A diving stop there
sweeps from outside off, gets it towards deep square

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Berrington, no run
text: fullish, into the blockhole, and played back to the right of Maqsood
goes for the sweep again. Gets it away towards short fine. Appeal for leg before, but he must have got an under edge

shortText: Khawar Ali to Berrington, no run
text: tries to skip down the wicket, and he fires it in quicker. Fails to connect with an attempted sweep
Berrington clears his front leg this time, and takes it on the half-volley. Flogged straight down the ground! At 99m, the biggest six of the match!
fuller, around leg, and he drives this to long-off
short, into his body, and he hangs back to drag this over short midwicket. Just a single, with a sweeper in the deep

straight down the ground, for SIX MORE! What a shot to bring up the 100. Just backed away a bit towards leg side to open up the off side. Khawar responded with a fullish ball. Just allowed him enough room to get under it, and slap it over long-off, to the right of the man stationed there
drag down, around off, and he can drive it towards deep point
length, driven firmly towards deep cover

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Cross, no run
text: cuts this away but cannot beat point
short, and he rocks back to slap this across the line. Man from deep midwicket gets around to his left and puts in a good dive to keep them down to just the two
full, driven towards long-off
length, driven towards long-on
Bilal comes round the wicket. Short, just outside off, and he pulls it away towards deep square leg

shortText: Bilal Khan to Cross, no run
text: fuller, around off, and he drives towards cover
short, and he cuts this to point. A misfield will allow them a single

shortText: Bilal Khan to Berrington, no run
text: full, outside off, driven to mid-off

shortText: Bilal Khan to Berrington, no run
text: slower ball, back of a length. Cuts away with the angle across the batter, who looks to pull, but misses
banged in short, and he moves away looking to flick this over the keeper. Called a wide, in fact. Too short, in effect

shortText: Bilal Khan to Berrington, no run
text: full, wide of off, and he fails to get this away again. Some tidy bowling, but too little, too late. Surely?

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Cross, no run
text: length, comes into him, and he defends it back towards the bowler
length, angles into him, and he works it towards deep midwicket
low full toss, on the pads, and he dinks it towards deep midwicket
length, angles in, and he works it away towards deep square leg
back of a length, and he takes it from middle and leg, and deposits it between midwicket and long-on. Powerful blow, with loads of bottom hand on that

there's the six they need! It's a length ball, and he seems to have pre-meditated a dismissive swat over midwicket. Superb exclamation mark to what has already been a fruitful campaign for the Scotsmen!

shortText: Morea to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: edge! Did it carry? In the channel on fourth stump on a good length, prods at this flat-footed and the ball doesn't carry behind to Doriga, barely short hops him.

leg stump half-volley and he picks out one of the two men outside the ring during the Powerplay! Sese Bas is the man at deep square leg. Naim is too loose with the flick chipping this in the air to the leg side. Bas came charging in initially before having to steady himself and backpedal to take a theatrical catch tumbling backward 10 yards inside the rope. But he held on and that's all that matters.
Liton walks down the wicket first ball and pokes at a good length ball on fourth stump, guiding it wide of short third man.

shortText: Morea to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full on sixth stump, drives hard at this and an inside edge is dragged past leg stump just wide of short fine leg.
full on the legs swinging in, clipped through midwicket for one.

shortText: Morea to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: full on middle and off, clipped to midwicket.

shortText: Ravu to Liton Das, no run
text: back of a length on off, defended into the off side.
back of a length on middle, goes back to flick wide of midwicket for one.

shortText: Ravu to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: short and wide, slaps this high over backward point and cut off at deep third man for one.
back of a length on fourth stump, guided with soft hands behind point for one.

shortText: Ravu to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: full and driven back to Ravu.

shortText: Ravu to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: bouncer clears Shakib on the attempted hook.
full on fifth stump, pushed wide of mid-off for one.

shortText: Soper to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: short and wide, slaps this to backward point.

shortText: Soper to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: fullish length ball on off, driven through mid-on for one.

shortText: Soper to Liton Das, no run
text: back of a length on fifth stump, pushed back to Soper.
Audacious by Liton! Full on fifth stump, shuffles across and slog sweeps this over fine leg and sails over the rope.
good length ball on the hips, flicks this to deep fine leg for one.
good length ball on fourth stump, guided with soft hands behind point for one.

shortText: Ravu to Shakib Al Hasan, SIX
text: fullish length ball in the slot on fourth stump, Shakib winds up and cranks this high over long-on.

shortText: Ravu to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full on off stump, pushed firmly to mid-off for one.
good length ball on fourth stump, punches this square to backward point for what should be a dot. But Amini makes a rare miscue charging in and it goes under his hands and to the rope.
bouncer is too short to play, wide signaled from square leg.
full outside off, driven to extra cover, another fumble, this time by Hiri Hiri allows a single.

shortText: Ravu to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: short on fourth stump, Shakib plays it very late to deep third man.

shortText: Ravu to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 wide
text: good length ball but tailing down leg and beyond Shakib's reach off the hips. Wide called.

shortText: Morea to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full toss on the hips, slapped flat to deep square leg for one.
short and wide, slaps this high over cover for a long single.

shortText: Morea to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: fullish length outside off, guided into the covers for one.

shortText: Morea to Liton Das, no run
text: fullish length slower ball on fourth stump, Shakib way out in front pushing hard at this and is beaten between bat and pad.
fullish length ball outside off, pushed through mid-off for one.
slower ball again full and wide outside off, left alone.

shortText: Morea to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: slower ball lands on a fullish length on fifth stump, shoveled into the covers for one.

shortText: Bau to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: flighted full on the legs, goes back to flick through midwicket.
full on fifth stump, shuffles across and flicks to long-on, Ravu charges in and slides past the ball to open the door for a second run.

shortText: Bau to Liton Das, no run
text: flighted full on fourth stump, shuffles across to sweep and misses, big lbw shout denied. Hit well outside off stump. But Assad Vala has called for a review in desperation. Sure enough, ball-tracking shows impact comfortably outside off stump. Didn't even look like the ball was turning enough to hit off stump.
good length ball on fifth stump, goes back to flick into midwicket and weighted perfectly for a pair.
full on the legs, flicked into midwicket for another double.
good length ball on off stump, goes back and flicks into midwicket.
good length ball on the legs, flicked behind square for a long single.

shortText: Soper to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: fullish length on middle, punched back to Soper.

shortText: Soper to Shakib Al Hasan, 2 runs
text: good length ball on middle, flicks this high over midwicket for one.

shortText: Soper to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: charges Soper for a heave and misses.

shortText: Soper to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: short outside off, chops this into the off side ring.
short on fifth stump, pulls this flat to deep midwicket.

flighted full on fifth stump, shuffles across for a slog sweep and picks out deep midwicket charging in for a superb sliding catch. Bau misjudged the chance for Naim second ball at deep square leg but was athletic enough to recover. This time he reads it off the bat to perfection and the lack of hesitation is what allows him to cover the 20 yards rushing in to get his hands underneath the ball.

shortText: Vala to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full on the legs, chipped into the leg side for one.

shortText: Vala to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: good length ball on fifth stump, slapped to backward point.
short on sixth stump, slapped into the covers to the sweeper for one.

shortText: Vala to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full outside off, driven to wide long-off for one.
short and wide, guided wide of short third man.
full on fifth stump, driven to long-off.

shortText: Amini to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: flighted full on fourth stump, defended to Amini.

shortText: Amini to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: charges Amini, the bowler drags the length back and pushes this wide of Amini to the left through mid-on.

shortText: Amini to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: full on off, driven back to Amini.
good length ball pulled flat to Hiri Hiri at deep midwicket who charges across to stop it, brief fumble but they can't take a second.

shortText: Amini to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: short on sixth stump, slaps this flat to long-on.

shortText: Vala to Shakib Al Hasan, SIX
text: full on leg stump, slog sweeps this high and deep beyond the bleachers into the adjacent oval where some other local cricketers are training.

shortText: Vala to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: good length ball slapped through long-on for one.
short and wide, carved behind point to the sweeper for one.

shortText: Vala to Shakib Al Hasan, 2 runs
text: full and wide on sixth stump, carves this inside out over the infield. It falls short of the sweeper but a sharp replay comes in over the stumps to the keeper Doriga. Shakib has to stretch a long way to barely make it in. Doriga collected it at chest height and the time it takes him to get the ball to the bails allows Shakib to just make it home.

shortText: Vala to Shakib Al Hasan, 2 runs
text: short and wide, slaps this behind point and tracked by third man for a pair.

shortText: Vala to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full on sixth stump, punches this to long-off for one.

shortText: Atai to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full outside off, shuffles and sweeps to deep square leg

slaps it straight to deep square! This is dropped short and sits up nicely at middle and off stump line. Rahim waits on it, swivels, and gets a lot of bat on his pull shot. But it is flat and straight at the mid-riff of Hiri Hiri in the deep and he holds on at second attempt after it pops out briefly
good length and pushed through flat, into the stumps on the angle. Mahmudullah steps across into the off side and ramps this into the vacant short fine area
short of a length at middle stump, punched to long-on off the back foot

shortText: Atai to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full at leg stump, flicked down to long-on
short and into leg stump, gets deep into the crease and whips this to deep square off the back foot
pumped far over long-on! Nice, friendly offbreak this. Pushed through at a length and he steps down to the pitch of this and gets a lovely, clean swing of the arms to loft this
full at middle stump, steps out and drills it to long-on's left. Ravu has a lot of work to do there and he sprints and tumbles to stop it. Shakib is too tired to come back for a second that was there

shortText: Bau to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: length and into leg stump, flicked to deep midwicket's right

shortText: Bau to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 wide
text: short and wide outside off, left alone
yorker length and following him outside off as he shuffles. Waits on that and chops it to short third

shortText: Bau to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: good length and fired into leg stump, tucked through square leg with the angle
good length on leg stump, gets forward and flicks through midwicket
short of a length and skidding on outside off, under-edge on the cut to backward point

shortText: Amini to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: short of a length at middle stump, gets deep in the crease and punches to deep midwicket
good length at off stump, defended in front of extra cover

shortText: Amini to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full outside off, driven off the toe-end to long-off
good length and turning away outside off, and eventually past the bat as Mahmudullah brings out the reverse sweep
good length and tight at off stump, pushed with the turn to extra cover's left
good length at leg stump, looks to glance that and gets it off the thigh

shortText: Vala to Shakib Al Hasan, SIX
text: one-hand off but enough to clear the straight boundary. This is tossed up at driving length and Shakib frees himself up and swings at it

shortText: Vala to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: good length and slower outside off, grips and turns as Shakib stretches to try and launch this over extra cover

shortText: Vala to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT
text: no way Charles Amini! Stunning, simply stunning. Good length and turning away again outside off. Shakib gets forward and swings across the line as it turns. Not close to the pitch and something of a hail mary from him as he's been tiring. It comes off the bottom of the bat and heads in long-on's direction. Amini tracks it to his right all the way to the end, manages to get low as he does it, and then lunges forward to get his fingers under this. Superb judgement, because that ball didn't go too high and was dipping fast
good length at middle stump, waits on that and nudges it with soft hands through midwicket
good length at middle stump, gets forward and clips towards deep midwicket
dipping slower yorker outside off, reaches out and opens the face to run this to deep point

shortText: Morea to Afif Hossain, no run

text: just short of fine leg running to his left. Length ball at off stump and he looks to whip it aerially with the angle. That's a big boundary though and it lands in front of the fielder
offcutter at a length outside off, waits on it and jabs it towards point
lovely shot. This is a cutter at length as well and he steps across and swipes this over square leg
good length at off stump, defended into the off side with soft hands
more crafty stuff from the captain. Expert batting, this. Short of a length outside off, allows it to come and uses the pace to chop this between point and short third
short at middle stump, pulled to deep square

shortText: Ravu to Afif Hossain, no run
text: full and across off stump, keeps dipping away from him and he's beaten on the attempted cover drive
short of a length and down leg side, beaten on the glance
cutter at a length just outside off, opens the face and steers that to backward point
cutter, short and outside off. Shuffles and expertly pats this with soft hands to give deep midwicket no chance of stopping the second
short of a length at the hip, waits on it and pushes it to short fine's left
swung over deep midwicket! It's a lovely shin-high full toss at a friendly pace. Mahmudullah takes a step into his crease for that extra time and then clobbers this with an old-fashioned slog
short of a length cutter outside off, chopped through cover
bouncer down leg side, walks into the off and reaches out for a feeble hook shot. It trickles to short fine who gets a direct hit in but Mahmudullah was well in
another short ball but this one is under shoulder height. Flies past his attempted pull outside off
no-ball for second bouncer. Slower short ball, but climbs over his head and counts as the second one for the over, which means a free hit

see ya! Mahmudullah is a man on a mission today. It's a friendly delivery again, this time on length outside off. He shuffles into line and swipes strongly across the line to send it over deep midwicket
short and wide outside off and he latches onto that with a vicious cut past backward point to bring up his fifty! What a knock this is, knew what he wanted to do from ball one
at the stumps and swung away towards deep midwicket
full and wide outside off, just past the marker and called wide

we're going upstairs to check for no-ball. On height. It's a high full toss at leg stump, Mahmudullah is backing away as he swishes this into the leg side. He ends up hitting it to Chad Soper at deep square leg. Third umpire has a look at it, it's thigh height, so well under the waist. But the screen flashes not-out before they make amends and confirm Mahmudullah's innings is over. A complete gamechanger from the captain and he goes off with a smile at all that's just happened
full and wide outside off, reaches out and has a slash at that. Gets a thick outside edge for his efforts that rolls fine of short third
smartly put away. Short of a length and rising at middle stump, shuffles into the off side and uses the rise on the ball to ramp it over the keeper
full and just outside off, driven along the floor to long-off
stabbed straight to short third! Short and wide outside off, nice pace to attempt the shot that Nurul just has. But there isn't enough pace on it and it's an easy one for the fielder
length and at the stumps, walks down at it and miscues it towards the straight boundary
good length and just outside off, dabbed into the covers with soft hands
good connection but only one. Length ball, slower, outside off and he walks into the line and swipes across this. Picked up on the bounce by long-on to his left
slower ball at a length outside off, shuffles and clips into vacant square leg
oh poor ball. Overpitched and on the pads, with fine leg inside. Afif clips it away gratefully to the long leg boundary

another superb catch! What a joy it's been to watch them catch today. This is full and dipping outside off. He gets down on a knee for the slog sweep and gets a good connection on it. But he's too far under it and has absolutely skied it. Ravu runs in from the long midwicket boundary and stays stable enough that he can cover for the swerve - and it swerves gradually to his right and behind. He manages to keep his eye on it and dive about two yards to hold on
short at off stump, gets inside the line and hooks it straight to fine leg
full outside off, stays leg side of it and slashes through point

shortText: Soper to Mahedi Hasan, no run
text: length ball outside off, has a big heave and misses
on the pads, flicked square and they scamper back for a tight second as Siaka's dive gets him home to beat a relay to the keeper.
good length ball on the stumps, flicked away gently for one.
good length ball on off, guided with soft hands behind point for another tight run.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Siaka, no run
text: good length ball on off, defended.
full on off, walks down the track and flicks an outswinger wide of mid-on for one.
attempted yorker on leg stump is a low full toss on the shins and prodded into the covers for one.
full on fourth stump, driven into the covers for one.

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Siaka, no run
text: full and very wide, drives at this and is beaten.

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Siaka, no run
text: full on middle, defended.

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Siaka, no run
text: full on middle, goes to flick, inside edge on the pads. Massive lbw shout from Mustafizur denied. Clear double noise.
overpitched on fourth stump at 134 kph, driven firmly to mid-off for a sharp single.
short and wide, guided with soft hands behind point to deep third man.
full on the pads and flicked through the ring for one.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Siaka, no run
text: full on fourth stump, Siaka shuffles across to scoop and mistimes this into the ground to short fine leg.
attempted yorker sprayed down leg.

full and straight, Siaka's head falls across toward point missing a flick to midwicket. Big lbw shout upheld. He looked unsettled after the injury delay and he was off balance playing that shot. Hit on the knee roll in front of middle and leg. Siaka doesn't bother discussing with Vala whether to use a review. He felt he was out and just walks off.
full on fourth stump, guides this behind point for a tight run.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Vala, no run
text: good length ball, can't get this away.
full outside leg follows Vala backing away and he drives to long-on for one.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Vala, no run
text: short on fifth stump, punches this to backward point. Shakib keeps Vala honest.

Stunner by Nurul Hasan behind the stumps with a one-hander down the leg side. Sums up PNG's tourney. Short on the hips, goes to pull this with a short arm jab just trying to help it on its way through fine leg and instead gets it too fine to keep Nurul in the mix. He anticipated it well and timed his dive perfectly to pluck it at knee height, full extension.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Bau, no run
text: full and wide at 143 kph, left alone.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Bau, no run
text: short and wide again at 142 kph, Bau is hustled trying to pull and cue shots this to cover.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Bau, no run
text: bouncer outside off at 137 kph, beaten on the hook.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Bau, no run
text: short on fourth stump, guided to short third man.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Amini, OUT
text: Naim one ups Amini's catch from the first innings at long-on! Full on off, Amini winds up to heave this down the ground. Naim was fielding quite wide at long-on and has 20-25 yards to track to his right, leaps like a salmon and pouches a spectacular grab at chest height before holding on after a tumble on the landing just a foot inside the rope. 10/10 on the judge's scorecards from Romania, Fiji, Venezuela and Ivory Coast.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Bau, 1 run
text: full on the legs, flicked into midwicket for one.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Atai, no run
text: flighted full on the legs, misses a flick off the pads.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Atai, OUT
text: flighted full on fourth stump, goes to slog sweep, top edge goes to square leg. Too easy. PNG had to go hard early in the Powerplay to have any chance of overhauling the target and the result is looking quite ugly.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Bau, no run
text: dropped! Arm ball on fifth stump on a good length, Bau plays for turn when there is none and a thin edge is bobbled by Nurul before being put down.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Bau, 1 run
text: good length ball on the stumps, flicked into the leg side for one.
short on off, pulls this into the ground through midwicket and they scamper a tight two.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Bau, no run
text: good length ball on fifth stump at 144 kph, left alone.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Bau, no run
text: back of a length on fourth stump at 143 kph, hustled trying to pull and beaten.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Bau, no run
text: gas from Taskin at 145 kph short outside off, tapped into the covers.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Bau, no run
text: full now at 144 kph, defended back to Taskin.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Bau, no run
text: short on the hips flicked to short fine leg.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Hiri, 1 run
text: full on off, prodded away for one.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Bau, 1 run
text: full on middle, flicked through square leg for one.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Hiri, 1 run
text: flighted more on fifth stump on a good length, tapped in front of point for one.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Bau, no run
text: full on middle, flicked straight to midwicket.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Bau, 1 run
text: flighted full on off, slog sweep flutters well short of deep midwicket charging in from the rope.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Hiri, no run
text: flighted on a good length on fourth stump, defended.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Bau, no run
text: short on off, punched into cover.
flighted full on off, slogs this into the ground in the leg side.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Hiri, no run
text: good length ball on off, defended.
flighted full on the stumps, slog sweeps this to deep square leg.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Bau, no run
text: flighted full and very wide outside off, can't connect on the sweep.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Bau, no run
text: good length ball on off, defended to extra cover.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Hiri, no run
text: flighted full and wide outside off, goes to slog sweep and is beaten.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Hiri, no run
text: good length ball defended.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Hiri, no run
text: another flighted full delivery on fifth stump, wild slog sweep misses again.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Hiri, 1 run
text: good length ball on middle, flicked to midwicket for one.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Bau, OUT
text: flighted full on fifth stump, charges Shakib and skies this high to long-on. This time a far less adventurous effort from Naim. He reaches above his head three yards inside the rope and takes a simple catch.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Hiri, no run
text: flighted on a good length on fifth stump, defends and an edge goes through vacant slip (at 25 for 5....) to short third man.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Vanua, no run
text: good length ball on off, defended.

flighted full on fifth stump, Vanua with an impetuous slog second ball and skies this a mile high to Mushfiqur at long-off. He waits an eternity for it to come down. Limp end to the tournament from PNG as they continue to unravel.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Hiri, no run
text: good length and quicker at middle stump, hurriedly pushed to midwicket

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Hiri, no run
text: tossed up at a length on middle stump, steps out and deflects into the leg side off his pad
shot. Tossed up at a length on middle stump, steps out and crunches this over midwicket with a powerful slog

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Hiri, no run
text: short of a length at middle stump, pushed to midwicket's right off the back foot

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Doriga, no run
text: good length outside off, turning away and left alone

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Doriga, 1 run
text: good length outside off, opens the face and dabs that past slip

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Hiri, OUT
text: and another for Shakib. Four wickets for him. This is lobbed up at a length on middle stump, he steps out and then looks for he slog sweep. Gets a top edge that hangs behin Nurul and he takes it easily

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Doriga, no run
text: good length at off stump, defended on the front foot

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Doriga, no run
text: good length and dipping at off stump, looks for the slog sweep and is beaten

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Doriga, 1 run
text: short of a length outside off, punched to sweeper off the back foot
good length just outside off, pushed into the covers with soft hands
full on middle stump, driven towards the non-striker and the bowler can't stop cleanly
full at middle stump, steps out and drills it past the bowler's face. Rahim at long-off cleans up to his right
short of a length and jut outside off, backs away and cuts to sweeper

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Soper, no run
text: short of a length and skidding through, beaten on the late cut

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Soper, no run
text: short of a length and just outside off, punched to extra cover off the back foot
full and wide outside off, driven out to sweeper cover
full and just outside off, opens the face and pats it to extra cover's left
full cutter at off stump, looks to drive firmly and gets a thick outside edge to third man's right
good length cutter at middle and off, stays leg side of that and swings it to long-on's right
short and up at the ribs, hurriedly pulled to fine leg's left

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Soper, no run
text: bouncer at a leg stump line, ducks it hurriedly
short and just outside off, backs away and cuts to sweeper's left
pumped over long-on! Sweet, sweet connection on that from Soper. It's a length ball outside off and he jumps out at it and swings viciously to clear the fielder
short and wide outside off, backs away and cuts to sweeper's right

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Soper, no run
text: full and drifting away outside off, looks to sweep and gets an inside edge onto pad

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Soper, no run
text: full and at leg stump, hurriedly flicked to midwicket

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Soper, no run
text: good length and just outside off, patted down the pitch off the back foot

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Doriga, no run
text: good length cutter wide outside off, reaches out and slashes on the bounce to backward point
full and just outside off, drilled along the floor to long-off
slower ball at a length outside off, clears the front foot and punches towards long-off
full and just outside off, driven back at the bowler who deflects it into extra cover with a half-stop
splits the stumps! Searing yorker headed for middle and off. Soper clears the front foot and has a big heave across the line with no luck

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Morea, no run
text: short of a length and tight at off stump, opens the face and dabs this in point's direction

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Doriga, no run
text: yorker in at the toe this time, he looks to jam it into the leg side and cops it on the boot

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Doriga, no run
text: short and wide outside off, backs away and cuts, beaten
short and up at the ribs. Nervy swipe from underneath this and can only manage a glove on it. Trickles to fine leg's right who makes the ground and then lets it past him sloppily
full and into leg stump, clears the front leg and has a slog, gets a big inside edge to find the fine leg boundary again

dropped but also saved. Full offcutter at off stump. Comes nicely into his swinging arc and he gets a good connection on this. Mustafizur sprints to his left at long-on and times his jump perfectly to get two hands on it as he has the boundary line by his foot. Can't hold on but manages to parry it in

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Morea, no run
text: good length at off stump, backs away and mistimes a drive on the up to extra cover
gets enough on it! Full cutter at middle and off, clears the front leg and has a slog at it. Slices it a touch but there's enough to clear long-on
short of a length at leg stump, pulled on the bounce to deep square
short and rising at off stump, backs away and mistimes an upper cut towards sweeper cover
short of a length at middle stump, mistimed pull towards deep square

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Doriga, no run
text: slower short ball outside off, reaches out at that with a pull and is beaten

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Doriga, (no ball) 2 runs
text: full and just outside off, gets the front foot out and drives uppishly to long-off's left. It's a no-ball and they have a free hit
slower short ball at off stump, pulled out to deep midwicket
full and very wide outside off, left alone

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Morea, no run
text: full and wide outside off, swings and misses

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Morea, 1 run, OUT
text: full and at leg stump, clips it into the square leg region and wants the two. Afif is rapid in getting to the ball though and his throw is quick and on top of the stumps. Nurul clips the bails off and completes the job
full and just outside off, backs away and drives to long-off
slower short ball at middle stump, pulled to deep square
full and at the stumps, clears the front leg and clobbers this over long-on! Doriga is going out having some fun, 7 away from a half-century here
full and very wide outside off, can't reach that
short of a length at off stump, backs away and flat-bats it over the mid-off region!

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Ravu, 1 leg bye
text: short of a length and tight at the body, leaps as he tries to turn this into the leg side. Cops it on the body and they take the run at point

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Doriga, no run
text: good length cutter, wide outside off. Has a heave at it but that rips away from him
good length slower ball outside off, reaches out and pushes uppishly to sweeper cover and retains strike
slower short ball at leg stump, pulls it out to deep midwicket's right

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Ravu, no run
text: short and following him down leg side as he backs away and has a slap at it. Beaten
that's that! PNG fall shy of the 100 mark and Doriga of a half-century. This is short of a length outside off, he backs away and has a stab at this. Thin outside edge is taken easily
tossed up, eased back down the ground to get SL, and Nissanka, off the mark

he's claiming it, is he? No, he wants the umpires top consult, but Perera might be on his way!. A bit of a nothing shot, he spooned it just short of cover, but Dockerell puts in a brilliant dive in front of him - but has he cupped his fingers underneath it? The soft signal is out. I think it's going to be given, there's no clear pictures of the ball bouncing in front of him. Yep, it's given, Perera goes for a first-ball duck!
a bit of flight, keeping it straight and simple for now. Guided back down the ground
another nudge down to long-on
flatter and quicker on this occasion. Stirling collects the ball driven back at him
tickled to square leg, and that ends an excellent first over for Ireland and old Stirlo
kept low, and so went underneath the slash Chandimal tried to execute

gets this one through, and nearly sweeps himself off his feet in the process. Ran down the wicket, a bit of width on the offside, and just about clears point and he overbalances. First boundary for Sri Lanka
comeback from Little, Chandimal's dragged it back onto his stumps!. Too close to cut, and shaped in slightly, taking the other edge and rattling back onto the stumps. Ireland are flying!

two in two, what's happening here?Avishka's cleaned up for a first ball duck, what an absolute beauty of a delivery that was. Talk about Test match batsmen, that was a glorious Test match delivery. Lands on off-stump, shaping in, seams back in too and goes right through the gate, clipping the top of off.

shortText: Little to de Silva, no run
text: just about keeps it out. It came back in, that swing is proving a real handful

shortText: Little to de Silva, no run
text: defended, and that concludes a near-perfect over from Little
keeper does well to prevent that going for five wides, that was dragged well down
defended into the offside - I might have given Stirling another over personally
driven to long-on
full length, Nissanka nearly yorked himself as he tried to advance down the wicket
little flick of the wrist to get Hasaranga on strike

shortText: Young to de Silva, no run
text: banged into the pitch, defended back to Young
lofted over the infield towards third man, and he keeps the strike. Just two of that over

shortText: Little to de Silva, no run
text: swing and a miss

shortText: Little to de Silva, no run
text: slightly wider and fuller. Hasaranga drives to cover
gets a thick outside edge to third man
back of a length, thwacks him high on the pad
exquisite shot. Back of a length, and Hasaranga went back and just punched it through extra cover. Pure timing. Shot of the innings by a distance

shortText: Little to de Silva, no run
text: tucked him up, allowing less width. Punched to backward point
gets a streaky boundary first up. Think that was a slightly slower delivery, and Nissanka only manages an outside edge that's fine enough to evade a despairing dive from third man
nothing streaky about that one! A touch of width and Nissanka leans into the cut shot, placing it perfectly, wide enough to give third man no chance
defended
runs it down to third man
lovely timing, but that's much too full from Adair. It allowed the batter to lean into it, caressing it past mid-on to help himself to four more

shortText: Adair to de Silva, no run
text: gets the yorker right this time, and concludes an expensive over with a dot ball
eases it back down the ground

shortText: Simi Singh to de Silva, no run
text: makes room but only gets the bottom edge of the bat to it

shortText: Simi Singh to de Silva, FOUR
text: this time he makes room to good effect! Guides it through the cover and point region, splitting the two fielders right down the middle. It's the classical cricket shots that are fetching SL runs right now

shortText: Simi Singh to de Silva, FOUR
text: once more! This time he drives it over extra cover, taking advantage of the fielders in the ring

shortText: Simi Singh to de Silva, FOUR
text: three in three! Hasaranga really keen on making the most of this final Powerplay over. Slow and wide, and all Hasaranga needs to do is create width and wallop it over cover

shortText: Simi Singh to de Silva, FOUR
text: just gorgeous. A masterclass of Powerplay T20 batting from Hasaranga. Clears the front leg and lofts him over mid-off to round out the Powerplay with four fours in a row
good-looking shot, the fielder in the ring on the offside did well to get a finger to it or that might have been another four
runs it down to third man and that brings up 50 for Sri Lanka
width once more, and he times it to deep cover
worked into the onside to keep the strike rotating
opens the face and runs it down to the man at deep cover
slower delivery, turns it round the corner into the onside
runs it down to third man

shortText: Young to de Silva, no run
text: well timed but straight to extra cover
good pick-up but doesn't quite time it as well as he'd like. Lands short of long-off
nudged into the onside to allow the pair to exchange ends
slower ball, and he ended up being forced to play a one-handed shot. The lack of pace did him completely and it went high in the air, but thankfully for Sri Lanka, lands in a gap

rocked back and punched it over long-on, and that's connected so well it goes all the way for six!. It was slightly back of a length without enough pace to bother de Silva and he ends the over brilliantly
quick leg bye - Campher and Nissanka collided into each other but looks like no harm done

shortText: Campher to de Silva, no run
text: thick outside edge that nearly carried to short third. The fielder says it's bounced just short, though

shortText: Campher to de Silva, no run
text: takes the pace off that one, prodded to cover

shortText: Campher to de Silva, no run
text: driven straight to cover this time
crunched into the offside but sweeper cover's alert enough to prevent Sri Lanka from getting two
another drive down to the sweeper. Good over from Campher.
steps outside off stump, and nudges to the on-side

shortText: Simi Singh to de Silva, 1 run
text: patted from wide outside off once more, hitting with the spin to midwicket
reverses the hands, slaps an uncultured but effective pull/sweep through third man. Back of a length, and easy pickings
tucked to the on-side for the single

shortText: Simi Singh to de Silva, 1 run
text: very full length, dipping into the toes, clipped to mid-on
tapped into space at mid-on, the lack of pace allows them to hustle back for the second

shortText: Adair to de Silva, no run
text: low full toss, outside off, pumped firmly to cover

shortText: Adair to de Silva, no run
text: chopped out to point, weight rocking backwards, but can't open the angle

shortText: Adair to de Silva, no run
text: flashed into the covers, on a full length outside off again
advances to the pitch, turns it into a full toss, stays legside of it to pump another drive to the cover sweeper
full once more, eased out to cover

shortText: Adair to de Silva, no run
text: back of a length, hits the seam and climbs over an ambitious wipe. Gets out of the over cheaply
inside-out, up and over, launched to the stands at wide long-on! That's a stunning piece of timing, just caressed with the pace
tickled to the on-side, they hustle for the second, the shy is a direct hit at the keeper's end but safely home
punched to the off side, this will be close if the shy hits! Excellent one-handed stretching stop at short cover... and an aborted run results in a desperate dive for the crease
opens the face again, rolls the fingers on the slower ball, that's too wide at that pace and Hasaranga slices into the gap at backward point. Excellent work
banged in short, rolls the wrists out to deep midwicket. A pricy over from Campher, and Sri Lanka continue to thrive
crashed hard into the covers, and dropped! A fierce chance, but Balbirnie should have clung on, reaching high to his left
tight line, dropped into the off side
rolls the fingers on the full length, pushed out to the off side
width outside off, a gliding drive with an open face, down to the point sweeper.

right up to the toes, and pinned on the pads! Big appeal but the umpires says no ... Ireland ponder the review, and up they go... very full, leg-sided... and clipping the stumps... not out is the verdict
up on the toes again, back of a length, eased to deep cover and that is a magnificent rebuilding half-century, from 38 balls. it's as if that 8 for 3 never happened...
low full toss on the legs, flicked square
flipped to the on-side, singles there for the taking right now

shortText: Simi Singh to de Silva, 2 runs
text: gallop and slap, two steps to the pitch and slammed to wide long-off

shortText: Simi Singh to de Silva, FOUR
text: full toss again, another poor over taking shape, panned through backward point, retreating outside leg to cuff the ball between two fielders with an open face. Excellent placement

shortText: Simi Singh to de Silva, FOUR
text: wide full toss, wafty chop, out through point. Singh is not on song...

shortText: Simi Singh to de Silva, 1 run
text: fired into the toes, a big swing through the line, not quite timed as long-on tidies up
makes space on the leg side again, another full-blooded slap out to deep cover. Throwing the bat with abandon
plopped onto a full length, he sights the slower ball straight from the hand, and that's another magnificent inside-out loft over the covers. Runs flowing

hacked down to backward point, surely a run-out! The shy comes in to the keeper, but Campher isn't behind the stumps, and can't connect with a relay into the stumps! Looked like a fatal stutter, but it's a let-off
excellent bouncer, but it's all going Sri Lanka's way now! A hurried top-edge, sails up and away over the keeper's head
opens the face on the full length, fenced down to third man

flashed to deep point, rolling the wrists on an open-faced drive. The off-side has been hugely productive for Sri Lanka which tells a story. No slogging, all cultured cricket shots, to get them back into the contest
flicked round the corner, Nissanka has his fifty now, and it's even more brisk than his team-mates. 37 balls, and more to come, you sense

that's the end of that! Sliced to backward point, plucked with relief above the head in both hands. A well-directed slower ball, into the blockhole, no pace on the scything drive, and Ireland have a reprieve
full toss, wide of off stump, guided out to point for the single
slower ball, outside off, and that's outstanding placement. Dangles the hands with an open face, guiding the controlled edge down through a very fine third man

slower ball, inside-edged down into the pad flap, and Nissanka scuttles off for a single with the ball still in his possession! Adair looks miffed, but entirely accidental ... I think it was called dead-ball initially, but the umpires have changed their mind. But the single that Nissanka took is struck off
very full, tapped to the on-side
wide yorker, but Nissanka's wrists are primed to cash in on those... another filleted flick through third man
whoops, that's a horrible wide, attempted back-of-the-hander, doesn't hit the cut strip, on either axis...
patted to long-on, on a very full length
very full length, outside off, beats an attempted crack through the covers

picked up off the toes, and straight to deep square leg! Lots of hang time, as it plunges out of the floodlights, looked like a clean strike, but there's a lot of acreage out there. Ireland bite back again
attempted sweep, flicks the back of the bat as they hustle for the single
round the wicket, spears in a fine yorker, and poked out to point
beaten outside off, by a whisker! Good length, shaping in, eludes a flat-footed flick
on the legs, nudged to backward square
flogged through the line, and plugs just short of the man in the deep
cracked out to the covers, Ireland are regrouping well after their mid-innings meltdown
hauled across the line to deep midwicket
advances to the pitch, Young bangs in a short ball in response, and a scuffed pull lands behind the bowler. The end of a gutsy spell from Young, who's kept a lid on Sri Lanka's ambitions
blatted off the front foot! That's a monstrous strike, clean through the gap at deep midwicket. In fact, it plugged inches short of the rope, but was travelling at a rate of knots
advance to the pitch again, cuffed to the on-side on a full length
full length, beats a wipe to leg, and the keeper fumbles too to gift the bye
leathered to the long-off sweeper, climbing into a wide line

very wide, Nissanka chases the ball, and toe-ends it to the keeper! Had he left it, he'd have got that one again. But instead it's the end of a fantastic innings, and a fourth scalp for Ireland's main man!
very full, right into the blockhole, pumped back at the bowler. That's the end of a superb spell. Four-fours in consecutive matches for Ireland bowlers
full length, right into the blockhole, lumped to long-off
pace off, waits on the back foot, and pulls to midwicket with not much timing. But they hurry back for the second
yorker, timber! Dips into the blockhole, all around an expansive leg-side waft, and back goes the off stump
flipped off the toes, out to backward square
slower ball, sits in the pitch, and that is vast! A dismissive wind-up and wipe over deep midwicket, right under the ball to thunder it high onto the concourse. Bosh
cheeky! Dips into the ramp shot, picks off the full toss, and flicks it over the shoulder. No fielder at fine leg and Sri Lanka finish with a flourish
wicket-to-wicket, and Stirling dabs it to mid-on and gets off the mark
crunched off the back foot past cover-point. Loose delivery, short and wide, with little pace. Sat up for the batter
overcompensated, that was tailing down leg. Flicked to square leg
cramped him for room, saw him trying to back away and charge down the wicket

oh he's put it down! Rajapaksa had ground to cover, which he did brilliantly, only to drop it once he was underneath it. Stirling pulled the short ball away to cow corner, but never really got the timing he wanted
top-edged, and this time it's taken by short fine! Karunaratne has his wicket!. Top edge from O'Brien, it flew up high in the air, and the fielder makes no mistake
going way down leg
what on earth was that! Might have hit a crack because it reared in off the pitch so sharply the keeper had to leap to his left to prevent four byes. And all that at 146 kph. Unplayable
back of a length at full pelt. He blocks
pushed into the onside
streaky. Tried to heave it over long on, but gets a fine inside edge. Fine leg does well to cut it off
banged into the pitch, Balbirnie ducks under
this time the top edge is fine enough to give fine leg no chance. Banged in short, Balbirnie wasn't in control of the hook, but the rub of the green goes his way
flat, he had a smear at it but only gets an inner edge
connects this time, and gets it over the midwicket boundary. Hit it with the spin, and had enough power to carry it nearly all the way
and that's the end of Stirling! Fine leg nearly put down the easiest of chances but hangs on at the second attempt. Tried to sweep it past fine leg, but only sent it down his throat
flighted, defends to midwicket
flat and straight, did well to get his bat down in time
opened the face and ran it past first slip to get himself off the mark with a couple
angles back in off the seam, almost an identical delivery to Chameera's first. And this one's 146 kph, too
backed away and drove it through the offside, but only to point
lovely delivery again, jagging back in off the seam, and this time it does too much to prevent the keeper cutting it off. Four byes
full and straight, Balbirnie digs it out. This one's 149kph, real pace from Kumara this over

the pace does for him. Top edge to fine leg, who takes the catch, but has he touched the rope? He wants the umpire to check. The soft signal is not out. Yep, both feet touching the rope, that's six runs
ends with a yorker. 11 off an over that really deserved to be a wicket-maiden
slightly short of a length, nudged into the onside
bowled him The googly keeps low and clatters into Delany's stumps. he tried to cut it but the ball zooted underneath the blade. Ireland in trouble, and so, remember are the Netherlands

shortText: de Silva to Campher, no run
text: blocked

shortText: de Silva to Campher, no run
text: driven back to the bowler

shortText: de Silva to Campher, no run
text: kept low and spun away, almost doubled Campher up
wrong'un again, driven back down the ground to allow Campher to get off the mark and keep the strike
banged into the surface at 142kph. Defended
thick outside edge that perfectly pierces the first slip and third man in the deep. The pace means it rushes through the outfield for a fortuitous boundary
the extra pace means Campher can't get on top of it. Nearly took his outside edge
slower ball, and it looked like Campher had been anticipating it. Just 119kph, allowing him time to rock back and pummel this past mid-off.
reverts to the high pace - 147kph. Batter's nowhere near getting on top of it with his attempted pull shot
this kept low out of nowhere. Campher's pull shot wasn't in the same post code

shortText: de Silva to Balbirnie, no run
text: another googly - how has that missed the stumps. Just got an inside edge and barely saved his stumps

shortText: de Silva to Balbirnie, no run
text: defended back to the bowler
dropped! Reverse sweep went straight to the man at 45, who shells a routine chance. Hasaranga isn't happy

shortText: de Silva to Campher, no run
text: just about kept this one out too
dragged this down. Campher drives to long-off, who does well to keep it to one

shortText: de Silva to Balbirnie, no run
text: played all around it again. The inside edge saved his stumps once more
a beauty of a yorker that sends Karunaratne pleading to the umpire for lbw. It's not, but it swept the batter off his feet
driven to extra cover
connects off the middle for once. Wasn't much pace and it sat up to be smashed out of the park. Balbirnie obliged to deposit a 93m strike into over midwicket
paddled to midwicket - connected really well using the bowler's pace but it's straight to the man stationed there
cunning. Slower ball - just 103 kph - beats the batter all ends up
didn't get the timing right and flat-bats it down to long-on
keeps it straight, it's driven back to him
swept but didn't get the right connection
tossed it up nicely. Balbirnie places it into the onside and scampers off for two. Direct hit might have had the non-striker
flatter this time, pushed into the offside
nicely placed into the deep on the offside. Sweeper cover collects
came down the wicket but Theekshana adjusts his length, pulling it back. Finishes with a dot ball
opens the face and runs it down to third man
slashed at it but found himself beaten. The pace is proving hard to handle, that was 147 kph
brilliant yorker, but there's sloppiness in the field! Four overthrows, so Ireland get another five. Poor Kumara keeps conceding runs when he's done nothing wrong
full toss, timed into the offside
took the pace off it. All he can do is crunch it to deep point
full toss - is it a no-ball for height? The umpire reckons it's fine, so it's just a single. That's drinks

shortText: de Silva to Balbirnie, no run
text: uppish, nearly caught and bowled, that
opens the face and punches it into the offside
stepped across and smeared it past fine leg and hared back for two. Good running, but they need a few boundaries now
well flighted, he pushed it into the offside and raced through for a single
tossed it up, nice drive from Balbirnie. Deep extra cover did exceptionally well to make up ground to his right and keep it to two

shortText: de Silva to Balbirnie, no run
text: defended into the onside. Miller's coming in to take you through to the end
on the back foot, thumped to deep point
opens the face and punched out to cover
slower ball, very loopy, and patted up and over deep cover
right in the blockhole, an ambitious hack to the leg side
reverses the hands for a ramp, the bowler sees him coming and over-cooks the wide line outside off
slower ball outside off, steps across the stumps and flicks a well-placed paddle behind square
steps back and across, attempted club over the covers, doesn't connect properly, but that's a decent over... just about up with the rate at 10s
attempted sweep, not timed, bobbles to the leg side for the single
steps back and across, lofts into no-man's land in the covers, clean lines on the strike
back of the hand, wider line, chases it with an open face, cuffed uppishly to the cover sweeper, who gathers on the bounce
dragged down, hauled to the leg side
huge swipe across the line! And Campher is done! That one was pushed through a touch quicker, a touch fuller, lured the wide-eyed slog, then burst off the deck into the stumps
right back on the stumps, flicked to the leg side with a very lbw-inducing stance. Don't want to miss those!
very full again, pushed back at the bowler
sharp pace on the short ball, Tector lines up his pull and rather wears it, a deflection to the on-side
very full length, Tector gets underneath a ping to the on-side, from deep in the crease, and finds a gap at wide long-on
yorker, excellent length, dug out but straight back at the bowler

gloves the bouncer, and another one bites the dust! A sharp short ball, Tector falls to the off-side as the ball passes at arm-pit height, technically a leg-side strangle as the bat swings by, but it was better than that, good reward for hostile pace and smart variation
nudged off the legs, on the full length
fizzes through outside off, lovely tight lines, beating the outside edge

huge swish across the line, Perera is excited about this one, as he gathers and flicks off the bails in a fluid motion! It's gone upstairs, and that looks very out... but the umpire is checking for the edge first, as caught trumps stumped in the dismissals hierarchy... nope, no edge, so this will go down as a stumping. The toe clearly dragged out of the crease
back of a length, and clawed to the on side
very full, and punched out to the off side
full length, clubbed to the on-side, this is dribbling away now for Ireland
full once more, outside off, can't connect with a thump into the off side
full and straight, punched back down the line, grabbed at mid-off by Chameera, and that's a direct hit! Out by a good two metres. This one is cooked!
back of a length, outside off, chopped down to third man
nudged into the gap, singles won't cut it now. Nor, frankly, will boundaries...
sliced drive, and a stunning reflex take at backward point! The final roadblock is gone, Balbirnie flung his hands through the full length, and Avishka reached high to his left, cupped in both hands
full length, thumped on the pads, deflected to the leg side
low full toss, scuffed to deep point

shortText: de Silva to Simi Singh, 1 run
text: flicked off the toes to the leg side

shortText: de Silva to Young, no run
text: full length, can't connect on a hack to the leg side

shortText: de Silva to Young, no run
text: tossed up outside off, a flashy slog sweep, misses, off come the bails again ... the umpire's having a look. No edge involved, and the toe is grounded this time

shortText: de Silva to Young, no run
text: slower through the air, gripping back into the right-hander, worked to point
slapped from a full length, out to the leg side

shortText: de Silva to Simi Singh, no run
text: crunched back through the line, a sharp one-handed intercept to see off another tidy over, another tidy spell

yorker, clean through him! Outstanding bowling, wicket-to-wicket, sharp pace, full length, right in the blockhole and Young has no answer. The writing is on the wall now, and even the po-faced Lion on Sri Lanka's shirt is starting to look cheerful
full length, another attempted yorker, leg-sided this time

shortText: Chameera to Simi Singh, no run
text: swished to the leg side, inside-edge of the bat on a futile hack

shortText: Chameera to Simi Singh, no run
text: another massive biff, inside-edged into the pads, winding up on the full length, to little avail
short, clawed to the on-side, hitting down on the pull
another whoosh of a drive outside off, no contact

shortText: Karunaratne to Simi Singh, no run
text: leg-sided, flicks the pad to spare the wide
a skip to the pitch and a languid drive into the covers
turns inside out for a flick to leg, and misses! Back goes the middle stump, and that is a thumping win
slanted full on the pads, Myburgh goes to sweep and misses off the pads.
good length ball on middle and leg, goes back to flick through square leg.
good length ball on fifth stump, defended to cover.
arm ball skids on from fifth stump, goes to cut and misses.
full on off, whipped through wide long-on for a pair.
good length ball on off, goes back to pull flat to long-on.
good length on the hips, too straight and flicked off the hips behind square to the rope.
fuller on middle this time, defended into midwicket, unnecessary throw at the stumps and they take an overthrow.
good length ball on middle, defended back to Wiese.
full and slanted down leg, flicked gently to the fine leg rope. Too easy for O'Dowd.
short and wide, slapped behind point and cut off at deep third man for one.
back of a length ball outside off, goes to drive and beaten.
good length ball on off, defended.
good length ball on off, defended to point.
tries to bump him at 129 kph, pulled powerfully over backward square and flies over the rope.
fullish length outside off at 129 kph, shuffle down the track to convert this into a half-volley and carts this over mid-off to the rope.
136 kph ball very full on off stump, driven to mid-off.
131 kph good length ball on off stump, defended.
good length ball at 124 kph on off, defended.
good length ball on fourth stump, defended to extra cover.
back of a length on the legs, Myburgh is late on the pull.

dropped! Back of a length ball on the stumps, tries to pull this over the leg side ring and Wiese backpedals before reaching up and gets two hands to it, fingertips really, but can't clutch on at midwicket. Very difficult chance because of the height it came in and Wiese is a tall man. 8/10 on difficulty, but he mistimed his bunny hop or else he might have got the full hand and palm around it.
back of a length follows Myburgh backing away, goes to flick and tickles it fine.
back of a length glided away but not timed all the way, chased down at the rope and they run sharply to come back for a third.
fullish length ball on fourth stump, driven high over wide mid-off for two.
good length ball on off stump, defended.
fullish length on fourth stump at 130 kph, driven to extra cover.
good length ball on the stumps, flicks this behind square for one.
fullish length following him backing away from leg but Myburgh is still able to create enough room to drive inside out through cover past a diving fielder on the ring to the rope.
full on the legs, flicks this toward mid-on for a very tight single.
fullish length slanted down leg as Myburgh moved across his stumps, nearly bowls him behind his legs.
good length ball on off stump, carved behind point for one.
good length ball slanted down leg.
good length ball, charges Frylinck but misses a big heave.
fullish length ball, driven in the ring for one.

slower bouncer, hard to sum up how slow it was, and Myburgh struggles to keep his hands back trying to uppercut it over point, but can't get any power behind the shot and it lobs up gently to the point fielder on the ring. Clever from Frylinck, easy catch for Baard.
good length ball outside off, slapped through the ring for a pair.
another good length ball tapped away for a single.
fullish length on off, punched away for one.

shortText: Scholtz to van der Merwe, 1 run
text: good length ball on the legs, flicked behind square for one.
full on middle and leg, driven to long-on.

shortText: Scholtz to van der Merwe, 1 run
text: flighted more on middle on a good length, backs away to slap into the off side for one.
good length ball on middle, punched over mid-off.

shortText: Scholtz to van der Merwe, FOUR
text: breaks out the reverse sweep to a ball speared into middle and leg, carts it high over backward point and backspins away to the rope.
full on middle and off, flicked to deep square leg.

shortText: Wiese to van der Merwe, OUT
text: short on fifth stump, tries to cut this but it climbs on him and winds up slashing it to deep third man. Fielder is stationed fine on the rope and it finds him to perfection. Scholtz with safe hands two yards inside the rope with the floppy hat takes it at chest height.
short and wide, slapped wide of the cover sweeper for a pair.
back of a length on the stumps, can't get this through the ring.
short ball outside off, can't get the cut shot off.
fuller on the legs, flicked through wide long-on.
full on the legs, flicked through square leg for one.
full on the stumps, driven in the air down the ground for one.
good length ball on the legs follows him backing away, can't piece the gap at backward point.
good length ball on leg stump, again jammed out to the ring fielder.
backs away from leg again to create room driving a full ball off leg stump to long-off.
good length ball on the legs, flicked through square leg for one.
back of a length on fourth stump, sliced behind point for one.
good length ball outside off, driven firmly to the cover sweeper.
short on fifth stump, pulled in the gap between long on and deep midwicket for a pair.
short on the legs, flicked behind square for one.
full on fifth stump, driven to extra cover.
full on middle and leg, misses a flick and the ball dribbles off the pads into the leg side for an extra.
back of length outside off and Ackermann steers it away to deep cover

chance at the on-striker's end, no direct hit and O'Dowd survives! He pushed the length ball from outside off to cover and took off but he knew almost immediately that it wasn't a great decision. He gave up at three-fourths of the pitch and luckily for him the fielder didn't strike
nearly in the block hole and the batter bunts it back with hard hands
slices this one outside off and a diving fielder at backward point does great work to save a couple, if not three
on middle and off line, back of length, he heaves and misses it! Goes just over the stumps
on middle and leg now and O'Dowd whips it away to deep square leg to keep strike
stifled appeal for lbw as O'Dowd tries to work it to leg and gets only a leg bye for one
109kmh, slower ball cutting in towards the pads and it's helped to deep square leg
another slower ball, at 104kmh, shorter length and coming in with the angle, and O'Dowd pulls it late enough to beat the fielders behind square for four
angling in again from wide of the crease and he works it past midwicket for one more
room for Ackermann and he scythes that away for four more! At 118kmh, and enough width for the batter to free his arms and steer it behind square in the gap
cutting into him, he works it towards long-on for one
into the batter from around the wicket and he swings it off the pads to deep square leg
wide outside off but it's also short enough for O'Dowd to pull it to deep midwicket
wide outside off but in the block hole this time, he steers it towards extra cover for one more

another chance for run-out at the bowler's end and another life for O'Dowd! Slammed it to extra cover from wide outside off, they take off immediately again and the batter realises yet again that he's going to fall short so he gives up in the end. Again, no direct hit and he survives
takes a step down and digs it out from nearly in the block hole to sweeper cover
chases it really wide outside off but it's a wide
short and wide yet again, he slaps it down to long-off
into the stumps with the angle, he slams it back and the ball deflects off the bowler's hand for one
hint of width, slightly full as well, and O'Dowd lofts that nicely inside out and over the covers for a four to bring up another fifty
slides it a long way in and past the batter for a wide. It also goes off the keeper's gloves for one more
stays back and works the ball against the spin to leg
goes back in the crease and whips the ball to deep midwicket
in the gap on the leg side this time and its four more! He planted his front foot forward and pulled that short ball to the right of long-on in the gap
drives this one with the spin to long-off for one
swings this one with the angle to deep midwicket
low and wide outside off, he edges it thick and fr to third man
backs away and stays still this time, he bowls it wide outside off and O'Dowd slaps it to long-off, but not off the middle
deceives the bowler by backing away and then going across off, he goes down leg for a wide
goes for the block hole outside off, Ackermann goes for a swing but can only help it down to long-off for one
133kmh, keeps a bit low as it lacks pace and goes under the batter's swing outside off

great finish to the over from O'Dowd! Goes across early, and Trumpelmann sends down a full toss on the stumps, eyeing a yorker, which the batter swings late intentionally to collect four behind square
slow and short outside off, he pulls it away to deep midwicket

long-off running in for the catch, dives forward but it falls short! It was well outside off again and O'Dowd tried lofting it to the wide of long-off but the fielder ran hard to his left to put his hands behind the ball just in time and even keep it down to one
lack of pace, slower ball goes past the swing of the bat to the keeper
just past the keeper! Short and slow, rising on the off side, which he tries to pull but only manages an edge and the ball lobs wide of a leaping keeper to his left towards short third man
makes room and drives this fuller ball to cover for one
nearly in the block hole, which he steers away to deep point
pretty wide outside off, he drives it away to deep point
in the block hole although way too wide, and he steers it to third man late for one

third life for O'Dowd, this time a drop! Flicks the low full toss but only manages a leading edge which goes really high towards the covers, a fielder runs in, has plenty of time, but has to dive full length forward to get two hands, but can't hold on
continues outside off and he works it towards point for one
goes across a long way and sweep-flicks it to deep midwicket
well outside off, lack of pace, Ackermann swings hard towards point but misses and it's not called a wide because the batter had gone a bit too far on the off side
slow and on the stumps, flicked in the air to deep midwicket
finally Ackermann gets a big hit and will he be relieved! He's been scratchy today but made that look easy by flicking that with great timing from the stumps over fine leg for a six
makes room for the slow yorker on leg and he does well to work it to leg again and comes back for the second
