slower one into the pitch but down leg for a wide
holes out to deep midwicket this time, easy catch. Slow and into the pitch on short of length, Ackermann has to go after this one but he doesn't get enough to clear the fielder in the deep
helps his first ball with the angle to leg and all the fielders are near the rope so they come back for the second despite the heat O'Dowd has been running in
short ball banged in towards leg, pulls it late to fine leg
wide outside off this time, slower ball, as expected, and he drives it away from the body and misses
110kmh, back of the hand slower ball comes in and goes past leg for a wide
goes across to the off side to target the shorter leg side boundary and he connect well after going down on a knee and sweep that over the fielder in the deep for six!
wants to swat this one from outside off to wide long-on but misses this time
in the block hole outside off, he drives it past cover this time for one
slower ball outside off, he comes down and drives down the ground but misses

loud appeal from the bowler but this struck him outside leg and they sneak in two leg byes because the throw is at the wrong end! The ball deflected off the pad to leg, there was one leg bye for sure, and when they returned for a second, the fielder didn't go for O'Dowd's end. He must be exhausted by now
slow but it's too short and wide, and Edwards waits before punching that to the cover boundary. Great start to the over for Netherlands
much closer to the stumps and he works it behind square. A fumble there means it's an easy couple

O'Dowd is finally run out after lives I've lost count of! Edwards bunted this yorker down to long-on and there was no harm in trying for the second with just three balls to go. But an accurate throw means O'Dowd is well short. Superb innings that kept the innings together until the last over
bangs in a short ball, and Edwards is ready for the reverse hit, and he adjusts well to almost scoop that over the keeper's right hand for four
wide yorker left alone just inside the guideline.
full on fourth stump, driven to extra cover.
full on off, punched straight and cut off at mid-off for one.
full and speared into the legs, goes to flick and misses, sliding well down leg. They take an extra to square leg.
full and speared down leg.
full and wide, driven to mid-off.
fullish length slanted across fifth stump at 133 kph, Baard beaten on the drive.
flighted full on fifth stump, goes for a hammer sweep and sends it in the air over square leg, very safe to the rope.
how good is this! Now Green goes for the reverse sweep to a full ball on fifth stump again, same line and length but pierces the gap between backward point and short third man.
good length ball on middle, defended.
goes to reverse sweep again to a ball darted into the legs, can't get this away.
full on middle, driven to mid-on.
full on the legs again, sweeps this off the gloves over the keeper and goes through fine leg for a pair.

shortText: van Beek to Baard, no run
text: full on the stumps, defended.
good length ball on fifth stump, shuffles across to flick a pull over square leg, finds the rope with ease.
back of a length on the hips, flicked through midwicket for a well run pair.

shortText: van Beek to Baard, no run
text: full on fourth stump, driven to cover.

shortText: van Beek to Baard, no run
text: missed runout! Good length ball punched into cover, they set off for a suicide run into cover. The throw from van der Merwe misses with Baard 10 yards out. If he had waited a second longer, he could have relayed to Edwards over the stumps but really rushed the throw unnecessarily. However, Edwards was also very slow getting to the stumps and was still several yards away when the throw was unleashed.
Baard makes the Dutch pay next ball by powering this through the ring and all the way to the rope.

shortText: van der Gugten to Green, no run
text: good length ball defended.

shortText: van der Gugten to Green, 1 run
text: good length ball on the pads flicked into midwicket for one.

shortText: van der Gugten to Baard, no run
text: van der Gugten leaps wide of the crease to slant this in to Baard on off stump, defended.

shortText: van der Gugten to Baard, FOUR
text: van der Gugten again leaps very wide to deliver at 118 kph, too straight slanted into the pads and flicked to the fine leg rope.

shortText: van der Gugten to Baard, 1 run
text: yorker on middle and leg, flicked behind square.

shortText: van der Gugten to Green, FOUR
text: Green charges van der Gugten and a 123 kph ball is converted into a half volley on off stump and carved high over mid-off for four.
full on off stump, guided behind point for one.
back of a length on middle, goes back to flick and misses, hit above the pads, lbw shout denied.
back of a length on fifth stump, Green goes to pull and drags on. Didn't come on to the bat as he expected and a bottom edge is the result.
good length ball defended.
good length ball angled across fifth stump, beaten driving.
back of a length slapped behind point for one.
full on off, punched wide of mid-off for one.
full on middle and off, flicked into midwicket.

shortText: van Beek to Williams, no run
text: back of a length on off, punched to extra cover.

shortText: van Beek to Williams, no run
text: back of a length on middle, defended to point.

shortText: van Beek to Williams, no run
text: slower ball slanted into the legs, misses a heave to the leg side.
back of a length outside off, slaps this through cover for a boundary to end the Powerplay.

shortText: van der Merwe to Baard, no run
text: full on middle and off, defended.

shortText: van der Merwe to Baard, 1 run
text: reverse sweep comes out to a ball full on fourth stump, gets it fine and stopped by a dive at short third man. They think about a second initially but Myburgh recovers well enough to prevent that.

shortText: van der Merwe to Williams, 2 runs
text: good length ball on off stump, punched to cover.

shortText: van der Merwe to Williams, no run
text: good length ball on fifth stump, punched to extra cover.

shortText: van der Merwe to Williams, 2 runs
text: full on middle, flicked to wide long-on for a well placed and well run pair.

shortText: van der Merwe to Williams, 1 run
text: good length ball on off, tapped through extra cover for one.

Williams won't be posting this shot on the Instagram stories later tonight... Gentle flighted ball on fourth stump on a good length, tries an almighty slog, the length wasn't nearly full enough for the shot and the timber is rattled. Williams was batting with a cap on and immediately puts his hand over his face to express his personal disgust.
full on middle, jammed out.
full on middle, flicked to midwicket in the ring.
good length ball on off, guided to backward point.
good length ball slapped into the leg side for a pair.
full toss sails over Erasmus' head and the keeper too, they run a pair afterward.
good length ball defended into the off side.
full and driven to extra cover, diving stop by van der Merwe.
full on the stumps, Baard tries to flick across the line and misses, castled.
good length ball on middle, flicked to midwicket.
full on middle, flicked into midwicket.
full outside off, driven to cover.
good length on off stump, defended.

shortText: van der Merwe to Erasmus, SIX
text: Erasmus charges van der Merwe first ball of the over and drives this full ball high over long-off for a maximum.

shortText: van der Merwe to Erasmus, 1 run
text: good length ball outside off, slapped into the off side for one.

shortText: van der Merwe to Wiese, 1 run
text: good length ball on off, punched down the ground for one.

shortText: van der Merwe to Erasmus, 1 run
text: back of a length on sixth stump, slapped behind point for one.

shortText: van der Merwe to Wiese, SIX
text: Wiese charges him this time now and swings with a pendulum strike straight and high over van der Merwe 20 yards over the long-off rope.

shortText: van der Merwe to Wiese, 1 run
text: short on fifth stump, punched to the cover sweeper.

shortText: van der Gugten to Wiese, no run
text: back of length outside off, he defends it back

shortText: van der Gugten to Wiese, FOUR
text: strays towards leg and Wiese has no trouble in helping that long, off his pads, fine on the leg side for four

shortText: van der Gugten to Wiese, 1 run
text: much better line on off stump, punches this one down to long-on

shortText: van der Gugten to Erasmus, no run
text: nie and tight on length just outside off, he nudges it to point

shortText: van der Gugten to Erasmus, FOUR
text: gets just a bit of width and this time Erasmus deftly steers that away between point and short third man to bisect the gap

shortText: van der Gugten to Erasmus, 2 runs
text: slower one to end the over outside off and he punches it to deep cover. The ball isn't going too fast so they come back for a second
whacked over long-on! On length and turning into the batter, he lofts that high over long-on and into the stands
much shorter and towards middle and leg, this time he pulls behind square towards fine leg where the fielder dives to his right to save two
another six down the ground, this one is absolutely straight! Wiese is not leaving anything. Pitched up on off, right in the slot, and he lofts that straight down the ground
too short and turning in, Wiese will be unhappy with himself for not timing that well and straight to short fine leg
it's raining runs here! Short ball again, Wiese, with his wide stance, eyes the fine leg boundary again and this time gets four by middling it between short fine and deep square leg
short ball to end the over too, but not too much towards leg, he pulls it to deep square leg for one and keeps strike

shortText: van Beek to Wiese, no run
text: leading edge falls short of point! Wiese goes across to scoop it over the keeper but doesn't time it well and gets a leading edge towards point
full and slow, 114kmh, and the lack of pace won't deceive him because it's too full and he drives it all along the ground through the covers. The fielders can only watch

shortText: van Beek to Wiese, no run
text: thick inside edge past the stumps. He pokes outside off and only manages an edge that just misses the stumps before going to leg
tighter line from length towards middle and he flicks it across to leg for one
swings towards off but gets an edge to leg for one
punches the length ball down to mid-off for a quick single and he keeps strike
angling in towards the stumps, Wiese works it off the pads to deep midwicket for two
too much width and he dispatches that in the air and in no time past a diving backward point for a cracking four!
105kmh, digs this one out from off to cover for one more

shortText: de Leede to Erasmus, no run
text: 134kmh, strays towards leg and the bowler gets away with it. The ball deflects off the pad to the keeper
Erasmus gets an edge for four, he'll take that one. Slow and wide, cutting away further, Erasmus throws his hands at this one and it rolls away between the keeper and short third man
middles it for four more, make that 15 from the over! Wide and slightly full, Erasmus drives it square, in the gap and that races away for four more
big appeal from him first ball, the umpire doesn't move and Netherlands review. Angling in from around the wicket, hits him in front of middle and leg, and UltraEdge shows there's a spike for an edge
bit of pace and angle, worked off the pads to leg for one
in the air and past short third man for four! He slices it away outside off, it's gone in the air, but well wide of short third man
bit of a mix up but Erasmus makes it back just in time. Went off his pad to the off side, he took off for one, but was sent back almost immediately
uses the angle from middle and leg to deep midwicket for one
excellent stop at backward point with a dive to the right. Wiese steers the back of the hand slower ball to off and gets only one. But keeps strike
stifles him for room by bowling into the pads, he can't get it away
eyes the line outside off and Wiese dances down to hammer that over the cover boundary for another massive six. A stunning 29-ball fifty from Wiese
outside off and pushed into the covers for one
towards the stumps and he works it to leg for one
strikes him right in front, loud appeal but turned down! It's Wiese but they decide not to take the review. He slid it in with the angle so was maybe going down leg
comes down this time to work it to leg, struck on the pad again but well outside leg

shortText: van der Gugten to Erasmus, 1 run
text: pushes the length ball into the covers to get Wiese on strike

shortText: van der Gugten to Wiese, 2 runs
text: some width on the off side and he steers it square of the wicket in the gap for two. Reduces the gap further in the equation

shortText: van der Gugten to Wiese, SIX
text: smoked over wide long-on! Charges down with disdain, it's not a bad ball at all outside off, but the swing of his bat will take anything from along the way to beyond the boundary. What a strike

shortText: van der Gugten to Wiese, 1 run
text: patiently works this one from inside the crease to leg for one

shortText: van der Gugten to Erasmus, OUT
text: edged behind, the finger goes up, but Erasmus doesn't seem convinced. He thinks and eventually reviews it. The ball stayed a bit low outside off as Erasmus went after it, and got an under edge, UltraEdge confirms

shortText: van der Gugten to Smit, 1 run
text: drives the length ball into the covers for one
uses the angle to work the ball to leg from middle stump
deceives a charging Wiese with a slower ball, strikes him on the pad outside leg
124kmh, goes after it again but doesn't middle it at all and the ball lobs towards mid-on, the fielder is in the deep, and the bowler has to turn around and chase it. The batters run two meanwhile
charges and swings, but misses it completely this time as the ball goes just over the stumps. Klaassen looks and smiles

Wiese just can't connect anymore, and the credit goes to Klaassen. Angles in another slower ball, Wiese stays in this time and swings to leg, but is struck on the pad outside leg. They manage a leg bye
great end to a great spell, a dot ball as Smit swings to leg and misses as well
gets into position easily to scoop the length ball, doesn't connect, and screams for a leg bye as the ball deflects to short third man
some width outside off and he easily steers this wide of point in the gap. Easy two
too slow and wide outside off, not an extra Netherlands should be conceding right now

shortText: van Beek to Smit, no run
text: another wide delivery but Smit strikes it back and the bowler does well to get both hands to it between his legs
beats him outside off but it's well outside the wide line, second wide of the over!
smashes the back of length ball from off stump down the ground before long-on goes to his left and they get two
oh goodness, third wide in the over. Another one way outside off that's left easily
that should do it, all in Namibia's favour now as Smit stays still till the end before driving that short ball just wide of point right in the gap for four!
finishes it with an over to spare, thick edge runs away to the third man boundary for four more! Right in the block hole and Smit gets enough bat for a thick edge for four

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: some swing away, but early swing and starts a touch wide. Naim gets a sighter as he leaves it alone

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: this one swings away from closer. Naim gets behind it and defends

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: swing away from middle and off, hits the outside half of the bat

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: first attempt to look for runs as Bilal overpitches, but he plays it straight to short cover

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: back to swinging it away, pushed to point with an open face

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mohammad Naim, 1 wide
text: appeal for catch down the leg side but that's just an attempt to prevent the wide. The umpire, though, exercises his arms. Gets the line wrong as he bowls the change-up

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: short of a length, just outside off, runs it down to third man for one

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mohammad Naim, 1 wide
text: that is a harsh wide call. Short of a length, swinging away, beats him on the cut, and goes inside that blue line for wides

shortText: Kaleemullah to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: short of a length, tucks him up, defended back to him

shortText: Kaleemullah to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: beaten on the late cut as he looks to open the face away from the body
short of a length, opens the face to point, nobody is looking for a single, but Ilyas has a go from point and concedes an overthrow

shortText: Kaleemullah to Liton Das, no run
text: and he has been given caught at the wicket immediately, and he reviews immediately. Short of a length, outside off, seams away, he defends, the ball goes right next to the bat, but there is nothing on UltraEdge. Overturned. Liton stays
misfield at cover-point as he punches this nicely. Gets two for it
again some late movement away from just short of a length. Das runs it down to third man

shortText: Bilal Khan to Liton Das, 1 run
text: Das shimmies down, Bilal bowls a swinging yorker, appeals for an lbw for pad first, but the umpire is not interested. Another throw in from point, and another overthrow

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: first real attacking shot as he picks this off his toes, but he has found the man at deep square leg

shortText: Bilal Khan to Liton Das, no run
text: on a length, swinging in, defended back to him

shortText: Bilal Khan to Liton Das, 2 runs
text: dropped. Das looks for the big shot off the pads, gets a massive leading edge, Prajapati from deep midwicket runs to his right to reach deep square, but the ball pops out as he dives. Slower ball it is

shortText: Bilal Khan to Liton Das, OUT
text: appeal for pad first again as he gets late swing from a full length. Not given, and this time they review it. And it is pad first. Wow this looks really tight now. It is hitting the middle of middle. Das really late to adjust to the swing. What a review

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mahedi Hasan, no run
text: late swing again, ending up on off and middle, pushed back to him

shortText: Kaleemullah to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: short of a length, around off, pushed to short cover

shortText: Kaleemullah to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: short of a length, wicket to wicket, played back to him. Excellent bowling. Giving him nothing to work with
slightly too short, and ever so slightly mind you. Not wide either, but Naim makes him own room and length by arching back and late-cuts it past point
overcompensates, bowls on a length, and straight, and Neem is waiting. Clears the front leg and lifts it over midwicket for six

shortText: Kaleemullah to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: on a length, just outside off, 132ks, beats him as he looks to go over cover

shortText: Kaleemullah to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: back to short of a length with no room. No option but to defend it back

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mahedi Hasan, no run
text: and straight away beats him for pace. Recorded 135ks on the gun, but Mahedi is late into his defensive shot outside off

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mahedi Hasan, no run
text: opens the face on this, but can't get it past point

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mahedi Hasan, OUT
text: stunning return catch. Mahedi out of sorts against his pace. He tries the big shot back over his head, and is late into it. Lobs it softly to the left of Fayyaz, who changes direction in follow-through and dives to complete the catch

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR
text: quick again, Shakib late on this full toss, but gets a thick edge wide of slip for four

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: full-length dive in his follow-through again, this time to field a drive from Shakib

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: on a length, angling in, quick, played back to Fayyaz, who looks for a reverse flick at the non-striker's behind him, but doesn't let the ball go

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: short of a length, no room, pushed to cover

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: seam movement back in from short of a length. Extra bounce too. Runs off his glove for one to square leg

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: Shakib shapes up for the ramp, Nadeem sees him and goes wide outside off. Draws a defensive shot

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: this one swings in from middle and leg. Tucked away for a single to short fine leg

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: seam movement and extra bounce again, Naim gets a single off the soft inside edge

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: takes the quick single to mid-off as he pitches this up just outside off

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: short of a length, angling in, tucked away off the hip for one

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: short of a length, 140ks, outside off, runs this down to third man for one

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: late on the pull. It goes dangerously towards deep square leg but falls well short of the man. Bowled at 136ks this time

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mohammad Naim, 2 runs
text: pitches this up, and Naim drives it with an open face past cover. Gets two. The outfield is slow

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mohammad Naim, SIX
text: another catch dropped. Oman have been great with the ball but their fielding has been letting them down. It was ground fielding the other day but it is catching today. This is dug in short, Naim cuts this in the air and in front of square. Jatinder runs to his left from deep point, gets to it, but can't hold on. Just the awkward height for him around chest and he is also on the run. Ends up parrying it over the rope

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: single to mid-off this time

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: another slower ball, pitched up on off, driven to the left of deep cover. Ayaan makes sure they get just the one with a run to his left and a one-handed pick-up and throw

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mohammad Naim, 1 wide
text: slower ball, well down leg, called wide

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: flashes at this short-of-a-length delivery and is beaten. On-pace this time

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: short of a length, no room, runs this down to third man for one

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: gets the width on this shortish delivery, goes hard at it, but is beaten by the bounce

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: dropped again. Prajapati again. Naim makes room to pull, smacks it clean, but straight to midwicket, where it goes in and out. Prajapati then looks for the direct hit, and poor backing up allows them an overthrow

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: tries the big hit to a length ball outside off, beaten as he ends up playing inside the line

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: short of a length, pulled down to long-on for one

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR
text: too short this time, and Shakib rocks back to pull this between deep square leg and long-on

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: Ilyas stays short again, and Shakib makes room to cut him to deep cover for one

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: on a length this time, punched down to long-off

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: down the wicket to drive this to long-on

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: goes back to punch this to deep cover
extra bounce from his high release, hit to deep cover for one

shortText: Kaleemullah to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR
text: plays the ramp this time, and this time he doesn't give it away early. Makes a late decision to shuffle across and helps this length ball over short fine leg

shortText: Kaleemullah to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: on a length, wide, Shakib tries the big cover drive, and is beaten

shortText: Kaleemullah to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: runs this down to third man for one
slower ball, 94ks, short of a length, wicket to wicket, pulled to deep square leg for one

shortText: Kaleemullah to Shakib Al Hasan, 2 runs
text: mid-off is up so he looks for a drive over him as he pitches this on a length. Doesn't make a clean connection but manages to clear the infield

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: fuller on off, crisply driven but straight to extra cover

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Mohammad Naim, 1 bye
text: short and wide outside off, didn't bounce as much, he was giving himself room to cut, gets an under-edge. There was only a blink of an eye for the keeper to react, and it brushed the fingertips of his gloves

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR
text: lifts this over the extra cover fielder, made room and carved it inside out, lots of power behind that shot.

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: a bit short, rocks back to pull but gets an under-edge that bounces near boot.

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Shakib Al Hasan, 2 runs
text: fuller on the stumps, takes a step forward and drills it past the bowler with a full bat face. They sprint hard and make it two runs

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: down the track again, the length is a bit shorter this time, worked to long-on

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR
text: down the track again and that's a stunner of a shot. Was giving himself room, the ball was bowled into him, but he holds shape and punches it past mid-off and into the boundary with a peachy shot.

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR
text: Shakib really on the attack here. Was struggling for timing early on but he's picking the gaps now, even if the timing is not pristine. Dropped short, he swivels and short-arm jabs a pull through backward square leg

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: back of a length going across him, clipped through midwicket

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mohammad Naim, SIX
text: wham. Too short, and on the stumps, sat up, and he goes on the back foot to slug it across the line for a home-run over deep midwicket

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mohammad Naim, 2 runs
text: clears short fine leg with his scoop. Premeditated the shot, going forward and across, got it off the end of the bat but lifted it well clear of the fielder

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: swing and a miss. Length ball going across him, he was looking to drive on the up through cover

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Shakib Al Hasan, 2 runs
text: short and wide outside off to start, crashed through extra cover. It's not wide enough of the fielder in the deep, who can cut it off to his right

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: flatter outside off, thumped to long-off

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Mohammad Naim, FOUR
text: reverse swept for four past short third man. This was bowled well across him, he changed stance and swung it past the fielder

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: clipped through midwicket

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: yorker on the stumps, dug out towards cover

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Mohammad Naim, 1 leg bye
text: yorker length on leg stump, rolls off the pad towards short fine leg as he misses the glance

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mohammad Naim, 2 runs
text: dug in short of a length, seemed to hold a bit in the surface, no timing on the pull shot but it drops well short of the deep midwicket fielder

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: bouncer well clear of off stump, he was looking to slap it through the offside, but doesn't get on top of it well, and it goes off the under edge towards short third man

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT
text: brilliant direct hit at the bowler's end. Ilyas from point has run Shakib out just when he was cutting loose. This was a great ball too, yorker homing in on off stump, carved towards point and they set off for a single. But after a so far forgettable day in the field, Oman turn it around with a moment of brilliance.

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: given room outside off and it's too short too, crashed through point but there's protection in the deep

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Nurul Hasan, 1 run
text: some shape on the ball from Fayyaz, very full length on the stumps, clipped to deep midwicket. There's one run short because Naim didn't cross the line at the keepr's end while stretching out his bat. It was a tight two runs, and in the hurry to take it, he didn't stretch enough

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Nurul Hasan, 1 run
text: nearly another run out. Steered to point and they set off for another risky single. There's another shy at the stumps, but it misses this time. They think about taking another run on the overthrow but decide against it. Ilyas again the fielder.

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Nurul Hasan, 1 run
text: length outside off, opens the face to hit to point

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Mohammad Naim, FOUR
text: thumped back hard and straight to raise fifty. Full on the stumps, clears his front leg and absolutely drills it. No time for the bowler to react with the ball already past him as he got his hands up.

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Mohammad Naim, no run
text: smashed again but Zeeshan stops it with his left leg, stretching it out, almost by reflex

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Mohammad Naim, 2 runs
text: swept through square, and Kashyap has to run hard to his left and cut it off before it crosses the boundary

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: down the track, gets to the pitch of a flat delivery and slugs it across the line to deep midwicket

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Nurul Hasan, OUT
text: caught at long-off. Oman hold on to a catch. Stepped out to go over the top, didn't get it right off the middle though, and the ball didn't have the distance on it. Drops safely into the hands of a waiting fielder.

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mohammad Naim, SIX
text: launched over long-on. Full in the slot, clears his front leg a tad and plays the lofted drive with one hand coming off the bat, carries all the way over long-on

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mohammad Naim, 1 run
text: yorker on the stumps, goes deep in his crease to jam it to long-on

shortText: Bilal Khan to Afif Hossain, no run
text: yorker goes through him outside off. Goes between bat and body as he was looking to steer it

shortText: Bilal Khan to Afif Hossain, no run
text: there's some noise as the ball passes the batter, swinging down leg, and Oman think there's bat on that. With one second left, they go for the review for caught behind. Think it flicked the pad and no bat there. Replays confirm no bat on that, just pad. Oman lose one review.

shortText: Bilal Khan to Afif Hossain, no run
text: nicely done, saw him backing away and dug it in short, goes over the stumps and over his bat as he's flailing at that

shortText: Bilal Khan to Afif Hossain, 1 run
text: another yorker outside off, driven off the inside half to long-on. Excellent comeback from Bilal after the first ball of the over went for six
caught at the extra cover boundary. Full ball angled across him, this was squirted off the leading edge and went very high. Jatinder under it, and he's nicely in position to gather it safely.
swatted across the line, no timing on that, goes over the bowler and bounces well in front of long-off
slower ball, shape away from him, very full outside off, swung to deep square leg

caught at deep midwicket. Oman now catching everything. Bouncer dug into the surface, came slower onto him than he expected, and he ends up playing the pull too early, only for the ball to balloon to the fielder for a comfortable take.
length ball, very straight, tucked off his pads to deep midwicket
gorgeous. Given a bit of width outside off with a ball that's slightly back of length and he cuts it beautifully through backward point

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mahmudullah, no run
text: down the track, looks to smash through off, swing and a miss to a length ball in the channel
fuller on the stumps, flicked through backward square leg

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: rocks back to pull this through midwicket, but there's protection in the deep there so it's just a single
boom. Too short and he's swivelled to pull this way over square leg. Magnificent contact with the ball.
back of a length slower ball on off, mis-times his pull to deep midwicket

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run
text: fuller on off, driven to extra cover, they take the quick single. Shy at the stumps is wide, could have been close with a direct hit. Would have been out in fact. Jatinder had only one stump to aim at.

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mushfiqur Rahim, OUT
text: he's dabbed that straight to the keeper. Got a little bigger on him than he expected, and was a slower ball too. Superbly done by Fayyaz, what a key strike that is. Back of a length slower ball that kept rising, and Mushfiqur was looking to steer it very fine, ends up steering it right into the keeper's gloves.

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 wide
text: went for the wide line outside off, and the umpire thinks Mushfiqur hasn't moved enough, so that's a wide. Was outside the tramline and Mushfiqur did move, but from outisde leg stump to in front of the stumps

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Mohammad Saifuddin, OUT
text: caught at long-off. Length ball outside off, Saifuddin gave him the charge first ball, slaps it in the air, without timing, and it's travelled straight down Jatinder's throat. Another catch for him.

not the best delivery to bowl for an attempted hat-trick, sliding on the pads and Mahmudullah clips it fine. Good sliding effort by the man running to his right to fine leg to pull it in just before it hits the boundary cushions.
back of a length slower ball outside off, chopped towards point

shortText: Fayyaz Butt to Taskin Ahmed, 1 bye
text: well bowled, but they concede a single through a bye. Slower bouncer outside off again, Tasking has a heave at it and can't connect, but the keeper can't collect cleanly and it goes to short third man
stays very still and cuts this beautifully through backward point for a boundary. Back of a length outside off

shortText: Bilal Khan to Taskin Ahmed, 4 leg byes
text: keeps it full and straight but Taskin is moving across and it flicks the outside off his pad and goes very fine, past the keeper, for four leg-byes

shortText: Bilal Khan to Taskin Ahmed, 1 run
text: yorker outside off, he's deep in his crease and gets low to drive this to extra cover. Zeeshan dives to his right to stop it

knocked him over. Went around the wicket to Mahmudullah and nailed a yorker on off stump, tailing into him too. Mahmudullah flays at it with feet static and the ball sneaks through to crash into the stumps

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mustafizur Rahman, no run
text: quicker bouncer on the stumps, he's looking to arch out of the way while ramping it over the keeper, can't connect with the ball

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mustafizur Rahman, 2 runs
text: backing away, he bowls it in the blockhole, inside edge goes to fine leg as he's looking to drive

shortText: Bilal Khan to Mustafizur Rahman, OUT
text: Bilal gets a wicket with the final ball. Captain Maqsood catches it at long-off. Fizz backed away and swiped hard at this, got way more height than distance on it, and Oman end an innings marked by dropped chances with one safely taken.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Aqib Ilyas, 2 runs
text: good timing right away as he opens the face on this short-of-a-length ball, placing it between point and cover-point

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Aqib Ilyas, FOUR
text: Oman not in a mood to mess around. Tasking strays a touch, and Ilyas plays a pick-up shot over square leg for four. A plum length ball on the pads at 142ks

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: beaten as this one holds its line outside off. Short of a length, 143ks, slight seam movement away, opens him up as he defends

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Aqib Ilyas, 1 leg bye
text: down the leg side with fine leg up and he is lucky to get away with just the leg-bye

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Jatinder Singh, 2 runs
text: Jatinder goes after him first up. This is short of a length, 143ks, and he just pulls it. Gets a top edge but clears the infield

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Aqib Ilyas, 1 leg bye
text: short of a length, 143ks, into the pads, goes for a leg-bye

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Jatinder Singh, 2 wides
text: down the leg side again, and Nurul Hasan does really well to save four extras. Just one wide, and one on the run. He has saved three here

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Aqib Ilyas, OUT
text: appeal for pad-first and is given. Ilyas reviews it. On-pace again, and it looked like pad first to me live time. Replays confirm it is pad first. This is on a length, pitches on leg, swings back in against the angle to be hitting off. Small swing, late swing. Oman's review is gone

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Aqib Ilyas, 1 wide
text: short of a length, on-pace, wide down the leg side

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Prajapati, no run
text: small swing, late swing again, and headed for middle and leg. Defended back to him, but he is a little late on it

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Prajapati, no run
text: another appeal for lbw, but not given. This one hasn't swung, which suggests this has pitched outside leg. Prajapati is setting off for a leg-bye that is not on, and a direct hit from point would have sent him back. Missed by inches

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Prajapati, no run
text: back to pitching it up and heading for off and middle, pushed to mid-off this time
short of a length, good wheels, good carry, 137ks, but outside leg
another wide down the leg side

flicked away for a six. Prajapati doesn't hold back. Mustafizur goes wide on the crease, but ends up bowling a juicy length ball on the pads. He picks it up flat over the deep square leg. There is a fielder in place there, but he clears him
another wide down the leg side. He is struggling to control the movement
slower ball, fuller, outside off, opens the face, gets a single
slower ball, and it starts outside leg and doesn't cut enough for this to not be called a wide

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Prajapati, no run
text: late movement away, Prajapati looks to open the face, and is beaten

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Prajapati, no run
text: have they missed a run-out?. Ordinary cricket from both sides. Prajapati calls no early but Jatinder takes an eternity to turn around. Shakib from cover-point lobs a throw back to Saifuddin who is running back, but he fails to collect it cleanly. The throw is so slow, though, that Jatinder would probably have made it

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Prajapati, no run
text: opens the face, can't get it past cover-point
dropped. They have the short third man pretty man, and that is where this edge goes as Prajapati plays a loose drive to an outswinger. Mustafizur dives to his left but is never in control of it

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: opens the face, but sends this straight to the short third man

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: full toss, hit hard, but long-on is back to keep it down to one

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: flat, on a length, pushed to cover

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, FOUR
text: switch-hit. That is a shot he likes to play. Takes this from outside leg and sends it high of the leaping Mahedi at cover-point

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: Shakib sees Jatinder coming and slows it down, Jatinder recovers to defend

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: short of a length, outside off, hit hard to mid-off for a single

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Prajapati, no run
text: forward-defensive as Shakib bowls on a length

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Prajapati, 2 runs
text: only slightly short of a length, and he goes back to whip this over midwicket. The slow outfield allows deep square leg to come around and field

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: he walks down the wicket to punch this length ball down to long-on for one

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Prajapati, no run
text: beaten outside off. Bowled at 128ks but this one zips off the surface from a length outside off. There is some seam movement to be had here
falls between two converging men. On a length, on the pads, he looks to go big on the leg side but gets a leading edge, which falls between deep square and the man running back from inside the circle

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: length ball, hit hard, across the line, but can't get it past midwicket

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Prajapati, no run
text: Prajapati has done well here. Defends a length ball, which is rolling back onto the stumps even as he looks for one. So he recovers quickly and rushes back to hit the ball away from the stumps. Just in the nick of time
on the up, and over mid-off. He doesn't have any room to play this short-of-a-length ball, but he goes hard nonetheless and clears mid-off

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: dropped. What are Bangladesh up to here? He does him in with a lovely slower ball, Jatinder gets a massive top edge, there are three-four men who can take this including the bowler, but Mahmudullah claims it running in from extra cover. He gets under it, but the hands don't come up right and he is hit in the chest

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Prajapati, no run
text: quicker, middle and leg, defended back to him
he has a fielder back for this, and Mustafizur goes short. This is not the sweetest connection, but the ground is not big enough to keep this in

Mustafizur finally gets a wicket. On a length, quick, angling across, takes the edge as Prajapati is late on the drive. The keeper takes the catch. Some relief around but Bangladesh know their campaign is in jeopardy right now

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: on a length, outside off, left alone

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: on a length, angling in, defended back to him

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: Jatinder down the wicket, not to its pitch, defends

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, FOUR
text: long hop with no deep midwicket, and Jatinder goes back to pull it over the infield for an easy boundary

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, SIX
text: beautiful batting. Down the wicket to a widish length ball, goes inside-out and over extra cover for a six. He is doing this to the best allrounder in the world. Perhaps not in this format but still

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: quicker, flatter, he goes back and punches this to extra cover

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: on a length, into the pads, defended to short midwicket

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: beats him in the air as he slows this down. Jatinder drives with hard hands but the uppish mis-hit doesn't reach the cover fielder on the full

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: short of a length, quick, played straight to short midwicket

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: flat, wide, beats him on the late-cut

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: on a length, still quick, can't beat short straight midwicket

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: gets the late-cut this time, but can't beat backward point. Six straight dots for Zeeshan

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Zeeshan Maqsood, 1 run
text: slight turn outside off, pushed wide of short cover for a single

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: pull from down on a knee, can't get it past short fine leg. Takes the single, though

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: short of a length, quick, skiddy, squeezes under his pull

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: proper bouncer now, 138ks, Jatinder looks to pull, gets the cue end and down it goes on its way to the keeper

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: short of a length, 140ks, and it goes back just as fast as Jatinder pulls it down to long-on

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Zeeshan Maqsood, 1 run
text: beaten for pace but he survives. he is really late on the pull on this one, but the top edge lands in backward square leg region with no one around to catch it

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Jatinder Singh, FOUR
text: stays short, at 142ks, but Jatinder is waiting for it and pulls this past midwicket for four. Much-needed boundary

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: full for the first time this over, strays down the leg side, and is clipped away for a single

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: low, round-arm delivery, driven to long-on for one

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: on a length, on off, pushed back to him

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Zeeshan Maqsood, 1 run
text: slows this dow, draws the outside edge, but there is no slip. Zeeshan gets off strike

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: yorks him up with a quick delivery as Jatinder looks to whip this to leg

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: drags the length back as Jatinder gives him the charge. He pulls regardless and gets it to deep square leg on the bounce

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Zeeshan Maqsood, 1 run
text: on a length, into the pads, worked away for a single

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Zeeshan Maqsood, 1 run
text: short to start with, pulled forcefully through square. There's a fielder at deep square leg

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: pace off, hard length outside off, he waits for it and steers it to short third man

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Zeeshan Maqsood, SIX
text: that's a super strike. Full ball on the pads and just picked up effortlessly to deposit it way over square leg. Amazing timing on that. Bad ball alright, but he took toll beautifully

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Zeeshan Maqsood, 1 run
text: back of a length on the stumps, opened him up a bit but he is behind the ball enough to push it towards short cover from the outside half of the bat

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: drilled back hard, good looking straight drive with the full face of the bat, but Taskin gets hands to it to take the pace off. Ball parried to his right to keep them to a single

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Zeeshan Maqsood, no run
text: dug in short on leg stump, ducks under it

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: takes a couple of steps down the track and flicks it from outside off through midwicket

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Zeeshan Maqsood, OUT
text: great catch by Mustafizur at deep square leg. Full outside off, Zeeshan goes for the slog-sweep, bat coming down in a big arc, but the ball is a bit too wide to connect cleanly. Gets a top edge that's swirling to Fizz's right, he moves with it and ends up having to dive and catch it, holds on.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: fullish outside off, worked towards wide long-on

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Ayaan Khan, no run
text: angled into him, clipped towards midwicket's right, Mahmudullah makes a tumbling stop

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Ayaan Khan, no run
text: fuller outside off, defended on the front foot

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Ayaan Khan, no run
text: darted in fuller at him, pushes it gently into the offside and wants the quick single, sent back

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, FOUR
text: great shot. Shakib strayed on legside, and dragged it short, he went down on his knees and swept it fine enough to beat the fielder behind square on the boundary.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: quicker and flatter on off stump, punched to long-off

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Ayaan Khan, 1 run
text: fuller outside off, swept hard, but straight to deep midwicket, who collects on the bounce

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, 1 run
text: reverse-swept, bit of premeditation in that, but the ball was on leg stump and there for the shot. NOt much percentage to the risk though because there's a deep square leg there

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Ayaan Khan, 1 run
text: down the track and squirted off the outside edge over cover

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Jatinder Singh, OUT
text: he's timed it beautifully but straight to deep square leg. Huge wicket. Went down on one knee again and swept it hard. More square than his boundary first ball of the over, and Liton Das moves quickly to his left and gets into position nicely to pouch it. Bangladesh's best has taken out Oman's best batter.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Ayaan Khan, 2 runs
text: flicked through midwicket and they push hard to get two

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Ayaan Khan, 1 run
text: flatter o nthe stumps, whipped to long-on

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Sandeep Goud, 2 runs
text: outside edge runs through a vacant first slip region. Pushing forward to one inside the line, gets a clear edge. Fizz runs after it and pulls it in before the boundary

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Sandeep Goud, no run
text: tapped to the bowler's right

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Sandeep Goud, no run
text: he could be stumped here. Beaten outside off again, drawn on the front foot and feeling for the ball, which goes past the outside edge. Has he dragged his back foot out while moving forward? The keeper thinks so. He removed the bails quickly and appealed with a lot of excitement. However, Goud's foot was grounded all the way through.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Sandeep Goud, 1 run
text: full toss drifting on the pads, glanced to backward square leg

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Sandeep Goud, no run
text: length ball jags back in and scoots along the ground almost, between his poking bat and the stumps

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Sandeep Goud, 1 run
text: length ball on off, squirted towards short third man and they sprint the quick single

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Ayaan Khan, 2 runs
text: short on the stumps, with pace off, he controls his pull and places it clear of short fine leg. Quick running again to get two

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Ayaan Khan, no run
text: back of a length going across him, he's looking to pull and makes no connection with the ball

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Ayaan Khan, no run
text: another back of length ball going across him, and Ayaan not reading the slower ball, into the pull too early again and makes no contact

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Ayaan Khan, 1 run
text: this is shorter and rises up to shoulder height, he gets bat on the pull  and gets a single to deep midwicket

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Ayaan Khan, 1 run
text: full ball going across him, heaved to long-on along the ground

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Sandeep Goud, no run
text: yorker speared on an off stump line, jams his bat down to keep it out

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Sandeep Goud, OUT
text: short and wide outside off, slaps it straight to cover. Was a little away from body and he had to reach for it, gets it on the end of the bat

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Naseem Khushi, no run
text: excellent ball first up, yorker on the stumps, dug back out past the bowler

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Naseem Khushi, 2 runs
text: slower ball, short outside off, throws his weight into a pull shot to deep square leg. Some hesitation before they take the second, but the throw from the deep is not accurate so they're safe

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Naseem Khushi, 1 run
text: was looking to go across and paddle-scoop it fine but ends up just directing it towards third man

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Naseem Khushi, no run
text: Misses the flick to a leg-side ball, that flicks pad and goes to keeper

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Naseem Khushi, 1 run
text: length outside off, punched to long-off

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Ayaan Khan, OUT
text: thumped straight to long-off. Shakib keeps it wide outside off, Ayaan has a big swat at it, can't really middle it and it goes straight down Mahmudullah's throat

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Naseem Khushi, OUT
text: and he's holed out too. Full ball on the stumps, lofts the drive over the bowler's head, but he's not made good enough connection to clear the boundary riders, and long-off moves to his right to grab it smartly

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Mohammad Nadeem, 1 run
text: length ball on the stumps, pushes forward and gets a thick inside edge to square leg

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Kaleemullah, 1 run
text: parried on the deep midwicket boundary by Mahmudullah to prevent a boundary. Short ball, thwacked powerfully, but Mahmudullah does well to run to his right and push it back in
full ball on the stumps, he just moved his front leg out of the way and threw the kitchen sink at this ball, drills it straight back. Hit hard enough that neither long-on nor long-off can cut it off
going across him, wide yorker outside off, he can't make contact looking to get bat horizontal and slap it square

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Kaleemullah, no run
text: off-cutter with pace reduced outside off, he's looking to swing over cow corner, connects only with air.

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Kaleemullah, no run
text: goes across him again, length a bit shorter, batter opens his stance and looks to scythe it through offside now but still can't connect

brilliantly caught by the keeper. Fizz keeps it slanting across the batter and this time Kareemullah gets some bat on it, but it's an edge off the bottom of the bat that is flying to Nurul's right. He puts some air-time of his own to dive full length to his right and get glove around the ball.

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Fayyaz Butt, no run
text: another swing and a miss to one going across him on a length

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Fayyaz Butt, OUT
text: tame catch to extra cover. Dug in short and going across him, he gets it on the low part of the bat while playing a half-pull, half-square drive, and the ball pops up for a simple catch

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Mohammad Nadeem, 2 runs
text: length ball outside off, nicely steered to third man. Good timing but the outfield is heavy with dew so the ball will not reach the boundary

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Mohammad Nadeem, no run
text: yorker on the stumps, clipped towards mid-on

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Mohammad Nadeem, no run
text: back of a length, wide outside off stump, goes for an expansive cut, doesn't connect

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Mohammad Nadeem, no run
text: full on the stumps, drilled to long-off. He's not going to take the single

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Mohammad Nadeem, 1 run
text: another full ball, makes room and drives to long-off again. Takes the single now, leaving one ball for Bilal to face

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Bilal Khan, no run
text: yorker outside off, keeps it out, defending towards mid-off

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Mohammad Nadeem, FOUR
text: nice hit. Full on the stumps and he clumps a cover drive over the in-field. Leaping Mushfiqur can't get near it and it thuds into the boundary

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Mohammad Nadeem, 1 wide
text: angling across him again but this is a touch wide of the tramline, and he'll have to rebowl that.

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Mohammad Nadeem, no run
text: full on the stumps, defended to cover. Not going to take the single so early in the over

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Mohammad Nadeem, no run
text: big heave to one going outside off, and he can't connect with the ball
full and speared into the pads, misses a flick to the leg side, big lbw shout denied. Likely missing leg. No thought really given to go for DRS.
full ball sprayed down the leg side for an extra to get off the mark.

full length on middle and leg, goes for a helicopter flick high over midwicket, one bounce over the rope to just beat Sese Bau's effort trying to slap this back into play running to his right from deep square leg.
back of a length on the body, flicks this off the hips behind square for one.
full on middle and leg, flicks this straight to mid-on.
classy! Length ball slanted across fifth stump, punched square on the up through cover point and races to the rope.
overpitched on middle, driven firmly wide of mid-on, tumbling stop on the ring to keep it to one.
good length ball on off, flicked through midwicket for one.
follows him backing away from leg with a quicker ball, jams him trying to drive.
shuffles outside off stump to sweep this powerfully behind square and splits the gap with square leg and short fine leg.
rinse and repeat! Shuffle across again for another orthodox sweep behind square, this time lofted over the ring to the rope.
short on fifth stump, punched flat through mid-on for a pair.
full on the pads, goes for another sweep but mistimes this and it dribbles behind square.
full on the stumps, driven to midwicket.

clever slower ball castles Coetzer! Morea isn't express by any means but even his subtle change of pace with a touch of inswing has fooled the Scotland captain and beats him with.a huge gap out in front of a drive between bat and pad.
good length ball on off, defended into the off side.
full on the stumps, defended again into the off side.
inswinger on a good length on middle and off, slices this to backward point.
inswinging yorker on middle and off, jams this out off an inside edge back down the pitch for one.
good length ball on fifth stump, punched behind point and the cover sweeper can't deny a second.
back of a length on fifth stump, goes to cut and a bottom edge misses leg stump through square leg for one.
full on fourth stump, driven to backward point.

full on fifth stump, skies a leg side heave and gets a big top edge to deep square leg. Hangs in the air forever but falls safely into the hands of the fielder settling in 15 yards inside the rope. Too easy for Lega Siaka.
back of a length on middle, goes back to flick behind square leg.

back of a length on the hips, goes to flick off his pads and misses as the ball dribbles wide to the left of the keeper Doriga, who shuffles to collect and fire at the stumps but Cross would've been safely in regardless of a direct hit.
full inswinger on middle and leg, flicked behind square for one.
slower ball full on fourth stump, blocked to extra cover.
inswinger on a good length on middle and off, jammed out into the covers off an inside edge into the pads.
overpitched on fourth stump, pressed firmly through mid-off and it makes it to the rope despite a vain dive by Vanua tracking from long-on.
peach! Scrambled seam this time as this one goes on with the angle on fourth stump and beats Cross on an attempted punch through cover on the up.
good length inswinger on off, defended to backward point.
good length ball outside off, punched into the off side to extra cover.
good length ball defended to cover.
short on the body, pulls this firmly behind square for a boundary.
back of a length on the pads, mistimes this off an inside edge into the pads before a carom to cover.
good length ball on fifth stump, beaten trying to drive.
good length ball outside off, beaten again going to cut.
flighted full on the pads, misses a sweep and comes off the pads behind square for one.
flighted full on off and defended to cover.
flighted full on off, smothered on the front foot.
uses his feet for the first time and clubs this high and mighty over long-on sailing for a humongous six.
googly for the first time today landing on a good length on fourth stump, defended late on the back foot.
flighted full on sixth stump, shuffles across to sweep behind square.
full on fourth stump, driven to long-off for one.
short on the stumps, pulled flat through midwicket and splits the boundary riders to the rope.
full on off, nudged gently into the covers for one.
googly lands short on off, goes back to flick into mid-on.
good length ball on fourth stump, punched in front of cover.
full on off, driven firmly to long-off.
full on the pads, flicked behind square for one.
full on middle, tap and run for a tight single into extra cover.
slower ball full on the legs, flicked through square leg for one.
full on off stump, driven firmly to long-off for one.
slower ball full on the legs, misses a flick as the ball goes off the pads in front of point for an extra.
good length ball on off, punched into the covers for one.
full on the stumps, flicked gently through mid-on and chased down by the bowler.
good length ball on off, goes back to flick into deep midwicket for a long single.
good length ball on the pads, goes back to flick into midwicket.
short on fourth stump, goes back to cut to the cover sweeper.
full on the stumps, uses his feet and punches into mid-on for one.
full on middle, driven to extra cover for a tight run.
tucked into the onside
that was a long hop, but he gets away with it. The hoick to cow corner finds the fielder on the bounce
clattered back along the ground
gorgeous shot. Too much flight from Amini, allowing Berrington to move to the leg side and thump it inside out over extra cover
a little nudge gets him off strike
that brings up the 50 partnership - what a way to do it, too. Smears it over midwicket all the way for a huge six
swept to short leg, but the fielder collects
another mighty swipe to the cow corner region - Berrington is coming into his own now. Disappointed not to clear the ropes with that
a little dab to long-on, and magnificent running that. Called two straight away, and gets there in the end
slashed into the offside
slightly short and very flat. Driven to extra cover
this one's right in the slot, allowing Berrington to wallop it over long-off for another massive six
rolled his fingers over it, driven to long on
streaky. Danced down the ground but only got a little inside edge, fine of short fine, and that goes away for four. Little PNG could have done about that
gives this a crack but doesn't get a hold of it. Just one to midwicket
pulled away to square leg, and they call two right away once more. Get there comfortably. Scotland are now beginning to turn it on
ho-ho! Now Cross gets into the action. Read the slower ball very well, and clobbered it over cow corner for another big six
Poor cricket from PNG. Terrible delivery, full toss at pace on the leg stump. It's smashed to fine leg, where a misfield allows Scotland to pick up another boundary! They are racing away from PNG now
Clapped back to long-on. Poor delivery but very good fielding at long-on prevents another four
driven to deep extra cover
dragged down legside
gives that a crack down the ground, long-on collects
saw Berrington racing down the track and pulled his length back. Clever bowling
just a single, and a rare good over for PNG. Can they finish it well now?
they can - it's just a single. PNG needed that badly
starts with a rank bad ball that he gets away with, because it's smashed straight to the man at cow corner
much better length. Fuller without being overpitched. Driven through the offside for one

another bad ball, and failing to put these away has cost Scotland in the end. Cross smeared it straight to cow corner once more, but this time right down his throat. Atai picks up a wicket PNG scarcely deserved, and Cross is apoplectic as he departs
starts off with a slash to cover
good ball, angling back into him, cut away to get him off the mark
driven to long-off to round out a successful over for PNG. Can they build on this as the death overs approach?
brings up his half century. Slashes it away past third man
sends that well wide of off stump, will have to reload that
half-volley, sliced to the offside. Thought about two, but it wasn't on this time
wicket-to-wicket from around the stumps, driven right back at the bowler
that was a weird shot, wasn't it? Walks out a few steps, and reverse sweeps it. perfectly splitting short third and backward point. That was more of a hockey shot, and placed to absolute perfection
and after that nonsense, gets himself off strike

this is just very ordinary bowling. Again, it's bowled at pace, on a half-volley length, just begging Berrington to clobber it. He's happy to oblige, this time right back over the bowler's head, and Scotland continue their merry progress
guided back down to long-on
lots of bottom hand in that smear over midwicket. But not quite the timing, allowing Amini to cut it off and keep it to two
slightly back of a length, cross batted back to Soper, who stops it from going past him

Berrington's just in the zone, that is a jaw-droppingly good shot. Wasn't quite that bad a length, but he cleared his front leg and absolutely smoked it over long-on for an 87m six!. They're racing towards a huge score
slow ball banged into the surface - that really is the way to go here. He has no pace to work with and can only muscle it away to the onside for one
uppish pull to square leg, but it bounces before reaching the fielder
comes around the wicket, wide full toss. Sliced to extra cover, where Tony Ura puts in a dive, but it's just short of him
good ball - a perfect yorker. That's impossible to get underneath. But the margin for error is so tiny with that option
two in a row - this one's on leg stump. Near topples the man over once it strikes his pads. Huge appeal, and while that's never out, it's a great start to the over
glorious bowling. He moved across to the offstump to try and guide it over short fine. But the yorker's perfect once more, and MacLeod gets nowhere with his attempt
a little misfield off his own bowling - it was another brilliant full delivery

missed his length this time; it was a juicy full toss. But Berrington misses out, and you might argue the bowler's earned his bit of luck with the clinic he just put out this over. Brilliant from PNG, and timely too.
slower ball banged into the wicket. Swipe to cow corner; he's annoyed he hasn't found the gap there

the extra bounce off the wicket dooms him. Bounced up high after he banged it into the wicket, and MacLeod couldn't get hon top of his heave to the onside. Instead it balloons up into the air, and midwicket completes a smart catch to send him on his way
a little bottom edge sneaks past the keeper, allowing them to come back for a couple. Good over so far once more

he's got rid of Berrington, too! He caught that very cleanly on the bat, did the Scot, but when it flew to Amini at long-on, so did the PNG player! Much too flat to clear the rope, and Scotland are falteringly slightly as the innings draws to a close
slower ball, pulled to midwicket
just a single, and that concludes a superb spell from Chad Soper. Included today, he's really made a difference to his side at a time when it was very rough going for the PNG bowlers
gets away with it. Wide yorker, but a metre further wide of backward point would have got Scotland four more
that ball was almost delivered in slow motion. Absolutely glacial, but he still couldn't get bat on it. Ran a bye, though, that's how long it took to get to the keeper. And it's a no-ball!
got the broom out to sweep it through the onside, but skies it, does Greaves. Siaka in the field had a little wobble, but managed to catch it on the second attempt
he misses his length, and for once, Scotland make PNG pay. It was a slow full toss outside off, allowing Leask enough time to step across and heave it over midwicket for six
this one doesn't quite have the same connection. Dropped safe enough, but Leask insisted on coming back for a second run that was never on, and got himself run out in the process
looked like he's connected cleanly enough. It was a half-volley Davey tried to thump over long-on, but only succeeds in finding the fielder. A manic final over, this

make it six in 11! Watt tried to reverse sweep it, and finds his off stump uprooted! . Four wickets in that final over, shades of that Amir over against Australia at the 2010 World Cup, which saw five wickets fall.
nearly a wicket straightaway! Full on the stumps, chips this awkwardly in the air just wide of Wheal off a leading edge and it goes to mid-on for one.
good length ball on the stumps, defended.
full on middle, goes to drive, inside edge off the pads caroms to point. Big lbw shout denied.
back of a length on middle and off, defended to midwicket.
good length ball on off, punched into the covers.
good length ball on the pads, flicks this past Watt at short fine leg who gives chase to keep it from going to the rope.
good length ball on the hips, flicked over square leg for one.
good length ball on middle, flicks it straight to short fine leg but they bolt for a sharp run.
chops on! Length ball on fourth stump, tries to cut this but is cramped for room, too tight and not enough width for the shot and winds up paying the price for it.
full on off, punched to mid-off.
good length ball angled into the pads, flicked through square leg for one.
good length ball on middle, clips this into midwicket for one.
good length ball tailing down leg flicks the pads and goes to Cross diving to stop it.
good length ball on fourth stump, goes forward to defend, clips the pads and goes to the off side, stifled lbw shout. Extra bounce was taking it over.
good length ball on fourth stump, flicked into midwicket this time for one.
short on the hips, flicked too easy down the leg side to the fine leg rope.
short of a length on the stumps, slams a pull through wide mid-on and races away to the rope.
Vala backs away and Evans counters with a short and wide ball that is toe-dragged into the ground back to Evans.
Classy! Full on fourth stump, Siaka takes a casual step down the track and flicks this high over wide mid-on.
full on off, defended back to Wheal.

charges again but pays the price for it this time. Wheal bowls this slightly back of a length on fourth stump, Siaka can't get to the pitch as intended and tries to smash this on the up. Instead it's a healthy edge carrying through to Cross.
gem! Good length ball on off stump seams away past a forward prod.
Amini walks down the track and Wheal bumps him in response, hook is controlled along the ground to deep backward square.
back of a length on the hips, pulled again to deep backward square where Leask charges in to deny a second.
good length ball on off, defended behind point.
half-volley on middle, Vala strides forward and pumps this back over his head to the mid-on rope.
Vala backs away from leg and slaps a length ball to mid-off.
good length ball slanted well down leg, Vala tickles this to help it on its way to the fine leg rope.

Vala gets greedy after collecting two boundaries in the over already off Evans. Length ball on middle and off, tries to swat this on the up over midwicket but it gets a touch of extra bounce with a slower offcutter to produce a top edge that swirls gently to mid-off on the ring.
good length ball on off, defended to backward point.
full on sixth stump, driven wide of extra cover but not timed well and rolls away for just a single.
good length ball, defended into the ring.

full slanted into the legs, flicked to deep backward square. Amini wanted a second but was sent back belatedly and a relay from Michael Leask to the keeper Cross is very very tight. It goes to the third umpire and the vice-captain is about a foot short when Cross breaks the stumps. Self-inflicted wound by PNG, but great work by Leask who has been denying the second run from deep backward square through the entire Powerplay and is now rewarded for it on the scorecard.
full on the stumps, punched firmly back down the pitch and fetched by Munsey running back from mid-on.
back of a length on the hips, can't flick it away.

Stunner from Berrington! It's his day! Full and wide, there to lash but Atai picks out Berrington at backward point. Didn't try to keep it along the ground at all but Berrington sticks up his left paw, his weaker hand, to claw it out of the air high over his head. Berrington? More like Bearington with that big girizzly claw!
full and wide, driven to the cover sweeper.
full and slanted into the legs, possible runout chance for Coetzer but he fumbles charging in to collect.
full and wide, driven square behind point for a pair.
short and wide, zips this in flat and quick to defeat an attempted cut.
full on fourth stump and driven back to Watt.
short outside off, spins away as an arm ball and slapped into the covers.
full and speared down leg, good work from Cross to save it from being five extras.
full on off, defended back to Leask.
darted in flat on a good length on fourth stump, defended again to Leask.
full on the pads, flicked behind square for a pair.
full on middle, flicked along the turf through midwicket.
short on the hips, tickled through square leg for one.
back of a length on middle, goes back to flick behind square.
short on fourth stump, skids past a back foot punch.
darts this in fuller on middle, Bas breaks out the slog sweep and heaves this high over backward square into the temporary stands.
good length ball on the hips, goes back to flick into midwicket.
good length ball on middle and off, defended.
full on the legs, flicked behind square.
full on middle, jammed out back to Watt.
good length ball on middle, tapped into the covers for one.
full and slanted into the pads, easy tickle past cross to the fine leg rope.
full on middle, defended.
short on fourth stump, guided gently behind point.
full on leg stump, chipped straight to midwicket.
good length ball on middle, tapped into midwicket for one.
runs it down to third man for a single
they dash through for a quick leg-bye
strolls down the wicket and attempts a languid slog through the offside. Slogs fresh air instead
nudged to midwicket, and it requires the fielder to come around, so they can get a couple
length ball on middle stump, pulled away for one
backed away and tried to slash it through point, but it's a slower ball and this is a swing and a miss
sliced to point, where a brilliant stop means Vanua can't come across
slapped to long-on
holes out to long-on. Excellent catch by brad Wheal, who can do no wrong at the moment. Looked to swipe it over midwicket, but only got a top edge, and PNG slide closer to a huge defeat
defended back to the bowler
flighted, slashed through cover, but the man in the ring got a slight hand to it, so it won't go for four
tickled into the onside and Vanua keeps the strike
low full toss, driven back to long-off for a couple
flat and low, cut away
guided down to long-on
zapped it in full and wide once he saw the batsman trying to make room
full, quick, defended into the offside
driven back down the ground, and it's another good over for Scotland
driven down to long-on
gives this one flight and it looks a juicy full toss, but he can't find the gap
in the slot, and for once, PNG find the ropes. Stood back, moved his front leg out of the way and slapped it over his head

slashed over cover, and a misfield means he finds another boundary. Alisdair Evans wasn't sure if it was carrying, so he went for it, only for the ball to bounce well in front and over the dive to trickle away for four
worked down to long-on
slashed to backward point
slightly uppish as he carved that into the offside. A misfield allows a second run, and Brad Wheal glowers at the man on the rope
to add to his frustration, Vanua now slaps him way wayyy over long-on for a big six. This was in the slot, asking for punishment, and Vanua, who's begun to find his range, was only to happy to oblige
rolled his fingers over that, but Vanue works it to fine leg and hares back for a couple
oh dear, Vanua's taken a liking to Wheal in this over. Rocked back and flat-batted it - timed ever so sweetly - all the way for a six over midwicket. Sensational hitting
gets off strike after doing all that damage
thumped it to long-on to keep the strike. 18 off that Wheal over, and PNG are just about breathing in this contest still
sliced over cover by Doriga, and they come back for two
now he's getting into the act. Flighted up, which is poor, because they don't need to do that, and Doriga skips down the ground to get another four back down the ground
top-edged, but the momentum's all going PNG's way right now. What should have been a catch is dropped
finds the gap at backward point
tonked to long-off, but this time the fielder's in the right position
slides it down leg side
cut away, but straight to a man. He kicks himself, clearly felt there was a chance to pick up four more
lucky to get away with that. Low full toss sliding down leg, hits him on the pads

clever bowling, and Doriga's done for! That was smart because Doriga showed his hand early. Was down the ground before Watt was through his delivery stride, so he sent it down the offside, leaving Cross to effect a nimble stumping
yorker darted in at the right hander, Soper gets off strike with one down o long-on
belted back down to long-on
tucked into the onside. Got away with that - had Vanua been on strike for that, it likely would have travelled
guides it to long-off and keeps the strike
pace off, bangs it into the pitch. Steers it to square leg, but they only manage a single
should have been a run-out, Vanua was three quarters of the way down the pitch. Davey had all three stumps to aim at and plenty of time to take stock, but he misses and they come through
full delivery, squeezed out to fine leg for one
another slower ball plugged into the pitch. Spooned out to midwicket
brilliant. Vanua looked to make room and the bowler sends that inches away from the wide off stump line

and that's the end for Vanua, and probably curtains for PNG. A nothing ball, slow and tailing down leg. Sat up for Vanua to smash for four and bring up his half-century. It hits Vanua on the glove, though, and Cross has the easiest of catches. Vanua smashes the ground with his bat in frustration
hits him back over his head, and Chad's smashed Brad for four! Scotland aren't doing their NRR any favours with this late sloppiness
gets off strike through the onside
guided to the offside to get Soper back on strike
crisply struck to long-off, but Soper was desperate to come back on strike. In the process, he sent Pokana on a suicide mission to the non-striker's end, and Wheal knocks the bails off
full and straight from Wheal, Soper gets off strike to cover
oh wow! The number 11 has just beautifully timed his first ball, sending it sailing over long-on for a huge six!. 24 to get off the final six balls now - it's somehow still flickering, this PNG side
swing and a miss from Soper. It was in the slot, but Soper couldn't get any connection on that attempted carve over cover
