made good connection with that, though. Again in the slot, but even so, it required some absolutely exquisite timing to send it flying over cow corner for an 86m six! Scotland just can't kill PNG off

slower bouncer, but has he nicked this through to the keeper? Dharmasena doesn't think so, but Scotland have reviewed. Yep, there's a feather on that, and that, finally, seals the game, and PNG's fate. Scotland win by 17 runs, and go top in this group. PNG's hopes of qualifying for the second round are almost over.
and beaten straightaway! Nice outswinger from the right-hand quick, taking the ball away from well outside off. Baard chases and misses
now swing this time but he's beaten again. Tries to slice this one well outside off again, misses
good bounce and he's beaten for the third time in a row! Bangs this one into the pitch on short of length well outside off, Baard goes after it for an upper cut and just doesn't connect
132kmh, strays well down the leg side this time and it goes off Kusal's gloves as well, for a wide

he's desperate to get some bat on ball but just can't. Takes a step towards off, Karunaratne swings it away just a bit from outside off, the batter keeps the bat close to his bat to defend and can't touch it
finally gets bat on ball and scythes this length ball from outside off straight to point
131kmh, ends the over by bringing it a bit too much into the batter, goes off the pad towards square leg for another extra
drives and misses! Chameera starts with an outswinger as well, fuller than Karunaratne's length, and Baard swings and misses yet again
crisp as a cracker! Can't connect for so long and then suddenly unleashes a punch with minimal footwork and threads the gap between cover and cover point for a well-timed boundary
nips it in from back of length outside off, Baard waits and then scythes to third man for one
144kmh, short of length and just outside off, Green taps it to point off the back foot
down the leg side for a wide

knocks him on the helmet at 135kmh! Bangs it into the pitch and the ball shapes in towards Green's face, he's also beaten by pace as the ball rises quickly on him and Green can barely lift his hands to defend it. He looks ok and they sneak in a leg bye but there's a concussion protocol to be followed
steers the rising short ball outside off to third man uppishly for one and keeps strike

he strikes first ball, some start to his World Cup! Length ball on off stump and Baard goes down the ground first ball but doesn't connect well at all, and a tumbling mid-off gets under it just in time to push with both hands
offbreak outside off, Green drives away from the body and gets a thick edge towards third man for two
turns this one in from off stump, Green gets his bat down just in time
offbreak into the batter, he hands back and defends it back
leans into the offbreak outside off and tentatively pushes it to cover
ends the over with a carrom ball as Williams comes down to negate the turn but is hit on the pad, maybe just in line or outside off. He's well down the pitch
down leg for a flat wide and Williams was out of the crease for half a second, Kusal flicks the ball back but doesn't hit the stumps
starts on the pads and Green clips it to midwicket for one
hardly moves his feet on the back foot and pokes the ball to point. Yet to get off the mark
142kmh, again minimal footwork for the length ball outside off, Williams goes after it with hard hands but doesn't middle it
makes room, but this one's traveling at 146kmh and hurries him for pace, getting him into an awkward position and the bat comes down just in time to get deflected towards fine leg
144kmh, nearly in the block hole, it's a low and dipping full toss on off, and Green taps it away for a quick single
143kmh, rising short of length ball, and Williams pokes it to point again
length ball with the angle outside off, Green drives away from the body and misses it completely
143kmh, thick inside edge just outside off as Green pushes towards mid-off but it's not too far from the stumps

Green is hit on the helmet as well! This one was 147kmh. Rising short ball, Green wants to pull but misses and he's struck towards the back of the helmet after pivoting on the backfoot. He shows a thumbs up to his partner but a concussion check has to be done
down the leg side this time and he tucks it off the hips past square leg
148kmh and right in the block hole, Green does well to dig out another yorker to mid-off for a quick single
144kmh, Williams taps the length ball from off towards cover for another quick one
hurried by pace but he dances down to the spinner and loft that straight over the long-off boundary for a confident six! The first of the innings
another short and flat one, this time on the pads and it's tucked away for one to leg
short and flat down leg for a big wide

very dangerous shot selection from Green, goes a long away across for the ball on off and he wants to paddle it fine but he merely sweeps it to his leg stump, and then loses balance while being out of the crease but eventually makes it back
falls this time, skies this one to mid-on! Pitched up a little bit in the slot, Green lofts it high down the ground but only for a sitter to mid-on
flat delivery turning into Williams' pads again, goes off them fine on leg for a leg bye
nice and accurate on off, a watchful Erasmus waits and defends the straight ball back to the bowler
length ball on off, he defends it back with a straight bat
follows it with a short ball, Williams misses the pull and gets a run off his right shoulder. Given as runs so probably got some bat too
length delivery around, he pushes it down to long-on for one
charges down towards leg but the bowler bangs it short outside off, Williams lets it go
131kmh, waits on the back foot for the rising ball towards him and steers it down to third man
full on the pads, probably eyeing a yorker, and Williams flicks it away nicely past midwicket in the gap for two

shortText: de Silva to Williams, no run
text: belts out an appeal first ball for lbw as Williams comes down to negate the turn, it turned in from just outside off, but he was a long way down the pitch

shortText: de Silva to Williams, no run
text: another wrong'un, this time he tries to cut but only manages an inside edge

shortText: de Silva to Erasmus, no run
text: he's gone after that with a big sweep but missed it completely to be bowled off the googly, losing his middle stump

shortText: de Silva to Williams, (no ball) 1 run
text: nearly beats him with a leagbreak, he lunges forward a bit and gets a thick edge to off for one
way smarter and deftly steered past short third man for four! He waited on the back foot, got a hint of room outside off and sliced it late enough to beat the fielders behind square
and that's two in two! Tosses up the wrong'un and it's too full, Erasmus gets right on top of that one and drives it all along the ground through the covers for four more
covers the line outside off, maybe expecting a googly from the line well outside off, and pushes to long-on
waits on the back foot and guides the ball behind square for one
clears his front foot on the back foot and heaves the length ball, but not off the middle, to long-on

loud appeal for lbw and they've reviewed immediately after the slower one beats Erasmus. Lack of pace from outside off, cutting in and hitting the front pad just around off, we'll know soon if it hit him in line. Waiting for ball-tracking. There you go, impact is outside off and it's not out
bangs in a bouncer and Erasmus ducks under it early.
whips this away from middle stump line to deep square leg for one
bang in the block hole, and he pushes it down to mid-off with hard hands for a quick one to keep strike
legbreak on middle and he sweeps it away against the turn just behind square, and the fielder from fine leg does well to sprint across and then dive just in time to keep it in

shortText: de Silva to Williams, no run
text: pushes this one back to the left of the bowler, who stops it quickly

shortText: de Silva to Williams, no run
text: turning in from off and middle, can't get it away

shortText: de Silva to Williams, no run
text: don't think Williams knows which way this is going to turn, tentatively pokes with the bat outside off, and gets an edge to leg
comes down the pitch this time and pushes it to long-on before the legbreak can turn a long way
goes straight towards middle, Erasmus taps it to leg for one
dropped by Chandimal. Short of length outside off, goes for the cut, makes good connection but fails to keep it down. Chandimal makes a mess of it
looked like a slower one. Cuts it through covers. Gets two to the sweeper
length outside off once more. Erasmus nails the cut once again. To the right of Chandimal at point who dives and makes a partial one-handed stop
short of length outside off, Williams looks to slog it in the leg side. Misses
fuller and slower outside off, throws his bat at it and misses again
fuller on the stumps, backs away and hits it towards extra cover. This is sloppy from Sri Lanka, a misfield and a run conceded
length ball, spinning in. Goes for the slog and misses. Gets hit on the leg. An appeal for lbw but it was heading down
use of feet but Theekshana shortens his length. Worked towards deep-backward square leg
length ball around off, backs away and chips it inside out over covers. Only a single
short of length on the stumps, goes back and pulls it towards deep square leg
length ball on the stumps, comes out of his crease and tucks it towards deep midwicket
Williams breaks the shackles. Goes down on one knee and slog-sweeps this fuller ball from outside off over deep square leg
fuller around off, almost in the blockhole. Digs it out on the off side
length ball around off, Erasmus goes for the slog but fails to middle it. Hasaranga waits at long-on with his fingers pointing skywards and lets the ball settle into his hands
a bouncer from Kumara. Williams was looking to come forward but had to take evasive action in the end
short of length on the pads, flicked towards deep square leg
a bouncer to welcome David Wiese to the crease. Ducks under it
fuller around off, drives it towards sweeper cover
length ball around off and spinning in, goes back and flicks it towards midwicket
down the track but Hasaranga shortens the length. Flicked towards midwicket and they come back for the second

given lbw but Williams decides to review this. A googly from Hasaranga, fuller around off. Williams went for the reverse sweep but failed to connect and was hit right in front. And the ball-tracking confirms it would have hit the middle stump, three-fourth of the way up
fuller on the stumps, pushes it towards long-on
fuller on the pads, clipped away towards square leg and they sprint back for the second

shortText: de Silva to Wiese, no run
text: another googly, punched towards extra cover off the back foot
length ball on the stumps, flicked towards deep square leg
a slower one but short and wide. Cuts it towards sweeper cover for a couple

A big blow for Namibia. A length ball around off, jags back in sharply to hit the batter on the pads. Beaten both by pace and movement as he looked to bring his bat down. A huge appeal and the umpire took some time before raising his finger. He decides not to review it. Replays show it would have hit the top of the middle stump, umpire's call. So that would have stayed out
fuller on the pads, flicks it towards short fine leg for a single. Off the mark
a bouncer, hurries on to the batter. Smit was looking to pull but gets a top edge, over short fine leg
length ball at the stumps, defended towards extra cover off the back foot
dropped? A length ball at the stumps, the batter went for the pull but misses. The ball hits the back thigh and the keeper fails to collect it. Not clear if there was an inside edge
length ball, tucked away towards midwicket
short of length outside off, works it towards long-on
bowled 'im. Third wicket for Theekshana. A length ball around middle and spinning away. Frylinck went for the sweep but made no connection
an appeal for lbw but was heading down. A length ball, the carrom variation. Beats the batter for the pace as he looks to flick it away. Pitched outside leg I think
length ball on the stumps, flicked towards square leg
fuller around off, digs it out for a single to covers
short of length around off, goes for the pull but is hurried on. The ball dribbles towards long-on
short of length coming in towards the batter. Backs away and looks to swat at it. Too quick and it drops towards extra cover
aims for the yorker but just misses his mark. Dug out towards cover
short of length, just outside off, sways away from it
a slower length ball on the pads, worked towards wide long-on. Only a single

shortText: de Silva to Smit, no run
text: an appeal for lbw from the keeper but there's a big inside edge. Tossed up around off, pushes at it but manages only an inside edge
length ball around off, slower in the air. Pulls it towards deep square leg

Given lbw. A length ball in the line of the stumps, the batter went for the reverse sweep but missed and it hit him on the front pad. Pitched in line, no bat involved and it would have just clipped the off stump. Umpire's call there, which was out. Hasaranga has his second
a length ball around off, googly from Hasaranga. Flicked towards midwicket. The bowler chases himself and fields it

shortText: de Silva to Smit, no run
text: length ball outside off, goes for the sweep but it keeps quite low and sneaks underneath the bat
length ball around off, punched towards midwicket
length ball around off, Smit works it towards covers and gestures it was a slower one
hurries the batter with pace he attempts a pull. The ball hits the bat but lands well short of the incoming point fielder

that's some catch from Shanaka. Another short one hurled at Trumpelmann. He was late on the pull and this time the ball lobbed just over and to the right of the bowler. But Shanaka ran from extra cover with an outstretched right hand and took it just above the ground and finished with the slide
slower one. Fuller on the stumps. Driven towards wide long-on
fuller around off, digs it towards mid-off but doesn't take the single
fuller around off, smashes towards extra cover where the fielder threw himself at the ball but couldn't hold on to
an excellent yorker. Right up there at the base of the middle stump. Ya France looked to jam his bat at it but couldn't make the connection. Namibia could be all out here
a length ball, just outside off, looks to push at it and gets beaten. Wasn't far away from the off stump

A run out. Kumara goes for the yorker but ends up bowling a full toss. Pushed back towards the bowler who fumbles but short midwicket is close by and picks it up. An underarm throws at the non-striker's end to hit the stumps direct. Scholtz was well short
starts just outside off, he defends with soft hands to cover and is off the mark straightaway
starts on his pads, he misses the whip and takes it on the pad for a run to the leg side
angling into the batter, he works it to leg for one more single
123kmh, low and slow full toss well outside off, he didn't pick the lack of pace early maybe and ends up pushing it down to mid-off
132kmh, short ball on leg but not so quick, this time Kusal misses the pull
punches the length ball outside off down to mid-off for one more
too full first up on off and Kusal smacks that back over the bowler's head to send that crashing to the boundary
on the stumps again and this time Kusal unleashes a short-arm jab for the not so short ball to the midwicket boundary. Kusal is warming up, ladies and gentlemen
lands a short ball, Kusal pulls off the middle and gets a single this time because of the fielder just placed there
shuffles across and tucks the ball from outside off to leg for one

the slower one does it, Kusal takes the aerial route again and finds mid-off! Slow and full on off, Kusal lofts it just wide of mid-off but a diving Smit to his right grabs it with both hands just before landing and breaks the opening stand
length ball with the angle around off, another single as he tucks it to leg again
flat and short almost down leg again, worked off the pads for one to leg
slides it in with the arm and down leg for a wide
mush better now, on the stumps, and he can't put it away
short outside off, Chandimal pushes to cover
comes down this time to drive with the turn but only manages an inside edge onto his pad. Or was there pad first? The bowler did appeal for lbw but alone
goes back this time to let the ball angle in and work to leg for one

another appeal for lbw, the umpire gives it out and a wincing Nissanka looks at Chandimal before taking the review. I have a feeling it struck him outside off. Nissanka went back and across for the length ball almost heading towards off stump, struck almost in front, we'll confirm that. Ball-tracking says impact in line and crashing into the stumps. Another one down!
slightly full outside off, pushes it down to mid-off for a quick one
short of length now around off and Avishka is off the mark
taps this back of length ball to point off the back foot and takes off quickly
136kmh, on length just outside off, he taps it into the covers
141kmh, targets the off stump now from back of length, no room to work at all and Avishka defends it back
leading edge flies to third man where the fielder runs to his left and slides to just about keep it in and save two. He went after it outside off but only managed an edge against the rising ball
towards middle stump with the arm, not much pace, defends it back
touch towards off stump now, defends it back again
some room now, but flat again, he wants to cut it away but gets an inside edge
comes down the pitch this time to drive it with the turn to long-off. A single after three dots
tries some flight and it's a juicy full toss wide outside off, but Avishka only slaps it down to long-off
sliding towards middle and leg, he comes down to get some bat towards mid-on and a quick single makes it three from the over

he's struck first ball, Namibia have their third! With the angle well outside off on length, Chandimal has been scratchy tonight and he wants to cut it away with hard hands, but only gets a feather-like edge to the keeper. Are Namibia pumped or what
angling in slightly outside off, he helps it to leg for one to get off the mark straightaway
no room around off, Avishka waits and defends carefully under his eyes

what a six that is! Initially it looked like he had just come down the pitch to take it on the full and whip it over the in-field but that whip, timed to perfection, has gone all the way over the wide long-on boundary! What a strike
waits in the crease this time and he defends on off

126kmh, excellent bowling but Sri Lanka get four leg byes. Heading towards off from middle and leg, strikes his back pad and goes to third man boundary quickly for four. Namibia take a review, in fact, and replays show it pitched just outside leg

shortText: Ya France to Rajapaksa, no run
text: nice and accurate towards off, he stays back to defend the length ball

shortText: Ya France to Rajapaksa, no run
text: looks to sweep early but changes his mind to push from outside off towards point. No time for a run

shortText: Ya France to Rajapaksa, no run
text: towards leg now, he wants to sweep this time but doesn't connect properly and it wasn't that far from leg stump
finally sweeps, in the gap, and it rushes to the boundary to beat a diving Trumpelmann at the fine leg boundary. He got a hand to it but couldn't keep it in cleanly
tossed up on middle, flicked to deep midwicket for one more
full and wide outside off, Avishka stretches out and works it to leg looking for two but they settle for one
works the length ball to leg for one
too wide outside off and Rajapaksa lofts that wide and over the cover boundary in the big gap for four
some turn into the batter from outside off, he wants to cut late but doesn't connect properly
more on middle and leg, and pulled to deep square leg for one
low full toss and he drives it into the covers for a single
outside off and turning away, steers it away to deep point for two
keeps a bit low on off from wide of the crease, steered into the deep on off for one more
dances down, nearly takes it on the full, and slams it over the long-on boundary for a confident six
wants to heave again but it's nearly in the block hole outside off and he taps it towards off in the end for one
another yorker and this time Avishka defends it back
no room outside off and he defends

dropped at fine leg and it even goes for four! Rajapaksa pulls the short ball late and behind square, fine leg barely has to move, waits for the ball to reach him, but suddenly moves his hands towards the left and the ball goes through. He either misjudged it or the ball moved late in the air
wide outside off, too wide, and Rajapaksa drives it uppishly and nicely with a flourish over the covers for four more
he responds with a slow and short ball, almost down leg, but not a wide. One for the over though
115kmh, another slower one and he pushes into the covers
length ball outside off, steered towards short third man
fuller around off, drives it towards long-on
round-armish, fuller outside off, Rajapaksa looks to push at it and gets beaten
fuller around off, drives it towards long-off
length ball angling down the leg side. Misses the flick but that's a wide
tossed up around off, comes forward and punches it towards long-on
round arm once again. Pushes it towards covers and sets off for a quick single
down the track, converts it into a half-volley but mistimes it towards long-on. All along the ground
short of length outside off, hits the shoulder of the bat and goes towards third man
length ball on the pads, whipped towards deep-backward square leg
a slower bouncer. Rajapaksa ducks under it early. Called a wide for height
fuller-length ball around off, comes forward and defends it towards covers. Was looking for a single but the fielder was quick to the ball
length ball, an offcutter. Pushes it down the ground for a single
fuller on the stumps, on-pace delivery this time. Lofted over the bowler's head. Not enough power behind it though. They get a couple before long-on picks it up
fuller around off, Avishka gets low, almost on one knee and lofts it over mid-off. Just an extension of the arms and it carries all the way
short of length angling towards middle and leg. Tucked away towards square leg
short, outside off, mistimes the pull towards midwicket
a bouncer from around the wicket. Pulls it towards midwicket for one more
short of length outside off, pulled towards deep midwicket. Shouts of catch it but it lands well short of the incoming fielder
fuller and wider outside off, slices it behind point. Wasn't in full control but gets a single to third man
fuller outside off, driven towards deep extra cover
short of length, slower outside off, drags it towards deep square leg
sealed with a six! Short of length once again and this time Rajapaksa pulls it over the deep square leg fielder, who puts in the jump but it just evades him
short and wide, slapped to mid-off as the ball holds up a bit in the pitch.
good length ball on fifth stump, goes back to flick through wide mid-on.

my goodness what a diabolical start! Totally innocuous delivery nudged to square leg. O'Dowd calls for a run and catches Cooper completely off guard who is a deer in the headlights with no voice to confirm or deny whether he wants to run or not. The throw comes in to Stirling over the stumps and Cooper is out by a good 10 yards. But wait... Stirling has knocked a bail off before receiving the ball. However one bail stays on and it means his breaking of the stumps with ball in hand is still deemed legal to effect the runout.
good length ball on fifth stump, pushed at by O'Dowd and misses.
another flat delivery on fifth stump actually turns away like a leg break and beats another prod.
good length ball again outside off, another play and miss.

shortText: Little to de Leede, no run
text: good length ball in the fourth stump channel, can't get it away.
good length ball on off, tap and run into the off side.
full on fourth stump, driven to backward point but a diving stop on the ring.
width on sixth stump on a good length, punched firmly through cover with a square drive and it flies behind point for the first Dutch boundary.
speared in full on the legs, misses a flick. Big lbw shout turned down immediately. Extra taken to square leg.

shortText: Little to de Leede, no run
text: full on seventh stump, drives at it and is beaten.
starts with a yorker on off at 128 kph, jammed out.
full on off, driven to backward point.
short on the hips, goes to pull and an inside edge goes off the inside thigh.
short on the stumps, charges Adair and pulls flat into the ground into wide mid-on for one.

shortText: Adair to de Leede, no run
text: back of a length tailing down leg, de Leede walks down the pitch to flick, noise as it passes. Appeal for caught behind given not out. Marais Erasmus feels it came off the hip and replays confirm as much.

shortText: Adair to de Leede, no run
text: short on fifth stump, tries to ride this fine to third man but is hustled a touch and has to defend.
full on off, flicked through mid-on for one.

shortText: Simi Singh to de Leede, 1 run
text: flighted wider on fifth stump, flicked through mid-on again for one.
full outside off, driven wide of mid-off, diving stop on the ring by KOB to keep it to one.

shortText: Simi Singh to de Leede, 1 run
text: full on middle and leg following de Leede backing away, flicks this into midwicket for one.
full on fifth stump, O'Dowd goes over extra cover, is able to do what he couldn't earlier in the over and pierce the ring for a boundary.
full on fourth stump, flicked through wide long-on for a well-run pair.

shortText: Little to de Leede, no run
text: full on off, punched into the off side ring for a dot.

shortText: Little to de Leede, no run
text: full on middle and off, de Leede backs away trying to drive through extra cover but can't get it past Tector.
length ball on sixth stump, De Leede steps down and thumps a lofted drive on the up whistling past Little's left ear and it races through mid-off to the rope.

de Leede won't be putting that on his Instagram stories later tonight.... He shuffles across his stumps in a premeditated attempt to scoop over fine leg, Little sends down a meatball of a full toss at thigh height that clangs into the top of leg stump after de Leede flails on his intended stroke. Yikes. You won't be seeing that in the MCC coaching manual for batter or bowler.
full on fifth stump, driven to cover.

back of a length on fifth stump, guided behind point for what looks like one but good running turns it into two taking on the arm of deep third man who was quite fine on the rope and had to travel some way to get to the ball.
full on the stumps, flicked away for a single.
back of a length on fourth stump, guides this to Little at short third man, who has fancy neon green frame Oakleys on to match his jersey.
short ball on sixth stump, Ackermann sways away from this 126 kph delivery. Looked more threatening than it was.
fullish length on fourth stump, punches it into cover but Tector swarms in.
another bouncer outside off at 129 kph and it swerves away dramatically with some funky swing you don't usually see out of that length, left alone again.
back of a length on fifth stump, pulls this flat and straight to mid-on fielded on the ring.
short and wide, loosener at 131 kph and O'Dowd cracks this behind point to the rope.
full and very wide on seventh stump, this time driven wider to the cover sweeper.
short and wide, cracks another square drive to the sweeper.
fullish length ball outside off punched past the bowler toward mid-off for one.
short and wide, slices a cut fine behind point and beats third man on the rope fielding very fine still.
short and wide down leg, late on a pull, wide called.
full and wide, driven hard but straight to extra cover.
full on fourth stump, driven to long-on.
full on middle and leg, charges to flick and tickles this to fine leg.

shortText: Simi Singh to O'Dowd, no run
text: full on middle and off, mishits this back to Singh.
full on off, driven through midwicket for one.
full on middle, backs away to flick this through midwicket.
good length ball on fifth stump, flicks this through wide long-on for one.
good length ball on fifth stump, slapped through cover for one.
full toss low at the shins on middle, swept to deep backward square for one.
googly floated too full on fifth stump and O'Dowd smokes this through long-on to the rope.
short on fifth stump, slapped to the cover sweeper for one.
full on off, uses his feet to flick into midwicket for one.
short on fifth stump, defended to cover.
full on fifth stump at 132 kph, drives hard but picks out extra cover on the ring. A recurring theme so far in this innings.
full and sprayed down leg at 130 kph.

short tailing down leg, big appeal for caught behind from Campher. Didn't sound like anything live as Ackermann is late on an attempted pull but both Campher and the keeper Neil Rock have convinced captain Andy Balbirnie to call for the review for possible caught behind. But it's a quality sales job by Campher as replays show Ackermann has gloved this with a spike showing up on UltraEdge! Another bad ball wicket for Ireland. After so much poor luck against the Dutch since that match at Sylhet in 2014, everything is going their way this afternoon in Abu Dhabi.

pitched up and pinned in front! Tendo goes first ball! Campher has two in two and Netherlands are in trouble. Someone needs to put a finger in the dyke! Full and straight and ten Doeschate, who announced his retirement from county cricket last month and has not been in great form, was stuck in treacle, bat coming across the line - looked to be hitting leg stump

goes full again, hit on the front pad... not given this time! Rod Tucker shakes his head, Campher looks imploringly at him. That looked close to me, and Ireland are going to review. No footwork once again, beats the inside edge of the bat... and Hawk-Eye has it smacking leg stump! Curtis Campher has a hat-trick! Netherlands have had the stuffing knocked right out of them

shortText: Campher to van der Merwe, OUT
text: bowled 'im! FOUR IN FOUR! Campher has done a Malinga, as van der Merwe throws the bat and drags a wide one into off stump. Incredible scenes as the Boys in Green seize control in Abu Dhabi. Campher had none for 12 at the start of his over - now he has 4 for 13!!
pitched up in the channel, this one is calmly tapped through the covers. Yeesh. Everybody take five
round the wicket, angling in on the stumps as Seelaar comes across
short ball, coming in with the angle, Seelaar swings at it and misses
pitched up in the corridor, gets on to the front foot and leaves
back-of-a-length ball on off, 135kph and pushed down square into the off side
bangs it in and Seelaar again plays it watchfully in defence
length outside off, 136kph/84mph and he thick-edges a drive down to third for one
good length and - woof! - this one kicks up past the outside edge with Seelaar feeling for it
shortish, tries to tuck this off the hip, the ball hits him on the body and bobbles wide of the stumps
slashed to third! Finally some width and Seelaar throws the hands, gets a thick edge to the boundary
angling in on the stumps, nudged for one leg side
back of a length, 135kph wide of off stump, draws a swing and a miss
slightly short and straight and O'Dowd flicks it behind square to keep the strike
looped up outside off stump, O'Dowd prods it square
clipped through the off side for a couple
floated up full outside off, O'Dowd squirts it towards cover
White loses this line
clubbed down the ground! Full and juicy and O'Dowd brings the bat down from on high, slugs it through long-on for four
dragged short and pounded in front of deep midwicket! Back-to-back boundaries from O'Dowd, heaving the ball away powerfully in front of square
pushed through on leg stump, worked for a single

shortText: Simi Singh to O'Dowd, no run
text: over the wicket, pushed through flat on the stumps, jabbed to midwicket
dobbed on off stump, no real turn and O'Down stays back to punch down the ground

shortText: Simi Singh to Seelaar, no run
text: tossed up slower, 88kph outside off, Seelaar leans out and pats it away
Seelaar gives him the charge but Singh drags it down, trying to fire it behind the pads... manages to shovel a single behind square
tossed up and O'Dowd stretches out to punch through mid-on

shortText: Simi Singh to Seelaar, no run
text: darted outside off, Seelaar drives around his front pad, Singh dives across to cut it off
starts with a low full toss on leg stump, O'Dowd gets something on it - that'll run away fine off the pads for four
slower at 127kph/79mph, maybe a cutter, O'Dowd taps it back
banged into the deck, fenced away towards point
length ball, fired in straight and O'Dowd gets it off the pad to the on side, Campher nearly colliding with Seelaar as he attempts to prevent one
pitched up, 131kph/81mph and nibbling back towards off stump, pushed to cover
pitched up, Seelaar backs away and attempts to slap down the ground... ends up being a tight single to mid-on! Think he was home as Adair's throw came in
looped up and worked into the midwicket region

rolls his arm over on middle and leg, O'Dowd nudges through leg... that's his half-century, standing tall for Netherlands amid the rubble of that four-wicket over. Can he drag them up to a fighting score?
tossed up outside off, Seelaar chips this aerially through extra cover
googly, I think, jabbed away into the covers on the back foot
flattish and swung leg side, just a single out to the midwicket boundary rider
pushed through flatter, driven down to long-off
tucked off the pads, long-on has to come running in a long way, but keeps them to one
length outside off, O'Dowd mistimes it back down the track

O'Dowd... Oh dear! Holes out to long-on! Adair's cutter does the trick, the batter unable to generate the power he needed when looking to slog down the ground. Almost went all the way, mind, only for Harry Tector to take a well-judged catch at head height in front of the rope
length ball, 126kph/78mph on middle and off, defended
shuffles across and runs this through backward point
short of a length and worked off the hip to long leg

shortText: Simi Singh to van Beek, no run
text: tossed up and prodded back

shortText: Simi Singh to van Beek, 1 run
text: pushed through and van Beek steps out to tuck through midwicket
slapped away through midwicket! Singh drops in a legbreak but it lands short and Seelaar swivels to biff it for four
lofted over cover, just one as he tries to come down

shortText: Simi Singh to van Beek, 2 runs
text: flatter as van Beek steps out, deflected past short third for a couple as Stirling gives chase

shortText: Simi Singh to van Beek, 1 run
text: lobbed up on the stumps and worked leg side

shortText: Little to van Beek, no run
text: round the wicket, full and wide out towards the tramlines, swing and a miss
pitched up, 135kph/84mph and van Beek swats it down to long-off, bringing up the Neth 100
wide yorker, beyond the tramlines as Seelaar swings and misses. Not called wide by Marais Erasmus, because Seelaar had moved across early
pitched up and dug out back to the bowler... van Beek should be run out backing up, but Little misses with an underarm from six yards! He'll take the dot, I guess
full outside off, Seelaar jumps across and attempts to paddle, gets hit on the boot - Little has a shy from further away this time, as they scramble through, but the ball comes out skewiff!
flung down full and straight, nurdled off the pads for one. Still a good over from Little despite the missed run-out opportunities
pitched up, van Beek digs it out down towards long-on and they hustle back

shortText: Adair to van Beek, no run
text: pace off, looks like a legcutter and it completely foxes van Beek, big old swing and a miss as it loops through outside off
full and fast,131kph/81mph and whipped leg side from off stump

slower ball, slogged to long-on! Seelaar's valiant attempt to scrap his side a score ends in the final over, completely mistiming a swish down the ground. Balbirnie runs in to take a straightforward catch

shortText: Adair to van Beek, 1 run, OUT
text: worked leg side, van Beek attempts to get back and keep the strike... but Rock takes the throw and runs him out! Good arm from the deep and he was always struggling, despite putting in the full-length dive. Netherlands finishing with a whimper

plopped straight up, long-off takes it running in! Campher with the catch, Adair has his third and Ireland end the innings with W-W-W! It's another collapse.com for the Dutch, who lost 4 for 0 in the tenth over and finish things in similarly chaotic fashion
touch of insuring at 134 kph full on middle, defended on the front foot.
inswinging yorker pings Stirling on the foot but it was going well down leg.
short and tailing well down leg.
bouncer sails over off stump as Stirling aborts a pull, it clears Edwards behind the stumps and goes to the rope for four byes.
good length ball in the fifth stump channel beats Stirling poking away from his body.
full and sprayed outside the off stump guideline.
full on off, defended on the front foot to mid-off.
full and sprayed well down the leg side for another wide.
good length ball on fifth stump, defended to point.

shortText: van der Merwe to O'Brien, FOUR
text: good length ball on off stump, KOB doesn't care and hits this on the up high over wide mid-off bouncing away to the rope.

shortText: van der Merwe to O'Brien, FOUR
text: good length ball on middle and leg, KOB backs away from leg stump to create room accessing the offside and slaps this through cover again for a boundary.

shortText: van der Merwe to O'Brien, 1 run
text: full outside leg stump trying to follow KOB backing away again, drives this firmly wide of extra cover on the ring for one.

shortText: van der Merwe to Stirling, 1 run
text: full outside leg, flicked into midwicket for one.

shortText: van der Merwe to O'Brien, no run
text: full and very wide as KOB backs away, too far to play at this and left alone.

shortText: van der Merwe to O'Brien, no run
text: good length ball on middle, defended to cover.
full and wide, driven through cover for a pair.
good length ball on the knees, clips this to deep backward square for a long single.

shortText: van Beek to O'Brien, no run
text: good length ball on fifth stump, defended to point.

shortText: van Beek to O'Brien, no run
text: good length ball outside off, hit into the off side.

shortText: van Beek to O'Brien, no run
text: slower good length ball at 114 kph on middle, defended back to van Beek.

shortText: van Beek to O'Brien, no run
text: bouncer left alone.
full on middle, defended at 129 kph.
good length ball on the stumps defended.

hello! Fullish length on fifth stump, just a simple slice over backward point and it flies away over the third man rope for six to bring up 2500 runs in T20Is for Stirling. Intentionally played there with an open face.
short and wide, slapped high over cover and a sweeper is in place to cut it off.
short on middle, KOB tries to imitate Stirling's slice over third man but instead he pops this straight up over extra cover in the ring. Easy catch taken halfway in from the 30-yard circle.
good length ball on fifth stump, tries to square drive this but backward point with a diving stop on the ring.
starts with an offcutter on fourth stump, Stirling shuffles across to flick into midwicket.
full on off, defended to cover.
full on off, driven to mid-off.
full and wide on sixth stump, drives hard and a thick edge squirts between slip and gully along the turf to the rope.
short on fifth stump, Balbirnie goes leg side this time pulling through midwicket and it races away.

the short ball plan finally comes off. Klaassen bangs this in again on fifth stump and Balbirnie tries to repeat the pull through midwicket but mistimes this and it flutters gently to van der Merwe in the ring who takes a catch tumbling to his right.

shortText: van Beek to Stirling, no run
text: full on middle, defended to cover.

edge! Dropped! Slip has departed for van Beek when he was there for Klaassen. Stirling charges the medium pacer to a full ball and gets a thick edge that flies to Edwards' right. He dove full extension and got a glove to it but it squirts out. If slip had stayed in, it was a regulation chance.

shortText: van Beek to Delany, no run
text: full on off stump, drives at this and a thick edge bounces short of slip.

shortText: van Beek to Delany, no run
text: good length ball defended.

shortText: van Beek to Delany, no run
text: short on the stumps, goes to pull and misses off the thigh.
full on fourth stump, drives at this and a thick edge goes to deep third man for one to end the Powerplay.

shortText: van der Merwe to Delany, 1 run
text: good length ball slides in as an arm ball into off stump, prods at this and a thick inside edge goes past Edwards for one.

shortText: van der Merwe to Stirling, 1 run
text: full on middle, prods forward and another thick inside edge goes through square leg.

shortText: van der Merwe to Delany, 1 run
text: good length ball on sixth stump, prods at this and it flutters into the covers for one.

shortText: van der Merwe to Stirling, 1 run
text: full on off, pushes this through mid-off for one.

shortText: van der Merwe to Delany, no run
text: flighted more on a good length on fourth stump, defended.

shortText: van der Merwe to Delany, FOUR
text: good length ball but width outside off, slaps this on the up through extra cover and it goes to the rope.
good length ball on fifth stump, goes to drive and is beaten.
good length ball outside off, punched to cover.
full on the legs, flicked to deep square leg.
full on middle, driven to mid-on.
short on fifth stump, cramped for room a touch going to cut and it flies wide of backward point to deep third man for one.
short on middle, pulls this flat to deep square leg.
good length ball sticks in the wicket on middle and is shoveled awkwardly over extra cover for one.
good length ball on sixth stump, flicked to long-on.
flighted more on a fuller length on fifth stump, driven to long-off.
full on the legs, heaved flat along the ground to deep midwicket for one.
flighted more on a good length on middle and leg, flicked into midwicket for one.
full on fifth stump, driven to extra cover.

shortText: van der Merwe to Delany, SIX
text: flighted full outside off, skips down the track to loft this over wide long-off for a maximum.

shortText: van der Merwe to Delany, 1 run
text: good length ball on fifth stump, cuts this behind point.

shortText: van der Merwe to Stirling, 1 run
text: good length ball pushed through the ring for one.

shortText: van der Merwe to Delany, 1 run
text: good length ball on off, pushed into the covers for one.

shortText: van der Merwe to Stirling, 1 run
text: good length ball on off, pushed through mid-off for one.

shortText: van der Merwe to Delany, FOUR
text: good length ball on off, goes to defend, thick edge goes past Edwards and trickles to the third man rope.

shortText: van der Merwe to Delany, 1 wide
text: full and down leg, wide called.
slower ball from round the wicket, dabbed behind square and they pinch one... there's a direct hit from backward point, but I think Delany is fine

shortish and swatted away on the pull, into the gap between long-on and deep midwicket... and Cooper misfields to gift four! Lack of communication with Ackermann and then his attempted sliding stop was too late
length in the channel, pace off again, tapped back
fired into the front pad, strangled lbw appeal from Klaassen. Erasmus not interested
length ball coming back in and worked to leg for one
length outside off, this skids through past the outside edge
fullish outside off, 136kph/84mph and steered calmly towards point
goes back outside off and glides one to third
hoicked high over midwicket! Banged in short and Delany is up on his tippy-toes to slam another boundary
length ball on the stumps, Delany makes room... stroked through the covers! Rides the bounce and times it beautifully for four
backs away and Glover fires it wide of off, 126kph/78mph and Delany watches it by
shortish outside off, Delany whips the hands through an uppish cut to the cover sweeper
lobbed up outside off, swiped through the covers
full and straight at 94kph, nurdled to leg
bit more air, wide of off stump and Delany slaps to extra cover
boom goes the dynamite! Seelaar is attempting to turn the ball away from the right-hander, but can't avoid Delany's hitting arc. Gets low and mullers it over long-on for an 86m six

bowled on the charge! Seelaar yorks Delany as he attempts to come down and finish this quickly... the ball skids into off stump but it's small consolation for the Netherlands captain, with the goose almost cooked
lobbed up from round the wicket, prodded calmly to cover

shortText: van der Merwe to Stirling, 1 run
text: tossed up and stroked through the off side

shortText: van der Merwe to Campher, no run
text: length ball on off, prodded away

shortText: van der Merwe to Campher, 1 run
text: tough straighter, flighted delivery and Campher gets off the mark with a sweep

shortText: van der Merwe to Stirling, no run
text: darted on the stumps, Stirling blocks

shortText: van der Merwe to Stirling, no run
text: tossed up full on middle and leg, defended

shortText: van der Merwe to Stirling, no run
text: floated up full and again Stirling is happy to tap it back

shortText: van Beek to Campher, no run
text: full length on off, dug out back towards the bowler
short and pulled in front of deep square leg, Ackermann can't get around the rope to cut it off. Ireland raise three figures, they are almost there
tucked into the leg side

shortText: van Beek to Stirling, no run
text: length, 133kph/82mph, Stirling steps out early and taps it away

shortText: van Beek to Stirling, no run
text: another good-length ball, blocked on off stump
pumped down the ground! Stirling remembers what he's there for and unceremoniously bashes four back through mid-off. Only his second boundary of the innings, levels the scores

tossed up full on the stumps and nurdled to leg, that'll do it - Ireland win by seven wickets, with almost five overs to spare. Curtis Campher follows up his four-in-four-balls with the winning runs, decent day's work from him

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Munsey, no run
text: ooh, a terrific delivery to start, full, and swinging back into the left-hander to beat his hurried flick. Appeal for lbw, not given. Was there an edge on that? Nah, it's swinging too much and missing leg stump

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Munsey, no run
text: some swing again, straightening in towards off stump from a good length. Stays back and defends to short midwicket

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Munsey, no run
text: length ball on off stump, lets it come and punches towards cover point

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Munsey, no run
text: not quite short enough to pull. Around bail-high on off stump, and he swats it to short midwicket

shot! Back of a length, slanting across and not swinging back on this occasion, and it ends up offering the smallest hint of width. Munsey just stands tall and slaps it away to the left of backward point

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Munsey, no run
text: good ball to end the over, yorker slanting away and pitching fairly wide of off stump. Not much footwork from Munsey, stands there and reaches out to try and slash it away, but he can't make contact

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Coetzer, no run
text: full, slanting away from off stump, and Coetzer goes for an angled-bat drive and misses. It was up there to drive, but he didn't quite get a front-foot stride in

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Coetzer, no run
text: full on off stump, driven to mid-off, not quite timing it

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Coetzer, 1 leg bye
text: appeal for lbw as Coetzer is beaten while looking to clear his front leg and swipe to leg, but the ball pitched well outside leg stump. Hits his back pad and rolls into the backward point region for a leg bye

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Munsey, no run
text: length ball, a bit of inward nip from just outside off. Presses half-forward and blocks it back to the bowler

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Munsey, no run
text: not at all short enough to pull, and it skids through to get under the bat and hit the back thigh pad. Missing leg comfortably, though, so no appeal

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Munsey, no run
text: short, rising slower ball outside off, and Munsey looks to uppercut but doesn't connect, beaten by lack of pace

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Coetzer, no run
text: full outswinger outside off, and once again Coetzer's front foot doesn't go across while he attempts a cover drive, and he misses as a result

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Coetzer, no run
text: wide-ish length ball, and Coetzer flat-bats it hard but within range of mid-off. where Afif Hossain makes a good stop sliding to his right

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Coetzer, no run
text: another big cover drive, and again he fails to connect. Saifuddin gets this to swing away again, from a wide-ish line outside off

bowled him! That's a terrific delivery, right up in the blockhole, and Coetzer, looking to make room and stab it away through the off side, ends up playing down the wrong line, as this swings away just a touch to miss his outside edge and hit off stump. Bangladesh have made a terrific start to this game
full outside off, opens his bat face and squeezes it out to deep point
looks to make room and Saifuddin follows him with a full ball that swings into his feet. Clipped to deep square leg

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Munsey, no run
text: appeal for lbw as Munsey misses the flick off a good-length ball, but it's clearly pitched outside leg. More a swipe than a flick, actually
leg-stump yorker, whipped away to deep square leg

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Munsey, (no ball) SIX
text: wristy, and has he juuust cleared the rope? Seems like it. Fullish on off stump, with a hint of swing into the left-hander, and Munsey whips it away with a big follow-through. Looks like Shakib has dropped a difficult chance running to his right and diving full-length at deep square leg. Pops out of his hands and past the rope. Oh, that wouldn't have counted anyway, because it's a no-ball. Wow.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Cross, no run
text: hits that hard length while angling the ball into the stumps. Cross stays on the back foot and defends it back to the bowler

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Cross, no run
text: and again, stays back to a good-length ball angling into the stumps from wide of the crease, and blocks it back to the bowler

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Cross, no run
text: back of a length on off stump, stays leg-side of the ball and jabs to backward point
length ball close to off stump, presses forward and opens his bat face to steer it down to deep third

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Cross, no run
text: nice field placement. It's a yorker close to off stump, and Cross opens his bat face to squeeze it fine, but short third is stationed nice and fine, so it's a dot ball

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Cross, 1 leg bye
text: length ball angling down leg, misses the flick but gets a leg bye to the right of midwicket
length ball on off stump, swiped down the ground towards mid-on

wide down the leg side, but you can see why he wanted to bowl that line. Missed it by just inches. Saw Munsey look to create room and followed him with a full one, but ended up the wrong side of his feet
full, angling in towards leg stump, he knows Cross is trying to make room to hit through the off side. Shows the full face and pushes to mid-off
in the blockhole on middle stump, makes room by moving away from leg stump, and swipes it to the right of deep midwicket, who makes a good diving stop
shot. For once Saifuddin offers Munsey width with a full one, and he gets down low to loft it cleanly over wide mid-off

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Cross, no run
text: back of a length, slanting away from off stump, and Cross misses the attempted swat through midwicket
back of a length slower ball at the hip, and Cross does well to wait and hold his shape, and then he's able to whip it away and beat short fine leg to his left

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Cross, no run
text: length ball on off stump, driven crisply on the up and mid-off makes a good stop diving to his left. From there he throws and hits the stumps at the keeper's end, but the backtracking Cross is back in time. Afif Hossain the fielder
shortish on leg stump, swiped to deep square leg, one bounce to the fielder

shot! This is why he's so dangerous. Bangladesh have bowled well to him, but he gets one in the slot, angling into the stumps, and he quickly gets his front leg out of the way to create swinging room and shovels it high over the long-on boundary. Excellent work with the bottom hand
digs in a bouncer fairly wide outside off, and Munsey reaches out and misses the uppercut
slower ball, full and angling into middle and leg, clipped away towards deep square leg

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Munsey, 1 run
text: back of a length, spinning in towards off stump, lets it come and punches to long-on

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Cross, 2 runs
text: tosses it up slow and wide of off. Reaches out to sweep to the left of deep backward square leg

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Cross, no run
text: slow again, this time drifting in towards middle and leg, pushes inside-out to short extra-cover

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Cross, 1 run
text: looped up slow again, wide of off, drags a sweep out to deep midwicket

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Munsey, 1 run
text: once again, Shakib shortens his length to the left-hander, bowling it into the pitch and turning into the stumps, lets it come and nudges it with the turn behind square

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Cross, no run
text: looks to make room and Shakib follows him with the arm ball. Ends up punching it back to the bowler while aiming through the covers
length ball pitching outside off and going with the angle, swept to deep backward square leg

appeal for lbw, and it definitely looked plumb. Richard Kettleborough raises his finger, and Cross is on his way. Fired in full at the stumps, and that's not an easy ball to sweep. It was too quick for him to get down on his back knee, and ended up playing an off-balance standing sweep with a cleared front leg. He misses, and the ball smacks into his back pad. It's probably hitting leg stump or maybe even middle and leg
length ball turning towards leg stump, gets forward to clip to deep midwicket

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Munsey, no run
text: keeps going with the angle as Munsey looks to flick from the crease, and the ball hits his pad. Missing leg, though

bowled him, what an over this is from Mahedi! It's another one that goes with the arm after pitching outside off, and Mahedi misses the sweep. The ball skids through and sneaks under his bat. This was one of those sweeps with the front leg out of the way, so there was no second line of defence once he'd missed with the bat
fullish at the stumps, clipped into the backward square leg region

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to MacLeod, no run
text: length ball going with the angle towards middle stump, gets forward to push into the covers

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to MacLeod, 1 run
text: another sweep, and very nearly another wicket. Looks to drag it from well outside off, and he's done in by Shakib's lack of pace. He just floated it up there. Top-edge, and Taskin, diving to his left at short fine leg, can't quite grab it as it descends from up above him

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Berrington, no run
text: length ball outside off, pushed to extra-cover

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Berrington, no run
text: straightens his line and bowls a bit quicker, and Berrington blocks it back to the bowler

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Berrington, 1 run
text: looks to make room, and the Shakib arm ball, skidding towards leg stump from a good length, denies him that room. Ends up driving to long-off while aiming through the covers

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to MacLeod, 1 run
text: slow, just outside off, makes a bit of room and slaps to sweeper cover

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to MacLeod, no run
text: back of a length, spinning in towards off stump, blocked back to the bowler

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to MacLeod, no run
text: quicker ball, goes with the arm towards off stump, defended to extra-cover

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to MacLeod, no run
text: goes back to a length ball on off stump, looks to punch to long-off, but he doesn't get the room for it and he plays it to midwicket instead

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to MacLeod, no run
text: now he looks to go back and across and work it square, but the ball skids through quick and he's forced to clip to that man at midwicket once again

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to MacLeod, no run
text: length ball, keeps going with the arm outside off. Wants to flick through the leg side from deep in his crease, ends up whipping it back to the bowler because of the lack of turn
back of a length, turning into the stumps, goes back and works it to deep square leg

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to MacLeod, 1 run
text: full on middle, punched firmly to long-off.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Berrington, OUT
wkt_text: RD Berrington c Afif Hossain b Shakib Al Hasan 2 (13m 5b 0x4 0x6) SR: 40.00
text: Berrington's charge goes awry thanks to some brilliance by Afif at long-on! Berrington uses his feet trying to smash this down the ground for six. Afif was cheating in a bit off the rope and had to backpedal sharply before leaping to cling on to this flat drive. He's about to lose his balance over the rope and manages to flick it up to himself before finishing the catch on the rebound once he's reestablished himself back in the field of play.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Leask, no run
text: full on off, defended back to Shakib.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Leask, OUT
wkt_text: MA Leask c Liton Das b Shakib Al Hasan 0 (3m 2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00
text: too easy. Poor shot from Leask shoveling this straight to long-off. Shakib slows up the pace a touch in the air and suckers Leask into a lofted drive, through the shot a touch early and without any power behind it. Catching practice for Liton Das on the rope who takes this catch five yards inside the rope reaching above his head.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to MacLeod, no run
text: full and driven back to Shakib.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to MacLeod, no run
text: good length ball on middle, goes back to defend to Shakib.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Greaves, no run
text: full on middle, defended to Mahedi.
good length ball on off, shuffles across to flick into midwicket wide of the bowler for one.

wkt_text: CS MacLeod  b Mahedi Hasan 5 (18m 14b 0x4 0x6) SR: 35.71
text: MacLeod backs away to cut, and now MacLeod backs away all the way to the pavilion. No boundaries in the last four overs for Scotland and the desperation to break the drought showed in that shot. MacLeod left his stumps exposed trying to get creative but the ball skids on from a good length by Mahedi Hasan and pings back off stump.

shortText: Mahedi Hasan to Watt, no run
text: good length ball defended into the leg side.
good length ball on the legs, flicked into midwicket.
full on fifth stump, swept through square leg.

shortText: Afif Hossain to Greaves, no run
text: zipped in flat and full on sixth stump, goes to sweep and misses.
backs away to cut a good length ball off fourth stump to deep point.
good length ball flicked into the leg side again.
full outside leg stump following Greaves backing away going to drive, thick edge flies wide of short third man for a pair.
reverse sweep finally comes off for once today. Scotland's first boundary since Munsey fell. It was full on fifth stump and Greaves swats it flat over backward point.
full on the stumps, uses his feet to flick through midwicket.
Good length ball on the legs, flicked through square leg.
full on off, Greaves shuffles across to sweep to deep backward square.
Watt charges a full ball on off and flicks to deep midwicket for one.

reverse sweep/pull to a full toss sails over the rope. Scotland bench wants a no ball called on height too. Premeditated shot and it comes in much higher than Greaves was expecting but still able to adjust to slam it high over backward point. Umpire deems the ball legal from a spinner on height and it came in at the thigh while crouching.
good length ball punched through cover for one.
full and wide, charges again to drive over cover for a pair.
good length ball at full pace, 137 kph on middle stump, guided with an open face behind point.
back of a length on middle, pulled flat to wide long-on for a pair.
length ball on fifth stump at 131 kph, Watt swats this with a two-handed tennis backhand over mid-off who is up in the ring, safe shot to the field and clears Liton Das to the rope.
slower ball finally arrives on a good length on off at 114 kph, tapped gently through cover for one.

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Greaves, no run
text: length ball off the pads going down leg side, Greaves misses an awkward pull. Big noise with a mild appeal for caught behind but clearly off the pads.
good length ball on middle, tapped into the covers for one to keep strike.
bouncer is too short and too wide down leg. Could've been called wide for either option.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Greaves, 1 leg bye
text: goes to reverse sweep again and misses, goes off the thigh into the off side for one extra.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Watt, FOUR
text: reverse sweep produces results for Watt. Perfect ball to pick full on fourth stump, short third man is up in the ring so it's very safe and clears him easily, one bounce over the rope.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Watt, 2 runs
text: bowled fuller and flatter on off, driven firmly to long-off.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Watt, no run
text: goes for the orthodox sweep this time to a full ball on fifth stump and misses off the pads.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Watt, 1 run
text: charges and chips this awkwardly over Shakib into no man's land short of long-off for one.

shortText: Shakib Al Hasan to Greaves, 1 run
text: good length ball on the legs, uses his feet to clip behind square for a long single.
short on middle, pulled flat to deep square leg.
short outside off, goes to pull but mistimes this off the toe and trickles wide of the keeper for one.
full outside off, goes to sweep the medium pacer behind square and picks up another single.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Watt, no run
text: Watt shuffles way outside off, almost off the pitch, to scoop over short fine leg but misses off his pads.
slower ball full and wide outside off, Watt stays in his crease this time and is just able to reach out and get toe on this into the covers.
good length ball on fifth stump, goes to cut and a thick edge flies between the keeper and short third man to go to the rope. It brings up a 50 partnership to give Scotland some life.

wkt_text: MRJ Watt c Soumya Sarkar b Taskin Ahmed 22 (28m 17b 2x4 0x6) SR: 129.41
text: starts with a slower ball full on middle, Watt is out in front of the shot and spoons this high over the bowler. Long-on and long-off converge. Mahmudullah backs away to allow Soumya Sarkar to clutch on with ease 10 yards inside the rope.
Cracking shot! short and wide at full pace, 141 kph, Greaves flays this behind point. Deep third man is very fine and has no chance to cut it off.

uppercut clears deep third man for a maximum. Scotland bench coming alive! Taskin tried to bump him but Greaves is able to back away from leg stump to get enough room on the ankle to ramp this over the rope.

overpitched, overcompensated and overly elegant from Greaves thumping this through wide mid-off to the rope. Sizzling shot to this pitched up ball on fourth stump and it splits the gap with extra cover on the ring!
yorker on leg stump is jammed out to long-on for a long single.

shortText: Taskin Ahmed to Davey, no run
text: yorker again, jammed out back to Tasking. Good start and end to the over sandwiched around some major damage off the bat of Greaves.

shortText: Mohammad Saifuddin to Greaves, 1 leg bye
text: full on the legs, can't flick this away and goes off the pads into midwicket for one.
yorker sprayed down leg. Wide called.
yorker dug out through mid-on for one.
slower wide yorker, Greaves shuffled away across trying to scoop over fine leg and struggles to adjust before a cue shot is scratched into short cover.

missed runout! slower ball again, this time back of a length, tapped straight to extra cover where Mushfiqur shows why he's been a keeper all these years with a wretched throw at the bowler's stumps that misses by five yards. Davey was out by three yards if it hit.
Good length ball slapped through the ring for one.

goes for yorker but misfires it in the slot for Davey to heave this flat over wide long-on, who was cheating in quite a bit off the rope, and just clears the foam triangle for six. If he was on the line, it was a chest high catch.

shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Greaves, no run
text: slower wide yorker, Greaves out in front of it trying to heave to leg and misses.

wkt_text: CN Greaves c Shakib Al Hasan b Mustafizur Rahman 45 (45m 28b 4x4 2x6) SR: 160.71
text: slower ball works a charm again as the Fiz is up to his old tricks. It was going to take something clever to dislodge Greaves and Mustafizur has done it with a slower ball on the legs. Greaves flicks this high to deep backward square where Shakib holds on while crouching a few yards in from the rope.

wkt_text: JH Davey  b Mustafizur Rahman 8 (15m 5b 0x4 1x6) SR: 160.00
text: The Fiz is on a hat-trick! Pinpoint slower ball yorker on middle and off at 117 kph. Davey way out in front. Too classy by Mustafizur and off stump is uprooted.
poor hat-trick ball. Half-volley well outside leg stump flicked to deep square leg.
thigh high full toss lands in the 15th row over deep square leg! The Fiz goes for the slower yorker but misfires badly and Sharif flicks this deep into the temporary grandstand.
yorker on middle, Sharif digs it out to long-on and they take on a sharp second just making it in the end.
length ball, straightens in the fourth-stump channel. Liton is half-forward to defend, and gets a thick outside edge down to deep third

wow, what a way to begin. On the fuller side of a good length, a bit of swing straightening in towards off stump, and Soumya takes a step forward and picks it up with the swing to hit it over midwicket, one bounce over the rope

shortText: Wheal to Soumya Sarkar, no run
text: back of a length outside off, chopped towards point
length ball straightening towards off stump, presses forward and dabs to the right of extra-cover
full, angling down leg, clipped to deep square leg. The bowler gets away there, because Liton could have put that away past short fine had he waited an instant longer

shortText: Wheal to Soumya Sarkar, no run
text: back of a length, angling across to off stump, defended back to the bowler

shortText: Davey to Liton Das, no run
text: ooh, big away movement from an off-stump line. Liton looks to get forward to defend, and it zips away past his outside edge. Movement off the deck rather than in the air
full, angling into middle and leg, clipped to deep square leg

wkt_text: Soumya Sarkar c Munsey b Davey 5 (7m 5b 1x4 0x6) SR: 100.00
text: he found the boundary with this shot in the previous over, but now he tries the same shot with deep midwicket back. Not the greatest shot from Soumya, you'd have to say. Fullish, angling into off stump, and he looks to whip it away in the air. Not sure why he'd play that shot with the man back for it
back of a length on off stump, stays leg side of the ball and dabs to the right of backward point

shortText: Davey to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: length ball angling in towards off stump, clipped towards short midwicket

shortText: Davey to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: fullish, angling in towards off stump, gets forward for a push to the right of mid-off

shortText: Sharif to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 leg bye
text: length ball finishing around leg stump, misses the flick and he gets a bit of pad on it into the backward square leg region
back of a length outside off, chopped down to deep third

shortText: Sharif to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: length ball angling across to off stump, stays on the back foot and dabs to backward point

shortText: Sharif to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR
text: back of a length on leg stump, and that's cleverly done. Big gap between short fine leg and deep square leg, and Shakib shuffles across to help it away into that gap

shortText: Sharif to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: down the track now, stepping away from the stumps to make room, and Sharif follows him with a back-of-a-length ball that skids under the attempted pull and doesn't miss leg stump by much

shortText: Sharif to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: back of a length, straightens late into Shakib to cramp him as he tries to make room to cut. Ends up bottom-edging into the square leg region

shortText: Wheal to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: shortish, slanting away as Shakib attempts to make room, and he ends up having to reach for the ball. Slapped to cover point

shortText: Wheal to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: short on leg stump, cramped for room on the pull as he plays it along the ground to deep square leg

wkt_text: Liton Das c Munsey b Wheal 5 (18m 7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 71.42
text: down the track, and Bangladesh are two down! Wheal sees Liton coming and bowls a slower one angling into him to deny him room to free his arms. Looks to hit it straight, doesn't get the power or elevation he wants, and Munsey takes a good catch at mid-off, tumbling to his right

shortText: Wheal to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: loud appeal for lbw as this length ball nips in from outside off but Mushfiqur, pressing forward, has got a thick inside edge into his back pad while looking to defend it
back of a length, angling into middle and leg, tucked away to deep square leg

shortText: Wheal to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: full on middle and leg, whipped firmly and Coetze dives right at midwicket to stop it

shortText: Davey to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: another big lbw appeal as Mushfiqur presses half-forward to defend, and the ball nips back to beat his inside edge. Was height an issue? Not given on the field, and Scotland have reviewed. Misses his inside edge, and hits him on the back thigh. Impact is in front of middle stump, and the ball is going on to clip the top of the leg bail, according to HawkEye, so it stays with the umpire
full, angling into middle and leg, clipped to deep square leg

shortText: Davey to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: length ball angling in towards off stump, gets on the front foot and clips it into the forward square leg region

shortText: Davey to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: fullish, angling in to finish close to off stump, presses forward and defends with soft hands towards backward point
fullish, angling into middle and leg, clipped to the right of midwicket. Played around his front pad there

shortText: Davey to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: length ball, angling into off stump from around the wicket, and maybe it nips back a little too. Shakib is on the front foot, looking for a push into the off side for one, and he gets a thick inside edge to short fine leg

back of a length close to off stump, lets it come and drops it with soft hands into the off side, and they pick up a quick single by the time the bowler sprints through in his follow-through to pick up the ball, slipping as he does so
back of a length, angling down leg, past the attempted flick

shortText: Sharif to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: lbw appeal, but that definitely pitched outside leg. Was looking to step across and work a length ball fine. Wait, what? Scotland have reviewed. There's no way that ball has pitched in line with the stumps. Yes, ball-tracking confirms it. Pitched a good foot outside leg stump

shortText: Sharif to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: back of a length at the pads, tucked away to deep square leg

shortText: Sharif to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: back of a length, angling in towards off stump, defended back towards the bowler

shortText: Sharif to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: full, angling into the stumps, shuffles across to clip to midwicket

shortText: Sharif to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: length ball angling into middle and leg, stays on the back foot and clips to short fine leg

shortText: Leask to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: full-toss dipping towards off stump, whipped to deep square leg

shortText: Leask to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: back of a length, straightening towards middle stump, cramps Mushfiq as he looks to punch into the covers. Is forced to jam his bat down and defend
tossed up outside off, driven to long-off

shortText: Leask to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 leg bye
text: fired down leg, misses the flick but gets a touch of pad on it down to short fine leg

shortText: Leask to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: shortish, slanting away into a wide-ish line, but the ball skids through quick and beats the attempted cut, goes under his bat

shortText: Leask to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: fuller now, on the stumps, clipped back to the bowler

shortText: Watt to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: back of a length, spinning in from outside off, punched down to long-on
wide of the crease, angles a back-of-a-length ball in towards off stump, makes room and chops it to the left of backward point, who makes a diving stop and saves at least a couple of runs

shortText: Watt to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: sees Shakib step out and fires it at his feet. Whipped down to long-on
makes room to drive a length ball from middle stump down to long-off

shortText: Watt to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: looks to make room and Watt fires it flat at the stumps. Swiped down to long-on, off the inside half of the bat, no timing at all
full, close to off stump, opens his bat face to squeeze it out to deep point
drops it short, and he rocks back to pull to deep midwicket

shortText: Leask to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: looks to make room and Leask bowls it flat and full on the stumps. Plays a flat-bat swipe down to long-on

shot. Steps across and lap-sweeps a quickish length ball on leg stump, to the right of the man at short fine leg. He does very well to sprint across and throw himself to his right to half-stop it at first, and then chase back and pull it in
bang. He loves the sweep, and he picks his line well. Length ball on leg stump, and he's quickly down on one knee to swat it over the boundary to the right of deep backward square leg
and another! Leask floats this one across, outside off, and Mushfiq loves sweeping from that line too. This one's the slog-sweep, and he easily clears the midwicket boundary

back of a length, angling across to straighten towards off stump, goes back and uses his wrists to clip it towards long-on. They chance a second run as the fielder runs in from the boundary, and a direct hit at the bowler's end would have sent back Shakib. Or even the bowler being in the right place next to the stumps

shortText: Watt to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: flat, back of a length on off stump, flat-batted down to long-on
back of a length, straightening just outside off, chopped away to the right of the diving fielder at point, and the man at backward point sprints towards the rope to keep it down to two
full, angling in towards off stump, whipped to long-on

shortText: Watt to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: sees Shakib looking to make room and bowls a flat one on leg stump. Slaps it towards extra-cover, where Coetzer misfields to allow the single
shortish, offers a bit of width, and it's cut away crisply but point gets a hand to the ball while diving to his right and he slows it down, so the man at sweeper cover can cut it off

shortText: Watt to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: back of a length outside off, swiped down to long-on

shortText: Davey to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: short and wide at 113 kph, slapped to the cover sweeper.
back of a length on fifth stump, Mushfiqur opens the face to run this to deep third man for one.

shortText: Davey to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: slower ball on the stumps, Shakib keeps his hands back long enough to flick this to deep backward square for a very long single. They wanted two but a good relay denied it.
short and wide at full pace, Mushfiqur pulls this 123 kph delivery over midwicket for one.

shortText: Davey to Shakib Al Hasan, no run
text: slower wide bouncer, Shakib way out in front with a pull and fans on it.

shortText: Davey to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 wide
text: Shakib charges and Davey tries to counter with a wide yorker but sprays it off the pitched. Wide called.

shortText: Davey to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run
text: missed runout! Coetzer is having a nightmare in the field today. Davey went for yorker and Shakib jammed it out into extra cover. The captain charges forward and has one stump to aim at from 15 yards with Shakib at least three yards short trying to make the single but the throw is two yards wide. Hands on head from the men in purple.

shortText: Greaves to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT
wkt_text: Shakib Al Hasan c MacLeod b Greaves 20 (53m 28b 1x4 0x6) SR: 71.42
text: How do you like that?! What a day Greaves is having. Rank half tracker but you know it's his day when he can fetch the wicket of Shakib with a ball like that. Shakib rocked back early to heave this over midwicket for six but the ball skidded a touch low and he wound up scuffing it closer to the toe of the bat. MacLeod ranges 25 yards to his right and takes a catch in stride at chest height along the rope.
skids this on quicker on fourth stump on a good length, swatted into midwicket for one.
charge from the captain to a full ball and heaves this in the air but safely in a gap at deep midwicket before MacLeod relays in for one.
short on the stumps, pulls this through deep midwicket, MacLeod and Wheal from deep square leg converge but can't deny the boundary.

shortText: Greaves to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: short on sixth stump, cuts this straight to point.
skids this flat and short down leg.
googly lands short on fifth stump, pulled flat to deep midwicket.

shortText: Watt to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: good length ball on fourth stump, goes to cut but picks out Greaves at backward point.

shortText: Watt to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: arm ball skids on from fifth stump, cuts to Greaves again.

shortText: Watt to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run
text: speared in very full on middle, jammed out to extra cover.
full and very wide, pushed out to deep cover.
jammed in full again, driven straight to extra cover.
full and very wide, just inside the guidelines and left alone. Correctly deemed legal.

wkt_text: Mushfiqur Rahim  b Greaves 38 (53m 36b 1x4 2x6) SR: 105.55
text: to quote Fazeer Mohammed, Mushfiqur... why did you do that?!?! Good length ball on the stumps, Mushfiqur premeditates a scoop/ramp over fine leg but goes too far across his stumps and misses a googly, leg stump knocked back.
short and wide, slaps this to the cover sweeper.
