full and wide, shovels this out toward Davey at deep cover, who grows alligator arms with the ball hanging in the air before dropping just in front of him. Needed a dive to make it into a chance and he wouldn't put it in.
full and wide, driven to long-off.
full on fifth stump, driven toward point, throw from Sharif to the non-striker's end is just wide or it would've been very tight on the third umpire.
googly lands on a good length on off, thick edge goes wide of Cross and Watt fumbles the ball at short third man to turn a single into two valuable runs.
good length ball on fifth stump skids a touch low to defeat an attempted steer to third man.
length ball cuts Mahmudullah in two on an attempted charge. Somehow the ball clears the top of leg stump. Nervy times for Bangladesh.
full on sixth stump, wild heave with Mahmudullah's head bobbing all over and he misses again.
full on off, heaves this to wide long-on where MacLeod dives along the rope to turn four into two. The tension is palpable as Scotland's fielders burst out in support of MacLeod's effort.
length ball on fifth stump, tries to swat this back over Wheal and it splices high just over extra cover for a nervy single.

the pendulum swings again as Afif ends the over with a clever boundary. Pinpoint yorker on off stump from Wheal but Afif jams it out with such deftness to beat short third man on the ring skittling away to the rope.
full on fifth stump, driven straight to Berrington at extra cover.
charges to make this into a low full toss slapped off the toe well short of long-on for one.

googly lands on a good length on fourth stump, carves this behind point for a definite one but they come back for a tight second. Direct hit from the boundary, but he's in by a yard. Afif showing his wheels off on that sequence.

shortText: Greaves to Afif Hossain, no run
text: dropped! Fullish length ball on fifth stump, goes to drive and a thin edge is spilled by Cross, who didn't stay low enough for long enough and it clangs off his gloves.
good length ball on the stumps, goes to heave this behind square but mistimes it for just one.
good length ball on fourth stump, slapped to long-on for one.
good length ball guided through the ring for a single.
super stuff from Afif. Picked the right ball for the scoop. Davey was trying for yorker but is too full and Afif flicks a low full toss over the ring fielder at 45.
full and wide, going for wide yorker but drives this straight to MacLeod for a single at long-off.
108 kph short on the body with a slower ball, pulls this flat to deep square leg.
short and wide off cutter slapped off the toe into cover.

goes for wide yorker, but Mahmudullah betters it with a reverse scoop to a 134 kph delivery to shovel this over short third man to the rope. Another crucial last ball boundary for Bangladesh gets them 12 off the over to keep pace with the required rate.
full on fifth stump, Afif shuffles across and drives to long-off.
full on off, smokes a drive past Watt's hands and Leask does a tremendous job at long-off denying a second run.

wkt_text: Afif Hossain c Davey b Watt 18 (22m 12b 2x4 0x6) SR: 150.00
text: the reluctance to come back for a second on the previous ball makes a difference! Watt darts this in full on middle and leg with Afif shuffling well across his stumps. Afif tries to heave this over midwicket but gets under it too much and skies this to the man on the rope. Too easy for Davey to pouch this five yards in from the rope.
full on middle, driven to Munsey at long-on for one.

shortText: Watt to Nurul Hasan, no run
text: full on off, scuffed back to Watt.
no last ball boundary in the over on this occasion. Watt finishes off a top-class over with another ball speared in full on fourth stump and it's guided away into cover for a pair.
low full toss at knee height on fourth stump, goes to drive and a thin edge goes to ground where Cross stops it behind the stumps on one bounce.

wkt_text: Nurul Hasan c MacLeod b Wheal 2 (5m 3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 66.66
text: full on fifth stump, heaves this a mile high but not far enough. MacLeod is stationed on the rope at long-on. He takes the catch angling his hips into position so he swivels with the ball coming down over the rope, but his body control is impeccable and flicks it back up to himself after coming back into play. Most people would take that with their back to the rope and struggle to maintain balance but he turned his body sideways to make it a much easier take.
in the slot on sixth stump, the captain is not going to lie down! Clubs this 10 rows back over the deep midwicket rope.
yorker on middle at 133 kph jammed back to Wheal.

wkt_text: Mahmudullah c MacLeod b Wheal 23 (40m 22b 1x4 1x6) SR: 104.54
text: slower ball full on fifth stump, MacLeod is a magnet on the boundary today. Mahmudullah skies this to the Glaswegian at long-on, and this time it's a far more casual take three yards inside the rope. Scotland are closing in on a historic victory to open up the World Cup!
length ball on middle, punched to extra cover for one.

yorker on middle and leg, goes to scoop this and miscues it off his helmet before it dribbles away for a run. Given off the bat, or more accurately the glove, before clanging into the helmet. Concusssion check in progress.
full outside off, shovels this over mid-off who was up in the ring. Bangladesh isn't done yet. 19 off 4 needed.
yorker follows him backing away from leg, scuffs it out back to the bowler for one.

full toss at thigh height clubbed high over square leg. Mahedi is desperately pleading for a no ball on height but it was definitely below the waist. Still it shows the nerves by Sharif, who misfires badly on the attempted yorker and pays the price.

low full toss on sixth stump at shin height, Mahedi flays this over extra cover for four but they needed to clear the rope on the full. Scotland will win this barring an illegal delivery off the final ball.
short ball on middle, pulled to deep midwicket for one. Scotland have won it by six runs!

shortText: Bilal Khan to Ura, no run
text: swing first up for the left-arm quick Bilal. On a length, 127ks, defended in front of middle and leg

shortText: Bilal Khan to Ura, no run
text: short of a length, outside off, Ura slashes at it and is beaten by low bounce

shortText: Bilal Khan to Ura, no run
text: swing back in again, and he plays this back to him again

shortText: Bilal Khan to Ura, no run
text: more swing for Bilal, he closes the face looking for a single, but can't beat midwicket

wkt_text: TP Ura  b Bilal Khan 0 (4m 5b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00
text: first wicket of the World Cup. Played on. the swing does it. The first ambitious shot of the innings, and he gets an inside edge on this inswinging delivery. He is bowled

shortText: Bilal Khan to Vala, no run
text: a wicket maiden to start off with. really full, swinging towards off from middle. Vala gets an inside edge onto the pad
and he gets away swing first up, beating the big drive from Atai
full, around off, swings away again. Defended this time

wkt_text: L Siaka  b Kaleemullah 0 (4m 3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00
text: another chop on. It is turning out to be a horrible debut for PNG. After two full outwingers, Kaleem goes short, Atai looks to pull, but the ball takes the bottom edge onto the stumps
on a length, this one angles away from him. Amini leaves it alone
Amini charges at him, Kaleem is bowling at 130ks, and he defends this length ball back to him
and PNG get their first run. Keleem gets swing again, back in to the left-hand batter, and it runs off the inside half of the bat for one

shortText: Bilal Khan to Amini, 1 leg bye
text: gets the swing away but starts too straight. Hits the pad but it is too far down the leg side for it to swing back in enough to get him the lbw

shortText: Bilal Khan to Vala, no run
text: slides down leg again. Trying too swing it from too straight. Kisses the pad on the way to the keeper

shortText: Bilal Khan to Vala, no run
text: goes full and outside off, 123ks, slight swing away, played with an open face to cover
nearly run out. Dabs on this, Amini calls him through as he is running to the danger end, but the throw from short third now comes at Vala's end and just misses
edged and no slip in place. Oh they had just taken the slip out. Bilal continues to get swing outside off, Amini pushes, gets a regulation edge, and enjoys his luck
this one is smoked back over mid-off. High back lift, smooth bat swing, and clears the field
Vala steps down and also backs away to make room to go over the covers. Beaten
on a length, slight movement away, beats him outside off as he pokes at it
down the wicket again, Kaleem pulls back the length, and he has given himself enough room to punch this on the up and through cover-point
skips out of the crease, takes this on the full, and drives it wide of mid-on for four all along the ground
big slower ball, Vala adjusts for it and looks to hoick him over square leg, but he is still early into it. Beaten. It is the back-of-the-hand slower ball
down the wicket again, slower ball again, Vala adjusts for it and crunches a cover-drive, but can't beat extra cover
not sharp at mid-off from Zeeshan. This is short of a length, Amini has punched this hard, but the mid-off is deep at the edge of the circle and should stop it, but Zeeshan lets it through
down the wicket this time and gets a thick inside edge for one

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Vala, no run
text: on a length, no turn, middle and leg, defended to leg
slightly shorter and flatter, into the pads, punched wide of square leg for two

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Vala, no run
text: on a length, around off, goes with the angle, defended back to him

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Vala, no run
text: backs away to try to hit this over mid-on but is beaten by the slowness of the ball. Appeal for a stumping. The ball goes between the wicket and the batter, and Khushi does well to whip the bails off, but the foot is down

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Amini, 1 leg bye
text: slight movement back in, concedes a leg-bye
short of a length, tucked away off the hip for a couple past short fine leg
on a length, wicket to wicket, pushed wide of mid-on for one
lovely whip off the pads. He has skipped down the wicket, picked the slower ball, and used his wristly flourish to send it over midwicket
muscled away. Nadeem is short of a length, and he pulls this down the ground, wide of midwicket, all along the ground

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Amini, no run
text: slower ball, a full toss, he adjusts late, plays it to midwicket
skips down the wicket, chips this over the infield and gets it wide of deep midwicket for two

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Amini, no run
text: flat, on off and middle, defended back to him
short of a length, goers back to punch this to deep midwicket. A misfield by Ayaan Khan allows them the second
roundarm delivery, on a length, into the pads, worked away for one
nearly caught and bowled. Vala early into thus but doesn't check the shot. Lobs it to the left of the non-striker, Ilyas flies across the breadth of the pitch but can't even get a touch on it
slinger again, single into the leg side
on a length, not much turn, worked to leg for one
too short, and he goes back to pull this between the two deep fielders on the leg side. And it carries all the way into the advertising boards
swept away to deep midwicket for one
short again, he goes back to cut this to deep point for one
short again, cut in front of deep point this time, and Amini initiates the second and makes it
and he is cut away again for a single. Khawar won't be happy with the lengths in that over

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Vala, no run
text: full, on iff, driven back to him
short, wide, misses out. Gets just the single to long-on
down the wicket to drive this inside-out for a single to wide long-off
quick, flat delivery, runs off the inside edge for a single
on a length, no turn, pushed to long-on for one
looks for the big sweep, the slowness of the ball gets a bottom edge from him, misfielded at short fine by Nadeem to allow them a single
short again from Khawar, punched down to long-on for one
oh he is pitching them short again and again, pulled away to deep midwicket for a single. They don't run on the misfield

shortText: Khawar Ali to Vala, 2 leg byes
text: big appeal for lbw, given not-out, and Oman review it. First use of DRS this World Cup. Vala is looking for the big sweep as he finally pitches it up, he is early into the shot, is beaten comprehensively and is hit in the midriff but he is on his knees so that is still interesting on height. Hang on. The UltraEdge shows it has missed everything, including his body. That seems like a malfunction. Very iffy. They still use ball tracking to check for the lbw, and it is umpire's call on height. They get to keep their two leg-byes
flighted again, driven in the air, on the bounce to deep cover for one
full, into the pads, swept away to deep square for one
full, on the pads, nudged away for one
length ball on off, bunted to long-on from the back foot
floated up outside off, stretches on the front foot to work it through midwicket
drifts on the pads and is tucked through midwicket
given width outside off and he's stroked that through cover. There's protection in the deep

shortText: Aqib Ilyas to Vala, no run
text: fuller on off, driven to extra cover
thwacked. Drags it down short, it sits up, he rocks on the back foot and unleashes violence on it, sends it well over deep midwicket

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Amini, no run
text: good start, yorker on off stump and he jams his bat down to keep it out
fuller, punched towards mid-off, they take a quick single

wkt_text: CJA Amini run out 37 (47m 26b 4x4 1x6) SR: 142.30
text: direct hit by the bowler and Amini is gone. That's a terrific bit of fielding and presence of mind, but Amini will rue getting dismissed that way after looking so good. Back of a length on leg stump, he tried to turn it away, doesn't get bat on it, the ball is rolling back down the pitch and Amini, at the non-striker's end, has set off thinking there's a single in it. There isn't one and he's sent back, but by then Nadeem swoops down on the ball while running in his follow through, turns and lets loose an accurate throw that shatters stumps.

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Vala, no run
text: fuller on off, pushed to extra cover
leg-stump ball, flicked off the pads, it's going straight to short fine leg, who lets it go through his legs. Sloppy fielding. Bilal Khan the fielder.

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Vala, no run
text: full on the stumps, driven to extra cover's left, who moves and fields

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Bau, no run
text: captains collide into each other. This was bowled flat and across him on off, driven to the bowler's right, who moved to field and tumbled, right into Assad Vala at the non-striker's end. Vala looks like he's in pain. His ankle's hurt. Didn't look like a heavy collision, but Vala looks like he's come down awkwardly on his ankle.

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Bau, no run
text: flat outside off, looks to cut and misses

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Bau, no run
text: floated up across him, nice drift for Zeeshan, he misses the cut again
goes a bit deeper in his crease and opens his stance more to finally connect with the cut, through cover
stand and deliver. Ankle might be crocked, so Vala just comes on the front foot and has a free swing of the arms to send this crashing to the extra cover boundary
this time he goes straight. On the front foot and hammers it back over the bowler. Goes all the way. Fine manner to bring up a good fifty for Vala.

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Bau, 1 leg bye
text: length ball on leg stump, he misses with the tuck and it strikes him above knee roll and rolls away into the offside. Bowler thinks he's got his man with a prolonged appeal but the umpire not interested. They have reviewed it. I think where it pitches might be a problem. And indeed it has pitched outside leg. So Oman lose this review.
back of a length on the stumps, powerful wrists in play as he flicks through square

shortText: Mohammad Nadeem to Bau, no run
text: down the track while giving himself room, the bowler spots him and bowls into him, punched towards extra cover from close to body

back of a length outside off, cuts from close to his body, and the fielder at point - Jatinder - does well to dive to his right and get a hand to it. They hesitate a bit for the second and take it eventually. A direct hit might have been trouble
fullish on the stumps, punch-driven to long-off
fuller, flicked off his pads to deep square leg

wkt_text: A Vala c Jatinder Singh b Kaleemullah 56 (65m 43b 4x4 3x6) SR: 130.23
text: squirted up off the leading edge and Jatinder takes a good catch running in from long-on. Key strike with the death overs approaching. Vala had been looking to be more aggressive since that tumble from Zeeshan into his ankle, and he wanted to go towards wide long-on with this one. Gets a lot more height than distance, and the ball goes steepling but Jatinder calmly gets udner it and holds on.
back of a length going across him, bit of zip on that, and he misses the cut as it goes over the bat
stumps to stump, on a hard length, punched from close to his body towards cover, they pinch the quick single. There's a shy at the non-striker's end but no direct hit.
slower ball, offcutter coming into him, has to adjust late and tap it between mid-on and midwicket. That was just 97 kph

another slower ball, he's not got hold of it properly but still gets a boundary. Opened his stance and was looking to smash to midwicket, but it ends up slapped straight back over the bowler's head and into the straight boundary
that's strayed on leg stump, back of a length and he moves nicely inside the line to pull this fine, well clear of short fine leg to his left. The runs keep coming for PNG.

wkt_text: N Vanua  b Zeeshan Maqsood 1 (6m 2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00
text: done him. Nice loop and turn too. Drew him forward, looking to clip through midwicket after taking a few steps, dips and pitches so that he can't reach the pitch, turns and takes out off-stump
fuller outside off, gets down on his knee and thumps it through cover with a horizontal bat

wkt_text: S Bau c Jatinder Singh b Zeeshan Maqsood 13 (24m 13b 2x4 0x6) SR: 100.00
text: he's reverse-swatted him straight to short third man. That was a ball that deserved punishment, proper long hop, he opened his stance and looked to reverse hit it over point, but can only pick out the safe as houses Jatinder.

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Doriga, no run
text: fullish outside off, stretches on the front foot and pushes to extra cover

wkt_text: K Doriga c Sandeep Goud b Zeeshan Maqsood 0 (3m 2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00
text: three in an over for Zeeshan. Tame leading edge pops straight to point. They're not reading the turn at all, he closed the face to length ball too early, and that's as straightforward a catch as any.

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Ravu, no run
text: darted in quicker into him, he's played down the wrong line and is struck on the pads. Half an appeal but that was heading down.

shortText: Bilal Khan to Atai, no run
text: back of length ball in the channel, too close to cut and he misses connecting with the ball.

shortText: Bilal Khan to Atai, 1 leg bye
text: down the track, the bowlers bowls it into his toes, rolls off the pad towards backward point

shortText: Bilal Khan to Ravu, no run
text: digs it in short and the batsman is forced to duck under. That came onto him quickly

top edge lands just beyond Ilyas's dive at short third man. Ilyas seems to have hurt himself on his right wrist while landing. Length ball on leg stump, he was looking ot swing for the fences over square leg, gets a steepling top edge that is headed to no-man's land between short third man and third man. Keeper, point and third man all converging on it. Ilyas at point is the closest and puts in the dive, but it's too far, and he lands awkwardly on his wrist.
ramped fine, but fine leg is fine enough to run to his left and cut it off. Got into position early and scooped it over his right shoulder and out of the keeper's reach

wkt_text: SK Atai c Ayaan Khan b Bilal Khan 3 (11m 5b 0x4 0x6) SR: 60.00
text: short ball does the trick. He set himself up to pull but this got big on him and he only gets a tame top-edge that midwicket does well to catch, taking a few steps backwards and holding it over his left shoulder, tumbling but not letting the ball go.
fuller on the stumps, flicked off his toes through midwicket

wkt_text: D Ravu c Mohammad Nadeem b Zeeshan Maqsood 1 (9m 4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 25.00
text: stunning catch at long-on with Nadeem timing his jump to a nicety. This looked like it was headed over the boundary, full in the slot and he had a full-blooded golf swing at it. Travelled a bit flatter than he intended perhaps but seemed to have enough legs to clear Nadeem. But the fielder showed Michael Jordan-like hang-time in leaping up and holding on, then landing with a stable base so that no danger of stepping over the boundary.
pushes at this on off and gets an inside edge towards short fine leg

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Pokana, no run
text: fuller fired into him, tapped back towards the bowler

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Pokana, no run

text: strays down legside that time for what is the innings' first wide.

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Pokana, no run
text: coming into him again, misses the flick and is struck on the pads. Sliding down

shortText: Bilal Khan to Morea, no run
text: full on the stumps, driven towards cover
full on off, driven to mid-off's left for a single
slower ball on middle and leg, tickled to fine leg on the front foot
change of pace again, coming into him, he's not read it, a bit early into the flick and misses, but the ball goes off inside edge onto pad to midwicket and they get a single

shortText: Bilal Khan to Pokana, no run
text: digs it in short outside off and the batter has to sway out of the way
yorker on off, dug out to long-off
fuller, given width outside off, and swatted straight over the bowler's head, one bounce to long-off
gets down on one knee and slaps it to long-off
setting himself up for a big wind-up but this skids on and he can only send it to long-on from the under-edge of the bat
looking to carve it over extra cover, gets a leading edge and there's a diving effort at extra cover but the ball lands just out of reach

shortText: Zeeshan Maqsood to Pokana, no run
text: length outside off, moves across his stumps and looks to heave it over cow corner but can't connect
yorker length on off, squirted towards short fine leg

shortText: Morea to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: length ball outside off, cuts it to point

shortText: Morea to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: full and into the batsman, shaping into him, on the front foot to flick to midwicket
on the pads again, glanced fine and the short fine leg fielder is too slow on his feet to drag it back before the boundary while running back
too far down leg and he'll have to re-bowl that. Got inswing on that too but wrong line

good length probing at that off stump line, punched to mid-off and they set off for a quick single. The fielde rthere swoops in and looks to under-arm it to the stumps while tumbling forward, can't quite release it properly
flicked off his pads to deep midwicket's left

shortText: Morea to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: fuller on off, stretches on the front foot and punches towards extra cover, who fields to his left

shortText: Ravu to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: nice line, in the channel, on a hard length, goes to cut and misses. Was too close to cut

shortText: Ravu to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: a bit more width on that and he latches onto the cut, but can't beat backward point. Amini the fielder there.

shortText: Ravu to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: hard length on off again, cuts it again, but Amini into the action again

shortText: Ravu to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: fuller on off, this is driven on the front foot to point, loud call of 'NO' from Jatinder at the non-striker's end with Ilyas looking for a single

shortText: Ravu to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: Ilyas looking for another single but Jatinder opts to stay safe. PNG are a good fielding side. This was length outside off, steered towards point
he's not been getting the singles but there's no stopping that. Too short, swivels and pulls on the back foot to the backward square leg boundary. Powerfully struck.

shortText: Pokana to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: fuller on off, driven to cover

shortText: Pokana to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: full on off, driven punchily but straight to mid-off. No runs off the free hit.

shortText: Pokana to Jatinder Singh, (no ball) 1 run
text: given room outside off and it's cut to third man's right. he's overstepped on that, so it's a no-ball.
fuller on off, closer to off stump, gets an inside edge as he's looking to drive, balls rolls towards square leg

shortText: Pokana to Jatinder Singh, 1 leg bye
text: good length on leg stump, can't connect while trying to work it away, balls rolls to midwicket off pad. No fielder there so there's a run for the taking

shortText: Pokana to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: takes the pace off, length ball going across him in the channel. Too early into the cut and he can't connect
good length outside off, driven between cover and extra cover, who is fairly straight, for a quick single
length ball outside off, steered to cover's right for a quick single

shortText: Ravu to Jatinder Singh, 1 leg bye
text: goes right across his stumps to scoop, don't think he gets bat on it, the ball rolls off pad to short fine leg. Struck well outside the line thou the bowler was appealing vociferously

shortText: Ravu to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: back of a length in the channel, cuts it to backward point
too straight with this length ball, flicked off his pads to deep square leg
fuller into him, worked off his pads backward of square
pierces the gap this time with his cut. This one is clear of Amini at backward point to his right, and is timed to a nicety. Short of a length outside off, allows him the space for a rasping cut
length ball on off, pushed to mid-off

stump to stump on a length, pushed back to the bowler. He can't stop it and the batsmen are looking for a single. Mid-on swoops on it an dlets loose a throw, but it's a bit wild and they get over throws to fine leg
too short, and at that pace, it just sits up to be belted, he stands tall and pulls majestically in front of midwicket

shortText: Pokana to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: length on the stumps defended back to the bowler
slower ball on leg stump, waits for it and glances it to fine leg
slower ball again, but dragged too short, easy pickings there, just rocks back and swats it to the midwicket boundary
gorgeous shot. Pulled back just inside the line at deep extra cover. Fullish outside off, he gets a nice stride out and punches with superb timing through the offside

no stopping that one. Another punch through cover, checked his shot because he has timed it so well. Wasn't all that full but he is taking nice big front-foot strides and gets close enough to drive that

shortText: Morea to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: off-cutter on the stumps, pace off the ball, clipped to midwicket

shortText: Morea to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: another slower ball, off-cutter, on the stumps, pushed back towards the bowler

outside edge goes to the third man boundary. This time he didn't get to the pitch of the ball, didn't move his feet as much, and Morea got the angle across him going nicely. Thick outside edge flies quickly

shortText: Morea to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: drops short of the keeper. Dug in short, he went to pull, seemed to get a top-edge onto the helmet that lobbed up near him. Keeper sprints in but can't get to it.
darted into him, clipped through midwicket
strays on the pads, nudged softly through midwicket. They think about the second but decide against it. The man on the boundary was haring in fast and had a quick release too, so good call
floated up on the stumps, on the front foot to work it gently to midwicket for a quick single
tossed up fuller on off, gets on the front foot and drives to long-off
too short outside off, rocks back and cuts, there's a sweeper on the offside boundary to clean up

clever shot. Was coming down the track, the bowler bowled it shorter, but Jatinder had the presence of mind and field awareness to control his pull through backward square leg, where there's no fielder.

shortText: Amini to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: fuller on the stumps, squirted towards point
too short, and he gets hold of it nicely, rocks back and heaves with all his power to smack it over wide long-on

shortText: Amini to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: makes room and punches to short cover

clatterd to the square leg boundary. Too short again, this is pulled more square, there's a fielder in the vicinity who dives to his right and forward but the ball is too far from him, and hit too hard

shortText: Amini to Aqib Ilyas, no run
text: pushed towards short cover
length outside off, stays beside it and steers with soft hands towards point for a single
tossed up outside off, driven to long-off
tossed up again, down the track and drives it to long-on
flatter on off, pushed to long-off

tossed up too full, and it's a full toss outside off, he gets down and unleashes a slog-sweep of ferocity to deep midwicket. Siaka there mis-times his jump and ends up palming it over the boundary. That was hit hard.
driven to long-on
fuller outside off, stroked to long-off
tossed up on the stumps, driven to long-off
given room outside off and he cuts it nicely to deep point
mis-field by backward point allows a single. Ura the man. Given room to cut again with the ball too short, and he does so

almost spectacular effort by Siaka to save six at the square leg boundary. Bad ball, too short, and he lays into the pull shot. Siaka jumps up and throws the ball back into the field as he's coming down. But his foot has touched the boundary cushion when coming down so it's a six.
quicker outside off, glided to short third man's left
fuller on the stumps, driven to long-off
and dropped first ball. Just a chip to long-on, and it goes through the fielder's hands to hit him in the chest

shortText: Siaka to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: beaten on the cut as this is pushed through
pulls out the switch hit, drags it from what would have been outside leg to send this over point for four
pushed into the pads, nudged away for a single
wrong'un, played off the pitch, punched into the leg side. Slow turn, which gives him time to adjust
flat legbreak, punched down to long-on for one

shortText: Ravu to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: on a length, on off, defended back to him
full and wide, doesn't get a good connection, takes the single to cover

full toss on free hit, and he has smashed this over long-on for a six. The fielder. on the fence is tall, he jumps high, but can't get a touch on it. That is fifty for Jatinder, the first for an Omani batter in World Cups

shortText: Ravu to Aqib Ilyas, 1 no ball
text: full toss, and it is a high full toss. Is it a no-ball?. He has been taken at fine leg so we are checking replays for height. And it is way too high to be a legal delivery. This is a no-ball. Free hit coming up
short of a length, not much width, but he has punched this superbly square on the off side, beating point in the circle to his right and deep cover to his left
full and wide, would have been called wide had he not driven this to deep cover for one
bouncer on the free hit but it is too high so it is called a wide

shortText: Ravu to Jatinder Singh, 1 no ball
text: low full toss, driven along the ground to long-off. Another no-ball. He has overstepped
full and wide, sliced away with an open face over point and to the right of third man. He makes a tight second
long hop, and pulled away nicely between deep square and deep midwicket for four more
cut away for a single this time
on a length, closer to off, punched to deep cover for one
wide outside off as he looks to hide this away from his wingspan
full, just outside off, driven to long-off for one
short again and he is lucky Ilyas has found short fine leg

shortText: Siaka to Jatinder Singh, no run
text: short of a length, looks to cut it, doesn't time it well. A rare dot
flat, middle and leg, punched to long-on for one
pushes this off the back foot to sweeper cover for one
fuller, driven to long-off for one. A fifty for Ilyas too
another long hop to end this early. Jatinder launches this over midwicket and holds up his arms to celebrate
